ee standing ambulatory surgery center.&nbsp;<b>The following is required and must be received at the Institute to the attention of the Surgical Office at least 5 days prior to surgery:</b></span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\"><span style=\"font-size: smaller\">&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-indent: -1in; margin: 0in 0in 0pt 1in\"><span style=\"font-size: smaller\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></div>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li><span style=\"font-size: smaller\"><b>History and Physical performed within 30 days of surgery and completion of the attached &ldquo;Patient History &amp; Physical&rdquo; </b></span><span style=\"font-size: smaller\"><b>form which includes &ldquo;Medications and Dosage&rdquo; required by NYS Department of Health.</b> </span></li>\r\n    <li><span style=\"font-size: smaller\"><b>An EKG strip with interpretation within 1 year or less as you deem appropriate</b>. </span></li>\r\n    <li><span style=\"font-size: smaller\"><b>Any other tests, including lab tests deemed medically necessary by you.</b>&nbsp;If lab tests are ordered, your simultaneous submission of an appropriate medical diagnosis to the laboratory will be of assistance to both the laboratory and the patient. </span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\"><span style=\"font-size: smaller\">&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: justify; margin: 0in 0in 0pt\"><span style=\"font-size: smaller\">If time does not permit mailing, please fax all of the above to the attention of the Surgical Scheduling Coordinator at <b>fax (718) 728-0770</b> and mail the originals.&nbsp;Your help in the preoperative assessment is greatly appreciated.</span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\"><span style=\"font-size: smaller\">&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\"><span style=\"font-size: smaller\">Thank you. </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0