(15,'Consent for Cataract','Consent for Cataract',11,'<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div>\r\n<div align=\"center\"><b>The Mackool Eye Institute, LLC</b></div>\r\n<div align=\"center\"><b>&nbsp;</b></div>\r\n<div align=\"center\"><b>Consent for Cataract Extraction </b></div>\r\n<div align=\"center\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>1.&nbsp;I hereby authorize <b><u>Dr. Richard James Mackool</u></b> at The Mackool Eye Institute, L.L.C., to treat the cataract (opaque area that has developed in the lens) in my {SITE}<span>.</span></div>\r\n<div>2.&nbsp;I understand and agree that <b><u>Dr. Richard Jonathan Mackool</u> </b>may perform some tasks or parts of the procedure.</div>\r\n<div>3.&nbsp;The tasks they are expected to perform include, but are not limited to:&nbsp;</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p><br clear=\"all\" />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>Opening and/or closing of surgical site</div>\r\n<div>Dissecting (cutting) tissue</div>\r\n<div>Removing tissue</div>\r\n<div>Inserting a medical device</div>\r\n<div>Altering tissues</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p><br clear=\"all\" />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>4.&nbsp;I also authorize the physician(s) to carry out such diagnostic procedures to administer such treatments, and to administer such drugs, transfusion and intravenous medication as may be deemed necessary.</div>\r\n<div><span>5.<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span>My physician(s) has fully explained to me the purpose of the operation. I understand that this will be done by making an incision (cut) into my {SITE}<span>.&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div><span>6.<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span>I have also been informed of expected benefits and complications (from known and unknown causes), attendant discomforts and risks that may arise, during the procedure and the recuperation period, as well as possible alternatives to the proposed treatment, including no treatment.&nbsp;The risks include, but are not limited to:&nbsp;bleeding into the eye, infection, retinal detachment, macular edema (swelling in the retina), clouding of the cornea, inflammation, double vision, drooping of the eyelid, partial or total loss of vision or even loss of the eye, cardiac arrest, respiratory arrest, allergic reaction to medications, brain damage and death.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span>7.<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span>I consent to the photographing or videotaping of the operation or procedures to be performed, including appropriate portions of my body, for medical scientific or educational purposes, provided my identity is not revealed by the pictures or descriptive texts accompanying them.</div>\r\n<div><span>8.<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span>For the purposes of advancing medical education, I also consent to the admittance of observers to the operating room.</div>\r\n<div><span>9.<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span>I have been given an opportunity to ask questions, and all of my questions have been answered fully and satisfactorily.</div>\r\n<div><span>10.<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span>I understand that during the course of the procedure unforeseen conditions may arise which necessitate procedures different from those contemplated.&nbsp;I therefore consent to the performance of additional operations and procedures that the above-named physician may consider necessary.</div>\r\n<div><span>11.<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span>Any tissues surgically removed may be examined and retained for medical, scientific or educational purposes and such tissues or parts may be disposed of in accordance with accustomed practices.</div>\r\n<div><span>12.<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span>I acknowledge that no guarantees or assurances have been made to me concerning the results intended from the operation or procedure.</div>\r\n<div><span>13.<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span>I understand that certain procedures require the services of an as