(19,'Femtosecond Laser Consent','Femtosecond Laser Consent',11,'<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div>\r\n<div align=\"center\"><b>Richard Mackool, MD, PC</b></div>\r\n<div align=\"center\"><b>&nbsp;</b></div>\r\n<div align=\"center\"><b>Consent for Femtosecond Laser Treatment in Preparation for </b></div>\r\n<div align=\"center\"><b>Cataract Surgery and possible Limbal Relaxing Incision(s) for Astigmatism</b></div>\r\n<div align=\"center\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>1.&nbsp;I hereby authorize <b><u>Dr. Richard James Mackool</u></b> to utilize the Femtosecond Laser to treat the eye in preparation for cataract (opaque area that has developed in the lens) surgery&nbsp;and possible limbal relaxing incision(s) performed either manually and/or by utilizing the Femtosecond Laser in my {SITE}<span>.</span></div>\r\n<div>2.<span>&nbsp;&nbsp; I understand and agree that <b><u>Dr. Richard Jonathan Mackool</u></b>may perform some tasks or parts of the procedure.&nbsp;These tasks include, but are not limited to:&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p><br clear=\"all\" />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>Opening and/or closing of surgical site</div>\r\n<div>Dissecting (cutting) tissue</div>\r\n<div>Removing tissue</div>\r\n<div>Inserting a medical device</div>\r\n<div>Altering tissues</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p><br clear=\"all\" />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>3.<span>&nbsp;&nbsp; I also authorize the physician(s) to carry out such diagnostic procedures to administer such treatments, and to administer such drugs, transfusion and intravenous medication as may be deemed necessary.</span></div>\r\n<div>4.<span>&nbsp;&nbsp; My physician(s) has fully explained to me the purpose of the procedure/s. I understand that the procedure/s will be done by making an incision(s) (cut/s) into my&nbsp;{SITE} either manually or utilizing the Femtosecond Laser. </span></div>\r\n<div>5.<span>&nbsp;&nbsp; I have also been informed of expected benefits and complications (from known and unknown causes), attendant discomforts and risks that may arise, during the procedure and the recuperation period, as well as possible alternatives to the proposed treatment, including no treatment.&nbsp;The risks include, but are not limited to:&nbsp;bleeding into the eye, infection, retinal detachment, macular edema (swelling in the retina), clouding of the cornea, inflammation, double vision, drooping of the eyelid, partial or total loss of vision or even loss of the eye, cardiac arrest, respiratory arrest, allergic reaction to medications, brain damage and death.&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div><span>6.<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span>I consent to the photographing or videotaping of the operation or procedures to be performed, including appropriate portions of my body, for medical scientific or educational purposes, provided my identity is not revealed by the pictures or descriptive texts accompanying them.</div>\r\n<div><span>7.<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span>For the purposes of advancing medical education, I also consent to the admittance of observers to the operating room.</div>\r\n<div><span>8.<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span>I have been given an opportunity to ask questions, and all of my questions have been answered fully and satisfactorily.</div>\r\n<div><span>9.<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span>I understand that during the course of the procedure unforeseen conditions may arise which necessitate procedures different from those contemplated.&nbsp;I therefore consent to the performance of additional operations and procedures that the above-named physician may consider necessary.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span>10.<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span>Any tissues surgically removed may be examined and retained for medical, scientific or educational purposes and such tissues or parts may be disposed of in accordance with accustomed practices.</div>\r\n<div><span>11.<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span>I acknowledge that no guarantees or assurances have been made to me concerning the results intended from the operation or procedure.</div>\r\n<div><span>12.<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span>I understand that certain procedures require the services of an assistant surgeon, and I authorize Richard James Mackool, MD to utilize the services of an assistant should he(they) decide that this is necessary during the procedure that I have authorized him(them) to perform.</div>\r\n<div><span>13.<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span>I confirm that I have read and fully understand the above information.&nbsp;All blank spaces have been completed prior to my signing.&nbsp;I have crossed out any paragraphs or words above that do not pertain to me.</div>\r\n<div><b>&nbsp;</b></div>\r\n<div><b>Patient Acceptance or Risk</b></div>\r\n<div>I understand that it is not possible for my surgeon(s) to inform me of all of the possible risks of my surgery.&nbsp;I do certify that I was given the consent form to take home with me and consider its contents prior to the day of surgery.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span><u>{SIGNATURE}</u></span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span><u><br />\r\n</u>Patient {TEXTBOX_XSMALL}/Relative {TEXTBOX_XSMALL}/Guardian {TEXTBOX_XSMALL}*</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span>Print Name: {TEXTBOX_MEDIUM}&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span>Date/Time: {DATE} / {TEXTBOX_MEDIUM}</span></div>\r\n<div><span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <u><br />\r\n</u>Relationship to Patient: {TEXTBOX_MEDIUM}&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbs