(33,'Attendings YAG PC Consent','Attendings YAG PC Consent',1,'<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div>\r\n<div align=\"center\"><b>The Mackool Eye Institute, LLC</b></div>\r\n<div align=\"center\"><b>Consent for YAG Laser Posterior Capsulotomy</b></div>\r\n<div><span>1.<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span>I hereby authorize&nbsp;{SURGEON NAME}&nbsp;at The Mackool Eye Institute, L.L.C., to perform a YAG Laser Capsulotomy upon me/the named patient.&nbsp;I understand that this procedure involves making an incision (cut) in the center of the lens capsule (covering) after removal of a cataract.&nbsp;I further understand that the purpose of the laser (high energy, focused light) treatment is to decrease the cloudiness of the lens capsule (covering) so I can see more clearly.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span>2.<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span>I am aware that this procedure will be done on the {SITE}<span>.</span></div>\r\n<div><span>3.<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span>I understand that the procedure involves the use of a laser to cut the lens capsule.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<span>4.<span>&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span>My physician has fully explained to me the purpose of the procedure and has also informed me of expected benefits and complications (from known and unknown causes), attendant discomforts and risks that may arise, both during the procedure and the recuperation period, as well as possible alternatives to the proposed treatment, including no treatment.&nbsp;The attendant risks of no treatment have also been discussed.&nbsp;I have been given an opportunity to ask questions, and all of my questions have been answered fully and satisfactorily.</div>\r\n<div><span>5.<span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span>The risks include, but are not limited to:&nbsp;allergic reaction to medication, increased intraocular pressure (pressure inside the eye), detachment of the retina, macular edema (swelling of the center of the retina), damage to or displacem