ze:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:\r\n-.2pt\">A. OUR COMMITMENT TO YOUR PRIVACY</span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;\r\nmso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:11.9pt;margin-right:2.5pt;margin-bottom:\r\n0in;margin-left:2.9pt;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;background:white\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:\r\n-.45pt\">Our practice is dedicated to maintaining the privacy of your individually identifiable health information (IIHI). In </span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:\r\n-.5pt\">conducting our business, we will create records regarding you and the treatment and services we provide to you. We </span><span style=\"font-size:\r\n11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:-.45pt\">are required by law to maintain the confidentiality of health information that identifies you. We also are required by </span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;\r\nmso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:-.4pt\">law to provide you with this notice of our legal duties and the privacy practices that we maintain in our practice </span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt;\r\ncolor:black;letter-spacing:-.45pt\">concerning your IIHI. By federal and state law, we must follow the terms of the notice of privacy practices that we </span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt;color:black\">have in effect at the time.</span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:10.45pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:\r\n0in;margin-left:2.9pt;margin-bottom:.0001pt;background:white\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:\r\n-.5pt\">We realize that these laws are complicated, but we must provide you with the following important information:</span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;\r\nmso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:.15in;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:0in;\r\nmargin-left:2.5pt;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-indent:0in;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;\r\ntab-stops:20.9pt;background:white\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size:\r\n11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt;color:black\"><span style=\"mso-list:Ignore\">&bull;<span style=\"font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:\r\n-.55pt\">How we may use and disclose your IIHI</span><span style=\"font-size:\r\n11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt;color:black\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left:2.5pt;text-indent:0in;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;\r\ntab-stops:20.9pt;background:white\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size:\r\n11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt;color:black\"><span style=\"mso-list:Ignore\">&bull;<span style=\"font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:\r\n-.5pt\">Your privacy rights in your IIHI</span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;\r\nmso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt;color:black\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left:2.5pt;text-indent:0in;mso-list:l0 level1 lfo1;\r\ntab-stops:20.9pt;background:white\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size:\r\n11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt;color:black\"><span style=\"mso-list:Ignore\">&bull;<span style=\"font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:\r\n-.45pt\">Our obligations concerning the use and disclosure of your IIHI</span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt;color:black\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:14.05pt;margin-right:4.7pt;margin-bottom:\r\n0in;margin-left:1.45pt;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;background:\r\nwhite\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt;color:black;\r\nletter-spacing:-.2pt\">The terms of this notice apply to all records containing your IIHI that are created or retained by our practice. We reserve the right to revise or amend this Notice of Privacy Practices. Any revision or amendment to this </span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt;color:black;\r\nletter-spacing:-.15pt\">notice will be effective for all of your records that our practice has created or maintained in the past, and for </span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:\r\n-.2pt\">any of your records that we may create or maintain in the future. Our practice will post a copy of our current Notice in our offices in a visible location at all times, and you may request a copy of our most current Notice </span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt;color:black\">at any time.</span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:10.1pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:\r\n0in;margin-left:1.1pt;margin-bottom:.0001pt;tab-stops:19.45pt;background:white\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:\r\n-.4pt\">B.</span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt;\r\ncolor:black\"><span style=\"mso-tab-count:1\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span><span style=\"letter-spacing:-.35pt\">IF YOU HAVE QUESTIONS ABOUT THIS NOTICE, PLEASE CONTACT:</span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left:19.8pt;background:white\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:\r\n-.45pt\">Jeanne Mackool, Privacy Officer and Administrator, 31-27 41 Street, Astoria, NY 11103, 718-728-3400.</span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:\r\n10.0pt\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:11.15pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:\r\n0in;margin-left:19.45pt;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-indent:-18.35pt;tab-stops:\r\n19.45pt;background:white\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:\r\n10.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:-.25pt\">C.</span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;\r\nmso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt;color:black\"><span style=\"mso-tab-count:1\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span><span style=\"letter-spacing:-.45pt\">WE MAY USE AND DISCLOSE YOUR INDIVIDUALLY IDENTIFIABLE HEALTH INFORMATION<br />\r\n</span>(IIHI) IN THE FOLLOWING WAYS</span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;\r\nmso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:10.45pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:\r\n0in;margin-left:.7pt;margin-bottom:.0001pt;background:white\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:\r\n-.5pt\">The following categories describe the different ways in which we may use and disclose your IIHI.</span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:\r\n10.0pt\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:11.15pt;margin-right:6.1pt;margin-bottom:\r\n0in;margin-left:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;background:white\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:\r\n-.35pt\">1. Treatment. Our practice may use your IIHI to treat you. For example, we may ask you to have laboratory tests (such as blood or urine tests), and we may use the results to help us reach a diagnosis. We might use your IIHI in </span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:\r\n-.45pt\">order to write a prescription for you, or we might disclose your IIHI to a pharmacy when we order a prescription for </span><span style=\"font-size:\r\n11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:-.35pt\">you. Many of the people who work for our practice&mdash;including, but not limited to, our doctors, technicians and nurses&mdash;may use or disclose your IIHI in order to treat you or to assist others in your treatment. Additionally, we </span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:\r\n-.45pt\">may disclose your IIHI to others who may assist in your care, such it your spouse, children or parents. Finally, we may also disclose your IIHI to other health care providers for purposes related to your treatment. </span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:\r\n-.35pt\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left:0in;text-align:justify;text-indent:0in;\r\nmso-list:l9 level1 lfo5;tab-stops:23.0pt;background:white\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:18.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:\r\n-.75pt\"><span style=\"mso-list:Ignore\">2.<span style=\"font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:\r\n18.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:-.4pt\">Payment. Our practice may use and disclose your IIHI in order to bill and collect payment for the services and items you may receive from us. For example, we may contact your health insurer to certify that you are eligible for benefits (and for what range of benefits), and we may provide your insurer with details regarding your treatment to </span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:18.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:\r\n-.35pt\">determine if your insurer will cover, or pay for, your treatment We also may use and disclose your IIHI to obtain </span><span style=\"font-size:\r\n11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:18.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:-.4pt\">payment from third parties that may be responsible for such costs, such as family members, Also, we may use your </span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:\r\n18.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:-.55pt\">HH1 to bill you directly for services and items. We may disclose your IIHI to other health care providers and entities </span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:18.0pt;\r\ncolor:black\">to assist in their billing and collection efforts.<span style=\"letter-spacing:-.75pt\"><o:p></o:p></span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:22.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:\r\n0in;margin-left:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:0in;\r\nmso-list:l9 level1 lfo5;tab-stops:23.0pt;background:white\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:18.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:\r\n-.75pt\"><span style=\"mso-list:Ignore\">3.<span style=\"font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:\r\n18.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:-.3pt\">Health Care Operations. Our practice may use and disclose your IIHI to operate our business. As examples of </span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:18.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:\r\n-.45pt\">the ways in which we may use and disclose your information for our operations, our practice may use your JIH1 to </span><span style=\"font-size:\r\n11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:18.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:-.4pt\">evaluate the quality of care you received from us, or to conduct cost-management and business planning activities for our practice. We may disclose your IIHI to other health care providers and entities to assist in their health care </span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:18.0pt;color:black\">operations.<span style=\"letter-spacing:-.75pt\"><o:p></o:p></span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:21.0pt;margin-right:4.0pt;margin-bottom:\r\n0in;margin-left:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:0in;\r\nmso-list:l9 level1 lfo5;tab-stops:23.0pt;background:white\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:18.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:\r\n-.75pt\"><span style=\"mso-list:Ignore\">4.<span style=\"font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:\r\n18.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:-.35pt\">Appointment Reminders. Our practice may use and disclose your IIHI to contact you and remind you of an </span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:18.0pt;color:black\">appointment.<span style=\"letter-spacing:-.75pt\"><o:p></o:p></span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:21.0pt;margin-right:4.0pt;margin-bottom:\r\n0in;margin-left:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:0in;\r\nmso-list:l9 level1 lfo5;tab-stops:23.0pt;background:white\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:18.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:\r\n-.25pt\"><span style=\"mso-list:Ignore\">5.<span style=\"font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:\r\n18.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:-.45pt\">Treatment Options. Our practice may use and disclose your IIHI to inform you of potential treatment options or </span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:18.0pt;color:black\">alternatives.<span style=\"letter-spacing:-.25pt\"><o:p></o:p></span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:21.0pt;margin-right:5.0pt;margin-bottom:\r\n0in;margin-left:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:0in;\r\nmso-list:l9 level1 lfo5;tab-stops:23.0pt;background:white\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:18.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:\r\n-.75pt\"><span style=\"mso-list:Ignore\">6.<span style=\"font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:\r\n18.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:-.35pt\">Health-Related Benefits and Services. Our practice may use and disclose your IIHI to inform you of health-</span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:18.0pt;color:black\">related benefits or services that may be of interest to you.<span style=\"letter-spacing:-.75pt\"><o:p></o:p></span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:20.0pt;margin-right:4.0pt;margin-bottom:\r\n0in;margin-left:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:0in;\r\nmso-list:l9 level1 lfo5;tab-stops:23.0pt;background:white\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:18.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:\r\n-.75pt\"><span style=\"mso-list:Ignore\">7.<span style=\"font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:\r\n18.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:-.2pt\">Release of Information to Family/Friends. Our practice may release your IIHI to a friend or family member </span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:18.0pt;color:black;\r\nletter-spacing:-.5pt\">that is involved in your care, or who assists in taking care of you. For example, a parent or guardian may ask that a </span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:18.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:\r\n-.25pt\">babysitter take their child to the pediatrician\'s office for treatment of a cold. In this example, the babysitter may </span><span style=\"font-size:\r\n11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:18.0pt;color:black\">have access to this child\'s medical information.<span style=\"letter-spacing:-.75pt\"><o:p></o:p></span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:19.0pt;margin-right:6.0pt;margin-bottom:\r\n0in;margin-left:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:0in;\r\nmso-list:l9 level1 lfo5;tab-stops:23.0pt;background:white\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:18.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:\r\n-.35pt\"><span style=\"mso-list:Ignore\">8.<span style=\"font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:\r\n18.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:-.25pt\">Disclosures Required By Law. Our practice will use and disclose your IIHI when we are required to do so by </span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:18.0pt;color:black\">federal, state or local law.<span style=\"letter-spacing:-.35pt\"><o:p></o:p></span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left:5.0pt;background:white\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:18.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:\r\n-.3pt\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left:5.0pt;background:white\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:18.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:\r\n-.3pt\">D. USE AND DISCLOSURE OF YOUR IIHI IN CERTAIN SPECIAL CIRCUMSTANCES</span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:19.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:\r\n0in;margin-left:4.0pt;margin-bottom:.0001pt;background:white\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:22.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:\r\n-.15pt\">The following categories describe unique scenarios in which we may use or disclose your </span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:22.0pt;\r\ncolor:black\">identifiable health information:</span><span style=\"font-size:\r\n11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:20.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:\r\n0in;margin-left:4.0pt;margin-bottom:.0001pt;background:white\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:18.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:\r\n-.4pt;mso-bidi-font-weight:bold\">1. Public </span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;\r\nmso-bidi-font-size:18.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:-.4pt\">Health <span style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight:bold\">Risks.<b> </b></span>Our practice may disclose your UHI to public health authorities that are authorized by law </span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:18.0pt;color:black\">to collect information for the purpose of:</span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:\r\n10.0pt\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpFirst\" style=\"margin-top:20.0pt;mso-add-space:auto;\r\ntext-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l3 level1 lfo9;background:white\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:18.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:\r\n-.5pt\"><span style=\"mso-list:Ignore\">1.<span style=\"font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:\r\n18.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:-.5pt\">maintaining vital records, such as births and deaths<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"margin-top:20.0pt;mso-add-space:\r\nauto;text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l3 level1 lfo9;background:white\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:18.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:\r\n-.5pt\"><span style=\"mso-list:Ignore\">2.<span style=\"font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:\r\n18.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:-.4pt\">reporting child abuse or neglect</span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:18.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:\r\n-1.35pt\"> </span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:18.0pt;\r\ncolor:black;letter-spacing:-.5pt\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l3 level1 lfo9;\r\ntab-stops:33.0pt;background:white\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size:\r\n11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:18.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:-1.35pt\"><span style=\"mso-list:Ignore\">3.<span style=\"font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:\r\n18.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:-.45pt\">preventing or controlling disease, injury or disability</span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:\r\n18.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:-1.35pt\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l3 level1 lfo9;\r\ntab-stops:33.0pt;background:white\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size:\r\n11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:18.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:-1.35pt\"><span style=\"mso-list:Ignore\">4.<span style=\"font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:\r\n18.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:-.55pt\">notifying a person regarding potential exposure to a communicable disease</span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;\r\nmso-bidi-font-size:18.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:-1.35pt\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l3 level1 lfo9;\r\ntab-stops:33.0pt;background:white\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size:\r\n11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:18.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:-1.35pt\"><span style=\"mso-list:Ignore\">5.<span style=\"font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:\r\n18.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:-.5pt\">notifying a person regarding a potential risk for spreading or contracting a disease or condition</span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:18.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:\r\n-1.35pt\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l3 level1 lfo9;\r\ntab-stops:33.0pt;background:white\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size:\r\n11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:18.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:-1.35pt\"><span style=\"mso-list:Ignore\">6.<span style=\"font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:\r\n18.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:-.45pt\">repotting reactions to drugs or problems with products or devices</span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;\r\nmso-bidi-font-size:18.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:-1.35pt\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l3 level1 lfo9;\r\ntab-stops:33.0pt;background:white\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size:\r\n11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:18.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:-1.35pt\"><span style=\"mso-list:Ignore\">7.<span style=\"font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:\r\n18.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:-.5pt\">notifying individuals if a product or device they may be using has been recalled</span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;\r\nmso-bidi-font-size:18.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:-1.35pt\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpMiddle\" style=\"text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l3 level1 lfo9;\r\ntab-stops:33.0pt;background:white\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size:\r\n11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:18.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:-1.35pt\"><span style=\"mso-list:Ignore\">8.<span style=\"font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:\r\n18.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:-.45pt\">notifying appropriate government agency(ies) <span style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight:bold\">and<b> </b></span>authority(ies) regarding the potential abuse or neglect of an </span><span style=\"font-size:\r\n11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:18.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:-.5pt\">adult patient (including domestic violence); however, we will only disclose this information if the patient agrees </span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;\r\nmso-bidi-font-size:18.0pt;color:black\">or we are required or authorized by law to disclose this information.<span style=\"letter-spacing:-1.35pt\"><o:p></o:p></span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoListParagraphCxSpLast\" style=\"text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l3 level1 lfo9;\r\ntab-stops:33.0pt;background:white\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size:\r\n11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:18.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:-1.35pt\"><span style=\"mso-list:Ignore\">9.<span style=\"font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:\r\n18.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:-.5pt\">notifying your employer under limited circumstances related primarily to workplace injury or illness or medical </span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:18.0pt;color:black\">surveillance.<span style=\"letter-spacing:-1.35pt\"><o:p></o:p></span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:22.0pt;margin-right:5.0pt;margin-bottom:\r\n0in;margin-left:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;tab-stops:25.0pt;\r\nbackground:white\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:18.0pt;\r\ncolor:black;letter-spacing:-.25pt\">2.</span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;\r\nmso-bidi-font-size:18.0pt;color:black\"><span style=\"mso-tab-count:1\"> </span><span style=\"letter-spacing:-.35pt;mso-bidi-font-weight:bold\">Health<b> </b></span><span style=\"letter-spacing:-.35pt\">Oversight Activities, Our practice may disclose your IIHI to a health oversight agency for activities<br />\r\n</span><span style=\"letter-spacing:-.25pt\">authorized by law. Oversight activities can include, for example, investigations, inspections, audits, surveys,<br />\r\n</span><span style=\"letter-spacing:-.1pt\">licensure and disciplinary actions; civil, administrative, and criminal procedures or actions; or other activities</span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt\"> necessary for the government to monitor government programs, compliance with civil rights laws and the health care system in general. <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:22.0pt;margin-right:5.0pt;margin-bottom:\r\n0in;margin-left:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;tab-stops:25.0pt;\r\nbackground:white\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:22.0pt;\r\ncolor:black;letter-spacing:-.85pt\">3.</span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;\r\nmso-bidi-font-size:22.0pt;color:black\"><span style=\"mso-tab-count:1\"> </span><span style=\"letter-spacing:-.6pt\">Lawsuits and Similar Proceedings. Our practice may use and disclose your IIHI in response to a court or<br />\r\nadministrative order, if you are involved in a lawsuit or similar proceeding. We also may disclose your IIHI in<br />\r\n</span><span style=\"letter-spacing:-.7pt\">response to a discovery request, subpoena, or other lawful process by another party involved in the dispute, but only<br />\r\nif we have made an effort to inform you of the request or to obtain an order protecting the information the party has<br />\r\n</span>requested.</span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:22.0pt;margin-right:5.0pt;margin-bottom:\r\n0in;margin-left:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;tab-stops:25.0pt;\r\nbackground:white\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:22.0pt;\r\ncolor:black;letter-spacing:-.35pt\">4.</span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;\r\nmso-bidi-font-size:22.0pt;color:black\"><span style=\"mso-tab-count:1\"> </span><span style=\"letter-spacing:-.55pt\">Law Enforcement. We may release IIHI if asked to do so by a law enforcement official:</span></span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;\r\nmso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:20.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:\r\n0in;margin-left:.25in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l6 level1 lfo8;\r\ntab-stops:38.0pt;background:white\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size:\r\n11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:22.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:-1.25pt\"><span style=\"mso-list:Ignore\">1.<span style=\"font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:\r\n22.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:-.7pt\">Regarding a crime victim in certain situations, if we are unable to obtain the person\'s agreement</span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:22.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:\r\n-1.25pt\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left:.25in;text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l6 level1 lfo8;\r\ntab-stops:38.0pt;background:white\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size:\r\n11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:22.0pt;color:black;position:relative;top:-1.0pt;\r\nmso-text-raise:1.0pt;letter-spacing:-1.75pt\"><span style=\"mso-list:Ignore\">2.<span style=\"font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;\">&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:22.0pt;color:black;position:relative;\r\ntop:-1.0pt;mso-text-raise:1.0pt;letter-spacing:-.75pt\">Concerning a death we believe has resulted from criminal conduct</span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;\r\nmso-bidi-font-size:22.0pt;color:black;position:relative;top:-1.0pt;mso-text-raise:\r\n1.0pt;letter-spacing:-1.75pt\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left:.25in;text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l6 level1 lfo8;\r\ntab-stops:38.0pt;background:white\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size:\r\n11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:22.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:-1.35pt\"><span style=\"mso-list:Ignore\">3.<span style=\"font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:\r\n22.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:-.7pt\">Regarding criminal conduct at our offices</span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:22.0pt;\r\ncolor:black;letter-spacing:-1.35pt\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left:.25in;text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l6 level1 lfo8;\r\ntab-stops:38.0pt;background:white\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size:\r\n11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:22.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:-2.25pt\"><span style=\"mso-list:Ignore\">4.<span style=\"font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;\">&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:22.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:\r\n-.75pt\">In response to a warrant, summons, court order, subpoena or similar legal process</span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:22.0pt;\r\ncolor:black;letter-spacing:-2.25pt\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left:.25in;text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l6 level1 lfo8;\r\ntab-stops:38.0pt;background:white\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size:\r\n11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:22.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:-2.25pt\"><span style=\"mso-list:Ignore\">5.<span style=\"font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;\">&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:22.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:\r\n-.7pt\">To identify/locate a suspect, material witness, fugitive or missing person</span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:22.0pt;\r\ncolor:black;letter-spacing:-2.25pt\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:1.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:0in;\r\nmargin-left:.25in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-indent:-.25in;mso-list:l6 level1 lfo8;\r\ntab-stops:38.0pt;background:white\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size:\r\n11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:22.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:-2.75pt\"><span style=\"mso-list:Ignore\">6.<span style=\"font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;\">&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:\r\n22.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:-.6pt\">In an emergency, to report a crime (including the location or victim(s) of the crime, or the description, identity </span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:22.0pt;color:black\">or location of the perpetrator)<span style=\"letter-spacing:-2.75pt\"><o:p></o:p></span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:24.0pt;margin-right:3.0pt;margin-bottom:\r\n0in;margin-left:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;background:white\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:22.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:\r\n-.3pt\">5.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>Organ and Tissue Donation. Our practice may release your IIHI to organizations that handle organ, eye or </span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:\r\n22.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:-.6pt\">tissue procurement or transplantation, including organ donation banks, as necessary to facilitate organ or tissue </span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:22.0pt;color:black\">donation and transplantation if you are an organ donor.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:24.0pt;margin-right:3.0pt;margin-bottom:\r\n0in;margin-left:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;background:white\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left:2.0pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:\r\n0in;mso-list:l1 level1 lfo10;tab-stops:30.0pt;background:white\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:22.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:\r\n-1.25pt\"><span style=\"mso-list:Ignore\">6.<span style=\"font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:\r\n22.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:-.6pt\">Research. Our practice may use and disclose your IIHI for research purposes in certain limited circumstances. </span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:22.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:\r\n-.45pt\">We will obtain your written authorization to use your IIHI for research purposes <u>except when</u> an Institutional </span><span style=\"font-size:\r\n11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:22.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:-.7pt\">Review Board or Privacy Board has determined that the waiver of your authorization satisfies the following: (i) the </span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:\r\n22.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:-.75pt\">use or disclosure involves no more than a minimal risk to your privacy based on the following: (A) an adequate plan </span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:22.0pt;color:black;\r\nletter-spacing:-.6pt\">to protect the identifiers from improper use and disclosure; (B) an adequate plan to destroy the identifiers at the </span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:22.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:\r\n-.65pt\">earliest opportunity consistent with the research (unless there is a health or research justification for retaining the </span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:22.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:\r\n-.7pt\">identifiers or such retention is otherwise required by law); and (C) adequate written assurances that the PHI will not </span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:22.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:\r\n-.55pt\">be re-used or disclosed to any other person or entity (except as required by law) for authorized oversight of the </span><span style=\"font-size:\r\n11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:22.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:-.65pt\">research study, or for other research for which the use or disclosure would otherwise be permitted; (ii) the research </span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:\r\n22.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:-.5pt\">could not practicably be conducted without the waiver; and (hi) the research could not practicably be conducted </span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:22.0pt;color:black\">without access to and use of the PHI.<span style=\"letter-spacing:-1.25pt\"><o:p></o:p></span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:24.0pt;margin-right:4.0pt;margin-bottom:\r\n0in;margin-left:2.0pt;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:\r\n0in;mso-list:l1 level1 lfo10;tab-stops:30.0pt;background:white\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:22.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:\r\n-.75pt\"><span style=\"mso-list:Ignore\">7.<span style=\"font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:\r\n22.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:-.5pt\">Serious Threats to Health or Safety. Our practice may use and disclose your IIHI when necessary to reduce or </span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:22.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:\r\n-.6pt\">prevent a serious threat to your health and safety or the health and safety of another individual or the public. Under </span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:22.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:\r\n-.7pt\">these circumstances, we will only make disclosures to a person or organization able to help prevent the threat</span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;\r\nmso-bidi-font-size:22.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:-.75pt\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:28.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:\r\n0in;margin-left:2.0pt;margin-bottom:.0001pt;tab-stops:39.0pt;background:white\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:22.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:\r\n-.35pt\">8.</span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:22.0pt;\r\ncolor:black\"><span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes\">&nbsp; </span><span style=\"letter-spacing:-.75pt\">Military. Our practice may disclose your IIHI if you are a member of U.S. or foreign military forces (including </span>veterans) and if required by the appropriate authorities.</span><span style=\"font-size:\r\n11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:23.0pt;margin-right:5.0pt;margin-bottom:\r\n0in;margin-left:1.0pt;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;tab-stops:51.0pt;\r\nbackground:white\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:22.0pt;\r\ncolor:black;letter-spacing:-.75pt\">9.</span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;\r\nmso-bidi-font-size:22.0pt;color:black\"><span style=\"mso-spacerun:\r\nyes\">&nbsp;&nbsp; </span><span style=\"letter-spacing:-.4pt\">National Security. Our practice may disclose your IIHI to federal officials for intelligence and national<br />\r\n</span><span style=\"letter-spacing:-.6pt\">security activities authorized by law. We also may disclose your HHI to federal officials in order to protect the<br />\r\n</span>President, other officials or foreign heads of state, or to conduct investigations.</span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:24.0pt;margin-right:5.0pt;margin-bottom:\r\n0in;margin-left:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;tab-stops:37.0pt;\r\nbackground:white\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:22.0pt;\r\ncolor:black;letter-spacing:-.85pt\">10.</span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;\r\nmso-bidi-font-size:22.0pt;color:black\"><span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes\">&nbsp; </span><span style=\"letter-spacing:-.7pt\">Inmates. Our practice may disclose your IIHI to correctional institutions or law enforcement officials if you are<br />\r\nan inmate or under the custody of a law enforcement official. Disclosure for these purposes would be necessary: (a)<br />\r\n</span><span style=\"letter-spacing:-.75pt\">for the Institution to provide health care services to you, (b) for the safety and security of the institution, and/or (c) to<br />\r\n</span>protect your health and safety or the health and safety of other individuals.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:24.0pt;margin-right:5.0pt;margin-bottom:\r\n0in;margin-left:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;tab-stops:37.0pt;\r\nbackground:white\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:22.0pt;\r\ncolor:black\">11.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes\">&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>Workers&rsquo; Compensation. Our practice may release your IIHI for workers&rsquo; compensation and similar programs. <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:12.0pt;background:white\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt;color:black\">E. YOUR RIGHTS REGARDING YOUR IIHI</span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:\r\n10.0pt\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:9.0pt;background:white\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:\r\n-.1pt\">You have the following rights regarding the IIHI that we maintain about you: <o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:9.0pt;background:white\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:\r\n-.1pt\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify;tab-stops:27.0pt;background:white\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:22.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:\r\n-1.75pt\">1.</span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:22.0pt;\r\ncolor:black\"><span style=\"mso-tab-count:1\"> </span><span style=\"letter-spacing:\r\n-.45pt\">Confidential Communications. You have the right to request that our practice communicate with you about<br />\r\n</span><span style=\"letter-spacing:-.35pt\">your health and related issues in a particular manner or at a certain location.<span style=\"mso-spacerun:\r\nyes\">&nbsp; </span>For instance, you may ask that we</span></span><span style=\"font-size:4.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify;background:white\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:22.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:\r\n-.8pt\">contact you at home, rather than work. In order to request a type of confidential communication, you must make a </span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;\r\nmso-bidi-font-size:22.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:-.4pt\">written request to Richard J. Mackool, MD, LLC, Attn: Medical Records Dept, 31-27 41 Street, Astoria, NY </span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:22.0pt;\r\ncolor:black;letter-spacing:-.65pt\">11103, 718-728-3400 specifying the requested method of contact, or the location where you wish to be contacted. Our practice will accommodate reasonable requests. You do not need to give a reason for your request.</span><span style=\"font-size:4.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:22.0pt;margin-right:2.0pt;margin-bottom:\r\n0in;margin-left:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;tab-stops:27.0pt;\r\nbackground:white\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:22.0pt;\r\ncolor:black;letter-spacing:-1.25pt\">2.</span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;\r\nmso-bidi-font-size:22.0pt;color:black\"><span style=\"mso-tab-count:1\"> </span><span style=\"letter-spacing:-.5pt\">Requesting Restrictions. You have the right to request a restriction in our use or disclosure of your IHHI for<br />\r\n</span><span style=\"letter-spacing:-.4pt\">treatment, payment or health care operations. Additionally, you have the right to request that we restrict our<br />\r\n</span><span style=\"letter-spacing:-.85pt\">disclosure of your IIHI to only certain individuals involved in your care or the payment for your care, such as family<br />\r\n</span><span style=\"letter-spacing:-.35pt\">members and friends. We are not required to agree to your request; however, if we do agree, we are bound by<br />\r\n</span><span style=\"letter-spacing:-.75pt\">our agreement except when otherwise required by law, in emergencies, or when the information is necessary to treat<br />\r\n</span><span style=\"letter-spacing:-.65pt\">you. In order to request a restriction in our use or disclosure of your IIHI, you must make your request in writing to<br />\r\n</span><span style=\"letter-spacing:-.6pt\">Richard J. Mackool, MD, LLC, Attn: Medical Records Dept, 31-27 41 Street, Astoria, NY 11103, 718-728-3400.<br />\r\n</span>Your request must describe in a clear and concise fashion:</span><span style=\"font-size:4.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:10.0pt\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:20.0pt;margin-right:0in;margin-bottom:\r\n0in;margin-left:74.0pt;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-indent:0in;mso-list:l2 level1 lfo11;\r\ntab-stops:109.0pt;background:white\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:22.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:\r\n-1.25pt\"><span style=\"mso-list:Ignore\">(a)<span style=\"font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:\r\n22.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:-.75pt\">the information you wish restricted;</span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:22.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:\r\n-1.25pt\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left:74.0pt;text-indent:0in;mso-list:l2 level1 lfo11;\r\ntab-stops:109.0pt;background:white\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:22.0pt;color:black;position:relative;\r\ntop:-1.0pt;mso-text-raise:1.0pt;letter-spacing:-1.3pt\"><span style=\"mso-list:\r\nIgnore\">(b)<span style=\"font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:\r\n22.0pt;color:black;position:relative;top:-1.0pt;mso-text-raise:1.0pt;\r\nletter-spacing:-.7pt\">whether you are requesting to limit our practice\'s use, disclosure or both; and</span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:\r\n22.0pt;color:black;position:relative;top:-1.0pt;mso-text-raise:1.0pt;\r\nletter-spacing:-1.3pt\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left:74.0pt;text-indent:0in;mso-list:l2 level1 lfo11;\r\ntab-stops:109.0pt;background:white\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:22.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:\r\n-1.55pt\"><span style=\"mso-list:Ignore\">(c)<span style=\"font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:\r\n22.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:-.8pt\">to whom you want the limits to apply.</span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:22.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:\r\n-1.55pt\"><o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:23.0pt;margin-right:5.0pt;margin-bottom:\r\n0in;margin-left:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;tab-stops:27.0pt;\r\nbackground:white\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:22.0pt;\r\ncolor:black;letter-spacing:-1.35pt\">3.</span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;\r\nmso-bidi-font-size:22.0pt;color:black\"><span style=\"mso-tab-count:1\"> </span><span style=\"letter-spacing:-.5pt\">Inspection and Copies. You have the right to inspect and obtain a copy of the IIHI that may be used to make<br />\r\n</span><span style=\"letter-spacing:-.65pt\">decisions about you, including patient medical records and billing records, but not including psychotherapy notes.<br />\r\n</span><span style=\"letter-spacing:-.7pt\">You must submit your request in writing to Richard J. Mackool, MD, LLC, Attn: Medical Records Dept., 31-27 41<br />\r\n</span><span style=\"letter-spacing:-.65pt\">Street, Astoria, NY 11103, 718-728-3400 in order to inspect and/or obtain a copy of your IIHI Our practice may<br />\r\n</span><span style=\"letter-spacing:-.55pt\">charge a fee for the costs of copying, mailing, labor and supplies associated with your request Our practice may<br />\r\n</span><span style=\"letter-spacing:-.8pt\">deny your request to inspect and/or copy in certain limited circumstances; however, you may request a review of our<br />\r\n</span>denial. Another licensed health care professional chosen by us will conduct reviews.<o:p></o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:23.0pt;margin-right:5.0pt;margin-bottom:\r\n0in;margin-left:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;tab-stops:27.0pt;\r\nbackground:white\"><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:22.0pt;\r\ncolor:black\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-left:0in;text-align:justify;text-indent:0in;\r\nmso-list:l7 level1 lfo12;tab-stops:32.0pt;background:white\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:22.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:\r\n-.75pt\"><span style=\"mso-list:Ignore\">4.<span style=\"font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:\r\n22.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:-.7pt\">Amendment. You may ask us to amend your health information if you believe it is incorrect or incomplete, and </span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:22.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:\r\n-.35pt\">you may request an amendment for as long as the information is kept by or for our practice. To request an </span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;\r\nmso-bidi-font-size:22.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:-.65pt\">amendment, your request must be made in writing and submitted to Richard J. Mackool, MD, LLC, Attn: Medical </span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:22.0pt;\r\ncolor:black;letter-spacing:-.3pt\">Records Dept., 31-27 41 Street, Astoria, NY 11103, 718-728-3400. You must provide us with a reason that </span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:22.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:\r\n-.55pt\">supports your request for amendment. Our practice will deny your request if you fail to submit your request (and </span><span style=\"font-size:\r\n11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:22.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:-.7pt\">the reason supporting your request) in writing. Also, we may deny your request if you ask us to amend information </span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:\r\n22.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:-.75pt\">that is in our opinion: (a) accurate and complete; (b) not part of the IIHI kept by or for the practice; (c) not part of the </span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:22.0pt;\r\ncolor:black;letter-spacing:-.65pt\">IIHI which you would be permitted to inspect and copy; or (d) not created by our practice, unless the individual or </span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:22.0pt;color:black\">entity that created the information is not available to amend the information.<span style=\"letter-spacing:-.75pt\"><o:p></o:p></span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:25.0pt;margin-right:2.0pt;margin-bottom:\r\n0in;margin-left:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify;text-indent:0in;\r\nmso-list:l7 level1 lfo12;tab-stops:32.0pt;background:white\"><!--[if !supportLists]--><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:22.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:\r\n-.75pt\"><span style=\"mso-list:Ignore\">5.<span style=\"font:7.0pt &quot;Times New Roman&quot;\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></span><!--[endif]--><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:\r\n22.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:-.55pt\">Accounting of Disclosures. All of our patients have the right to request an &quot;accounting of disclosures.&quot; An &quot;accounting of disclosures&quot; is a list of certain non-routine disclosures our practice has made of your IIHI for non-</span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:22.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:\r\n-.5pt\">treatment, non-payment or non-operations purposes. Use of your IIHI as part of the routine patient care in our </span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;\r\nmso-bidi-font-size:22.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:-.7pt\">practice is not required to be documented. For example, the doctor sharing information with the nurse; or the billing department using your information to file your insurance claim. In order to obtain an accounting of disclosures, you </span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:22.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:\r\n-.45pt\">must submit your request in writing to Richard J. Mackool, MD, LLC, Attn: Medical Records Dept, 31-27 41 </span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;\r\nmso-bidi-font-size:22.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:-.65pt\">Street, Astoria, NY 11103, 718-728-3400. All requests for an &quot;accounting of disclosures&quot; must state a time period, </span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;\r\nmso-bidi-font-size:22.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:-.6pt\">which may not be longer than six (6) years from the date of disclosure and may not include dates before April 14, 2003. The first list you request within a 12-month period is free of charge, but our practice may charge you for </span><span style=\"font-size:11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:22.0pt;color:black;letter-spacing:\r\n-.65pt\">additional lists within the same 12-month period. Our practice will notify you of the costs involved with additional </span><span style=\"font-size:\r\n11.0pt;mso-bidi-font-size:22.0pt;color:black\">requests, and you may withdraw your request before you incur any costs.<span style=\"letter-spacing:-.75pt\"><o:p></o:p></span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"margin-top:24.0pt;margin-right:4.0pt;margin-bottom:\r\n0in;margin-left:0in;margin-bottom:.0001pt;text-align:justify