wise and may involve leaving a message on answering machines, or otherwise which could (potentially) received or intercepted by others.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left\"><strong>TREATMENT ALTERNATIVES: </strong>We will use and disclose your protected health information to tell you about or to recommend alternative treatments or options that may be of interest to you.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left\"><strong>OTHERS INVOLVED IN YOUR CARE: </strong>We will use and disclose your protected health information to a famiy member, a relative, a close friend, or any other person you identify that is involved in your care.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left\"><strong>RESEARCH: </strong>Under certain circumstances, we may use and disclose medical information about you for research purposes regarding medication, efficiency of treatment protocols, and the like. All research projects are subject to an approval process, which evaluates a proposed research project and it use of medical information. Before we use or disclose medical information or research, the project will have been approved through this research approval process. We will obtain an Authorization from you before using or disclosing our individually identifiable health information unless the authorization requirement has been waived. If possible, we will make the information non-identifiable to a specific patient. If the information has been sufficiently de-identified, an authorization for the use or disclosure is not required.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left\"><strong>REQUIRED BY LAW: </strong>We will use and disclose your protected health information when required to by federal, state, or local law.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left\"><strong>TO AVERT A SERIOUS TREAT TO PUBLIC HEALTH OR SAFETY: </strong>We will use and disclose your protected health information to a public health authority that is permitted to collect or receive the information for the purpose of controlling disease, injury, or disability.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left\"><strong>WORKER\'S COMPENSATION: </strong>We will used and disclose your protected health information for worker\'s compensation or similar programs that provide benefits for work-related injuries or illness.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left\"><strong>EMERGENCY SITUATIONS: </strong>In addition, we may disclose medical information about you to an organization assisting in a disaster relief effort or in an emergency situation so that your family can be notified about your condition, stautus, and location.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left\"><strong>INVESTIGATION AND GOVERNMENT ACTIVITIES: </strong>We may disclose medical information to a local, state, or federal agency for activities authorized by law. These oversight activities include, for example, audits, investigations, inspections, and licensure. These activities are necessary for the payor, the government, or other regulatory agencies to monitor the health care system, government programs, and compliance with civil rights laws.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left\"><strong>LAWSUITS AND DISPUTES: </strong>If you are involved in a lawsuit or dispute, we may disclose medical information about you in response to a court or administrative order. We may also disclose medical information about you in response to a subpoena, discovery request, or other lawful process by someone else involved in the dispute. We shall attempt in these cases to tell you about the request so that you may obtain an order protecting the information requested if you so desire. We may also use such information to defend ourselves or any member of our Practice in actual or threatened action.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left\"><strong>YOUR HEALTH INFORMATION RIGHTS: </strong>Although your health record is the physical property of the health care practitioner or facility that compiled it, the information belongs to you. You have the right to:</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left\"><strong>A PAPER COPY OF THIS NOTICE: </strong>You have the right to receive a paper copy of this notice upon request. You may obtain a copy by asking our receptionist at your next visit or by calling and asking us to mail you a copy.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left\"><strong>INSPECT AND COPY: </strong>You have the right to inspect and copy the protected health information that we maintain about you in our designated record set for as long as we maintain that information. This designated record set includes your medical and billing records, as well as any other records we use for making decisions about you. Any psychotherapy notes that may have been included in records we received about you are not available for your inspection or copying by law. We may charge you a fee for the costs of copying, mailing, or other supplies used in fulfilling your request.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left\">If you wish to inspect or copy your medical information, you must submit your request in writing to our Practice Administrator or HIPPA Compliance Officer, c/o Swagel Wootton Hiatt Eye Center, DBA as Eye Surgery Center of Arizona, 220 S. 63rd Street, Mesa, AZ 85206. You many mail in your request, or bring it to our office. We will have 30 days to respond to your request for informatin that we maintain at our practice site. If the information is stored off-site, we are allowed up to 60 days to respond, but must inform you of this delay.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left\">We may deny your request to copy in certain, very limited circumstances. If you are denied access to medical information, you may request that our Compliance Committee review the denial. The person conducting the review will not be the person who denied your request. We will comply with the outcome and recommedations from that review.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left\"><strong>REQUEST AMENDMENT: </strong>You have the right to request that we amend your medical information if you feel that it is incomplete or inaccurate . You must make this request in writing to our practice administrator, stating exactly what information is incomplete or inaccurate and your reasoning that supports your request. The admendment must be signed, dated and notarized. We are permitted to deny your request if it is not in writing or does not include a reason to support the request. We many also deny you request:</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left\">- we did not create the information, or the person who created it is no longer available to make the amendment;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left\">- the information is not part of the record, which you are permitted to inspect and copy;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left\">- the information is not part of the designated record set kept by this practice; or if it is the opinion of the health care provider that the information is accurate and complete.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left\"><strong>REQUEST RESTRICTION:</strong> You have the right to request a restriciton or limitation of how we use or disclose your medical information for treatment, payment, or health care operations. <em>For example- you could request that we not disclose information about a prior treatment to family member or friend who may be involved in your care or payment for care. </em>Your request must be in writing to our practice administrator. We are not required to agree to your request if we feel it is in your best interest to use or disclose that information. If we do agree, we will comply with your request. However, even with a written response, if the information is excepted from the consent requirement or we are otherwise required to disclose the information by law, we shall not comply with your request.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left\"><strong>AN ACCOUNTING OF DISCLOSURES: </strong>You have the right to request a list of the disclosures of your health information we have made outside of our practice that were not for treatment, payment or health care operations. Your request must be made in writing and must state the time period for the requested information. You may not request information for any dates prior to April 14, 2003 (the compliance date for the federal regulation) nor for a period of time greater than six years (our legal obligation to retain information). Your first request for a list of all disclosures within a 12-month period will be free. If you request an additional list within 12-months of the first request, we may charge you a fee for the costs of providing the subsequent list. We will notify you of such costs and afford you the opportunity to withdraw your request before any costs are incurred.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left\"><strong>REQUESTING CONFIDENTIAL COMMUNIATIONS: </strong>You have the right to request how we communicate with you to preserve your privacy. <em>For example-you may request that we call you only at your work number, or by mail at a spcial address or postal box. Your request must be made in writing and must be specify how or where we are to contact you.</em> We will accommodate all reasonable requests.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left\"><strong>FILE A COMPLAINT: </strong>If you believe your privacy rights have been violated, you may file a complaint with the Practice or with the Secretary of the Department of Health and Human Services. To file a complaint with the Practice, contact our practice administrator, who will direct you on how to file an office complaint. All complaints must be submitted in writing, and all complaints shall be investigated, without repercussion to you. The practice administrator can be reached at this number (480) 641-3937.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left\"><strong>USES AND DISCLOSURES NOT COVERED: </strong>Uses or disclosures of your health information not covered by this notice or the laws that apply to us may only be made with your written authorization. You may revoke such authorization in writing at any time and we will no longer disclose healthinformation about your for the reasons stated in your written authorizaton. Disclosusres made in reliance on the authorization prior to the revocation are not affected by the revocation.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left\"><strong>CHANGES TO THIS NOTICE: </strong>We reserve the right to change this notice at any time. We reserve the right to make the revised or changed notice effective for medical information we already have about you as well as any information we may receive from you in the future. We will post a copy of the current notice in the Practice. The notice will contain the date of last revision and effective date. In addition, each time you visit the Practice for treatment or health care services you may request a copy of the current notice in effect.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left\"><strong>FOR MORE INFORMATION:</strong> If you have questions or would like additional information you may contact our Practice Administrator or HIPAA Compliance Officer at (480) 641-3937.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left\">{SIGNATURE}&nbsp;{DATE}</p>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\">{LAST NAME} {MIDDLE INITIAL}{PATIENT FIRST NAME}{DOB}</div>','true'),
(54,'Informed Consent/Cat','Informed Consent /Cat',20,'<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in -0.75in 0pt 0in\"><b><font size=\"6\"><font size=\"3\">SWAGEL WOOTTON EYE CENTER </font></font></b></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in -0.75in 0pt 0in\"><b><font size=\"6\"><span style=\"background: #a6a6a6\"><font size=\"3\">INFORMED CONSENT- CATARACT OPERATION AND/OR IMPLANTATION OF INTRAOCULAR OF INTRAOCULAR LENS</font></span></font></b></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\"><b><font size=\"5\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt\">INTRODUCTION</span></font></b></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\">This information is given to you so that you can make an informed decision about having eye surgery.&nbsp;Take as much time as you wish to make your decision about signing this informed consent.&nbsp;You have the right to ask questions about any procedure before agreeing to have the operation.</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\"><b>&nbsp;</b></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\">Except for unusual problems, a cataract operation is indicated only when you cannot function adequately in your normal daily activities due to poor eyesight produced by the cataract.&nbsp;You must remember that the natural lens within your own eye with a slight cataract, although not perfect, has some distinct advantages over any man-made lens.</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\">After the doctor has told you that you have a cataract , you and your doctor are the only ones who can determine if or when you should have a cataract operation based on your own visual needs and medical considerations, unless you have an unusual cataract that may need immediatesurgery.</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\"><b>&nbsp;</b></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\"><b>Alternative Treatments</b></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\">I understand I may decide not to have a cataract operation AT ALL.&nbsp;However, should I decide to have an operation I understand these are the methods of restoring vision after the operation.</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\"><b>&nbsp;</b></div>\r\n<ol style=\"margin-top: 0in\" type=\"1\">\r\n    <li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\"><b>INTRAOCULAR LENS- </b>This is a small plastic (PMMA), silicone, acrylic or collamer artificial lens which is surgically placed inside your eye permanently.&nbsp;The intraocular lens may be made from either soft or hard materials, which may or may not contain ultraviolet light (UV) absorbing material.&nbsp;The UV absorbing materials absorbs UV light similarly to the natural lens, which is being removed.&nbsp;The intraocular lens appears to show no change in the size of the objects you see.&nbsp;Conventional eyeglasses (not cataract spectacles) are usually needed in addition to an intraocular lens to give you the best visionpossible.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt 0.25in\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<ol style=\"margin-top: 0in\" type=\"1\" start=\"2\">\r\n    <li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\"><b>SPECTACLES- </b>(Glasses) - Cataract spectacles required to correct your vision are usually thicker and heavier than conventional eyeglasses.&nbsp;Cataract spectacles increase the size by about 25%; and clear vision is obtained through the central part of the cataract spectacles, which means you must learn to turn you head to see clearly on either side.&nbsp;Cataract spectacles usually CANNOT be used if a cataract is only in one eye (and the other eye is normal), because they may cause double vision.&nbsp;Cataract spectacles are rarely recommended today.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<ol style=\"margin-top: 0in\" type=\"1\" start=\"3\">\r\n    <li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\"><b>CONTACT LENS- </b>A hard or soft contact lens increases the apparent size of objects only about 8%.&nbsp;Handling a contact lens is difficult for some individuals.&nbsp;Most lenses must be inserted and removed daily and not everyone can tolerate them.&nbsp;For near tasks, eyeglasses (not cataract spectacles) may be required in addition to contact lenses.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\"><b>&nbsp;</b></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\"><b>CONSENT FOR OPERATION</b></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\">In giving permission for a cataract extraction and/ or for the possible implantation of an intraocular lens in my eye I declare I understand the following information:</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<ol style=\"margin-top: 0in\" type=\"1\">\r\n    <li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\">Cataract surgery by itself means the removal of the natural lens of the eye by a surgical technique.&nbsp;In order for an intraocular lens to be implanted in my eye, I understand I must have the cataract surgery performed either at the time of lens implantation or before lens implantation.</li>\r\n    <li style=\"margin: 0in -45pt 0pt 0in\">If an intraocular lens is implanted, it is done by surgical method.&nbsp;It is intended that the small lens will be left in my eye permanently.</li>\r\n    <li style=\"margin: 0in -45pt 0pt 0in\">The results cannot be guaranteed.</li>\r\n    <li style=\"margin: 0in -45pt 0pt 0in\">At the time of surgery, my doctor may decide NOT to implant an intraocular lens in my eye even though I have given permission to do so.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in -45pt 0pt 0.25in\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<ol style=\"margin-top: 0in\" type=\"1\" start=\"5\">\r\n    <li style=\"margin: 0in -45pt 0pt 0in\">At the time of cataract surgery my surgeon may choose to correct any corneal astigmatism, which is present.&nbsp;I consent to the correction of the corneal astigmatism at the time of my cataract surgery.&nbsp;The doctor has explained the risks and benefits; I understand the risks and benefits.&nbsp;Complications may occur days, weeks, and even years later.&nbsp;Complications may include<b>, </b>but are not limited to, the loss of corneal clarity and infection.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in -45pt 0pt 0.25in\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<ol style=\"margin-top: 0in\" type=\"1\" start=\"6\">\r\n    <li style=\"margin: 0in -45pt 0pt 0in\"><b>COMPLICATIONS OF SURGERY TO REMOVE THE CATARACT:&nbsp;</b>As a result of the surgery, it is possible that my vision could be made worse.&nbsp;In some cases, complications may occur weeks, months, or even years later.&nbsp;Complications may occur include hemorrhage (bleeding), loss of corneal clarity, infection, detachment of the retina, glaucoma, and/ or double vision.&nbsp;These and other complications may occur whether or not a lens is implanted andmay result in poor vision, total loss of vision or loss of the eye.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in -45pt 0pt 0in\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<ol style=\"margin-top: 0in\" type=\"1\" start=\"7\">\r\n    <li style=\"margin: 0in -45pt 0pt 0in\"><b>SPECIFIC COMPLICATIONS OF LENS IMPLANTATION</b>: Insertion of an intraocular lens may induce complications which otherwise would not occur.&nbsp;In some cases, complications may develop during surgery of implanting the lens, or days, weeks, months, or even years later.&nbsp;Complications may include loss of corneal clarity, infections, uveitis, iris atrophy, and glaucoma, bleeding in the eye, inability to dilate the pupil, dislocation of the lens and retinal detachment.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in -45pt 0pt 0in\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<ol style=\"margin-top: 0in\" type=\"1\" start=\"8\">\r\n    <li style=\"margin: 0in -45pt 0pt 0in\">At some future time the lens implanted in my eye may have to be repositioned or replaced.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in -45pt 0pt 0in\"><b>&nbsp;</b></div>\r\n<ol style=\"margin-top: 0in\" type=\"1\" start=\"9\">\r\n    <li style=\"margin: 0in -45pt 0pt 0in\"><b>COMPLICATIONS OF SURGERY IN GENERAL:&nbsp;</b>As with all types of surgery, there is the possibility of other complications due to anesthesia, drug reactions, or other factors which may involve other parts of my body, including the possibility of brain damage or even death.&nbsp;Since it is impossible to state every complication that may occur as a result of surgery, the list of complications in this form is incomplete.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in -45pt 0pt 0.25in\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<ol style=\"margin-top: 0in\" type=\"1\" start=\"10\">\r\n    <li style=\"margin: 0in -45pt 0pt 0in\"><b>ANESTHESIA:&nbsp;</b>The administration also involves serious risks, most importantly a rare risk of reactions to medication causing death.&nbsp;I consent to the use of such anesthetics, as may be considered necessary by the person responsible for these services.</li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in -45pt 0pt 0in\"><b>&nbsp;</b></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in -45pt 0pt 0in\">The basic procedures of cataract surgery, advantages and disadvantages, risks and possible complications, or alternative treatments have been explained to me by my doctor.&nbsp;Although it is impossible for the doctor to inform me of every complication that may occur, the doctor has answered all my questions to my satisfaction.&nbsp;In signing this informed consent for cataract operation/ and or implantation of intraocular lens, I am stating I have read this informed consent (or it has been read to me). I fully understand it and the possible risks, complications and benefits that may result from the surgery.</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in -45pt 0pt 0in\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in -45pt 0pt 0in\">I wish to have a cataract operation with an intraocular lens implant.</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in -45pt 0pt 0in\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in -45pt 0pt 0in\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in -45pt 0pt 0in\">&nbsp;{SIGNATURE}&nbsp;{DATE}&nbsp;{Witness Signature}</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in -45pt 0pt 0in\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in -45pt 0pt 0in\">&nbsp;{PATIENT FIRST NAME}{MIDDLE INITIAL}&nbsp;{LAST NAME}</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in -45pt 0pt 0in\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in -45pt 0pt 0in\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in -45pt 0pt 0in\">Physicians Declaration:&nbsp;I have explained the contents of this document to the patient and have answered all the patients&rsquo; questions, and to the best of my knowledge, the patient has been adequately informed.&nbsp;The Patient has consented.</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in -45pt 0pt 0in\"><b>&nbsp;</b></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in -45pt 0pt 0in\"><strong>&nbsp;</strong>{Surgeon\'s Signature}</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in -45pt 0pt 0in\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in -45pt 0pt 0in\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in -45pt 0pt 0in\">&nbsp;</div>','true'),
(55,'Light Breakfast Ins.','Light Breakfast',20,'<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center; line-height: normal; margin: 0in 0in 10pt\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center; line-height: normal; margin: 0in 0in 10pt\"><b><i><span style=\"font-size: 12pt\">Please sign upon your arrival</span></i></b></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center; line-height: normal; margin: 0in 0in 10pt\"><b><i><span style=\"font-size: 12pt\">Plan on being at the facility <span style=\"background: yellow\">3-4 hours</span></span></i></b></div>\r\n<div style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 0in 0in 10pt\"><b><i><span style=\"font-size: 12pt\">Although the surgery does not take very long it is extremely important that your eye is sufficiently dilated and that can take some time.&nbsp;Everyone dilates differently.</span></i></b></div>\r\n<div style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 0in 0in 10pt\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt\"><strong><em>Surgery Date:{DOS</em></strong>}<strong><em> Arrival Time: </em></strong>{TEXTBOX_MEDIUM}</span><span style=\"font-size: 12pt\"><span style=\"font-size: small\"><i>This is not the time your surgery will be&nbsp;performed.&nbsp;</i></span></span><b><i><span style=\"font-size: 12pt\"> Location: Swagel Wootton&nbsp;Eye Center&nbsp; 220 S. 63rd Street, Mesa, Az. 85206 (480) 641-3937</span></i></b></div>\r\n<div style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 0in 0in 10pt\"><b><i><span style=\"font-size: 10pt\">Pre-operative instructions, <span style=\"background: yellow\">failure to comply</span> with these instructions may result in cancellation or post-ponement of your surgery.</span></i></b></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center; line-height: normal; text-indent: -0.25in; margin: 0in 0in 0pt 0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size: small\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman\"><b><i><span style=\"background: yellow\"><span style=\"font: 7pt \'Times New Roman\'\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></i></b></span></span><b><i><span style=\"background: yellow; font-size: 10pt\"><span style=\"font: 7pt \'Times New Roman\'\"><span style=\"font-size: small\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman\"><strong>INSTRUCTIONS FOR PATIENT HAVING </strong></span></span><span style=\"font-size: small\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman\"><strong>SURGERY PERFORMED IN THE AFTERNOON</strong></span></span></span></span></i></b></div>\r\n<div style=\"line-height: normal; text-indent: -0.25in; margin: 0in 0in 0pt 0.5in\"><b><i><span style=\"background: yellow; font-size: 10pt\"><span style=\"font: 7pt \'Times New Roman\'\">\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center; margin: 0in 0in 0pt\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n</span></span></i></b></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center; line-height: normal; text-indent: -0.25in; margin: 0in 0in 0pt 0.5in\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"line-height: normal; text-indent: -0.25in; margin: 0in 0in 0pt 0.5in\"><b><i><span style=\"background: yellow; font-size: 10pt\"><span style=\"font: 7pt \'Times New Roman\'\">\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center; margin: 0in 0in 0pt\"><span style=\"font-size: small\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman\"><u><strong>IF YOUR ARRIVAL TIME IS 12 NOON OR LATER, YOU MAY FOLLOW THE PROVIDED INSTRUCTIONS.</strong></u></span></span></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center; margin: 0in 0in 0pt\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center; margin: 0in 0in 0pt\"><span style=\"font-size: small\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman\"><b>&nbsp;</b></span></span><span style=\"font-size: small\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman\"><b><span style=\"display: none\" id=\"1337797010951S\">&nbsp;</span>&nbsp;IF YOU ARE <u>NOT </u>A DIABETIC YOU MAY HAVE A LIGHT BREAKFAST UNTIL 8:00 AM.&nbsp;&nbsp; PLEASE SEE LIST BELOW FOR FOODS YOU MAY HAVE.</b></span></span></div>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li><span style=\"font-size: small\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman\"><b>DO NOT HAVE ANYTHING TO EAT OR DRINK AFTER 8:00 AM.&nbsp;DOING SO MAY RESULT IN CANCELLATION OR DELAY OF YOUR SURGERY.</b></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li><span style=\"font-size: small\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman\"><b>IF YOU ARE A <u>DIABETIC</u> WHO TAKES ORAL MEDICATION.&nbsp;YOU MAY HAVE A LIGHT BREAKFAST UNTIL 8:00 AM.&nbsp;<u>DO NOT TAKE YOUR ORAL DIABETES MEDICATION BEFORE YOUR SURGERY</u>.</b></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n<ul>\r\n    <li><span style=\"font-size: small\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman\"><b>IF YOU ARE <u>AN INSULIN DEPENDENT</u> DIABETIC YOU MAY HAVE A LIGHT BREAKFAST UNTIL 8:00 AM AND <u>TAKE &frac12; OF YOUR USUAL MORNING INSULIN DOSE.</u></b></span></span></li>\r\n</ul>\r\n</span></span></i></b></div>\r\n<div style=\"line-height: normal; text-indent: -0.25in; margin: 0in 0in 0pt 0.5in\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"line-height: normal; text-indent: -0.25in; margin: 0in 0in 0pt 0.5in\"><i><span style=\"background: yellow; font-size: 10pt\"><span style=\"font: 7pt \'Times New Roman\'\">\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt 0.25in\"><span style=\"font-size: small\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman\"><strong>&nbsp;L<span style=\"background: yellow; font-size: 10pt\"><span style=\"font: 7pt \'Times New Roman\'\"><span style=\"font-size: small\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman\"><u>IGHT BREAKFAST</u></span></span></span></span> </strong>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt 0.25in\"><span style=\"font-size: small\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman\"><strong>DECAFFEINATED TEA OR COFFEE</strong></span></span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt 0.25in\"><span style=\"font-size: small\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman\"><strong>WATER</strong></span></span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt 0.25in\"><span style=\"font-size: small\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman\"><strong>CLEAR JUICE SUCH AS APPLE OR CRANBERRY</strong></span></span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt 0.25in\"><span style=\"font-size: small\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman\"><strong>CLEAR BROTH</strong></span></span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt 0.25in\"><span style=\"font-size: small\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman\"><strong>CLEAR JELLO</strong></span></span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt 0.25in\"><span style=\"font-size: small\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman\"><strong>TOAST WITH JELLY OR JAM- NO BUTTER</strong></span></span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt 0.25in\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt 0.25in\"><span style=\"font-size: small\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman\"><u><strong>NO DAIRY PRODUCTS</strong></u></span></span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt 0.25in\"><span style=\"font-size: small\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman\"><u><strong>NO BUTTER OR MARGARINE</strong></u></span></span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt 0.25in\"><span style=\"font-size: small\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman\"><u><strong>NO CREAMER</strong></u></span></span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt 0.25in\"><span style=\"font-size: small\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman\"><strong><u>NO CITRUS FRUITS OR JUICES</u>.</strong></span></span></div>\r\n</span></span></div>\r\n<p><strong>&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: small\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman\"><strong><i><span style=\"font: 7pt \'Times New Roman\'\"><span style=\"font-size: medium\">1..</span>&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></i><u><span style=\"background-color: #ffff00\"><i>YOU</i></span><i> <span style=\"background: yellow\">MUST HAVE A DRIVER WHO WILL BE RESPONSIBLE FOR YOU THE DAY OF SURGERY.</span>YOUR DRIVER MUST REMAIN AT THE FACILITY UNTIL YOU ARE DISCHARGED.</i></u><i>&nbsp;YOU WILL NEED SOMEONE TO DRIVE YOU TO YOUR ONE-DAY POST-OP APPOINTMENT. YOU MAY NOT LEAVE BY TAXI OR BUS</i></strong></span></span></p>\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"font-size: small\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman\"><i>2.</i></span></span><span style=\"font-size: small\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman\"><i><span style=\"font: 7pt \'Times New Roman\'\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span><span style=\"background: yellow\">DIABETICS</span> <u>DO NOT</u> TAKE ANY DIABETIC MEDICATIONS, (ORAL OR INJECTABLE) ON THE DAY OF SURGERY, UNTIL YOU HAVE A MEAL FOLLOWING YOUR SURGERY, UNLESS INSTRUCTED TO DO SO.</i></span></span></strong></p>\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"font-size: small\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman\"><i>3.&nbsp; </i></span></span><span style=\"font-size: small\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman\"><i><span style=\"background: yellow\"><span style=\"font: 7pt \'Times New Roman\'\">&nbsp; </span></span><span style=\"background: yellow\">YOU MAY TAKE YOUR PRESCRIPTION MEDICATIONS WITH A SIP OF WATER.</span></i></span></span><span style=\"font-size: small\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman\"><i><span style=\"font: 7pt \'Times New Roman\'\">&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></i></span></span></strong></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: small\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman\"><strong>4.&nbsp; <em>TAKE A SHOWER PRIOR TO SURGERY.</em></strong></span></span></p>\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"font-size: small\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman\"><i><span style=\"background: yellow\"><span style=\"font: 7pt \'Times New Roman\'\"><em><font style=\"background-color: #ffffff\" size=\"3\">5.&nbsp; </font></em>&nbsp;</span></span>NO FACE MAKE-UP.NO SCENTED LOTIONS, PERFUME OR COLOGNE.&nbsp;&nbsp;LEAVE VALUABLES AT HOME. <span style=\"background: yellow\">DO NOT BRING YOUR CELL PHONE INTO THE</span> <span style=\"background: yellow\">SURGERY CENTER.</span></i></span></span><span style=\"color: #ffffff\"><span style=\"font-size: small\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman\"><i><span style=\"background: yellow\">&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></i></span></span><span style=\"font-size: small\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman\"><i><span style=\"font: 7pt \'Times New Roman\'\">&nbsp; </span></i></span></span></span></strong></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: small\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman\"><em><strong>6.&nbsp; DRESS COMFORTABLY.&nbsp;YOU WILL NOT BE REMOVING ANY CLOTHING PRIOR TO SURGERY.&nbsp;</strong></em></span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: small\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman\"><em><strong>7. YOU MAY KEEP YOUR DENTURES IN PLACE</strong></em></span></span></p>\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"font-size: small\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman\"><em>8.&nbsp; </em></span></span><span style=\"font-size: small\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman\"><i><span style=\"background: yellow\">BEGIN THE FOLLOWING DROPS 2 DAYS PRIOR TO SURGERY.</span></i></span></span><span style=\"font-size: small\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman\"><i><span style=\"background: yellow\">INSTILL ONE DROP OF&nbsp;BROMDAY <u>( ONCE A DAY)&nbsp;</u>AND ONE DROP OF VIGAMOX <u>(&nbsp;THREE TIMES A DAY)</u>&nbsp;IN THE {SITE}EYE.&nbsp; WAIT 5 MINUTES BETWEEN EACH DROP.&nbsp;THE FIRST DAY WILL BE {TEXTBOX_MEDIUM},</span></i></span></span><span style=\"font-size: small\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman\"><i><span style=\"background: yellow\">THE SECOND DAY WILL BE {TEXTBOX_MEDIUM}.</span></i></span></span></strong></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: small\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman\"><i><strong>9.<span style=\"font: 7pt \'Times New Roman\'\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>DO NOT THROW THE DROPS AWAY.&nbsp;YOU WILL BE GIVEN FURTHER INSTRUCTIONS FOR USE AT YOUR ONE-DAY POST-OP APPOINTMENT.</strong></i></span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: small\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman\"><i><strong>10.&nbsp;BRING ALL EYE MEDICATIONS WITH YOU TO EACH POST-OP VISIT. YOU DO NOT NEED TO BRING THE DAY OF YOUR SURGERY.</strong></i></span></span></p>\r\n<div style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 0in 0in 10pt\"><span style=\"font-size: small\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman\"><i><strong>YOUR FIRST POST-OP VISIT WILL BE AT OUR </strong></i></span></span><span style=\"font-size: small\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman\"><strong>{TEXTBOX_XSMALL}{East Mesa Office}</strong></span></span></div>\r\n<div style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 0in 0in 10pt\"><span style=\"font-size: small\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman\"><strong>{TEXTBOX_XSMALL}{Octillo Office}</strong></span></span></div>\r\n<div style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 0in 0in 10pt\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 0in 0in 10pt\"><span style=\"font-size: small\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman\"><strong><em>On:</em>{TEXTBOX_MEDIUM}&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp; <em>At:&nbsp; </em>{TEXTBOX_MEDIUM}</strong></span></span></div>\r\n<div style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 0in 0in 10pt\"><span style=\"font-size: small\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman\"><i><strong>If you should have any questions prior to surgery please contact the surgical counselor at our</strong></i></span></span></div>\r\n<div style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 0in 0in 10pt\"><span style=\"font-size: small\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman\"><i><strong>office&nbsp; </strong></i></span></span><u><span style=\"font-size: small\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman\"><i><strong>(480)641-3937</strong></i></span></span></u></div>\r\n<div style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 0in 0in 10pt\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 0in 0in 10pt\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 0in 0in 10pt\"><span style=\"font-size: small\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman\"><em><strong>Please place these instructions in a prominent place&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong></em></span></span></div>\r\n<div style=\"line-height: normal; margin: 0in 0in 10pt\"><span style=\"font-size: small\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman\"><i><strong>Acknowledgement of receipt of pre-op instructions</strong></i></span></span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt\"><span style=\"font-size: small\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman\"><strong>{SIGNATURE}&nbsp; </strong></span></span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt\">\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\"><span style=\"font-size: small\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman\"><strong>{LAST NAME} {MIDDLE INITIAL}{PATIENT FIRST NAME}{DOB}</strong></span></span></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 10pt\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n</span></span></i><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman\"><strong>&nbsp;</strong></span></div>\r\n<div style=\"line-height: normal; text-indent: -0.25in; margin: 0in 0in 0pt 0.5in\">\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','true'),
(63,'Generic','Generic',18,'<p>&nbsp;<font size=\"2\">1.</font><span style=\"font: 7pt \'Times New Roman\'\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span><font size=\"2\">I hereby authorize and direct<strong>&nbsp;</strong>{SURGEON NAME}<strong>, MD. </strong>my attending physician and/ or associates of </font><font size=\"2\">their choice, to perform the following procedure (s){PROCEDURE}{SITE} </font><font size=\"2\">eye and any other procedure(s)that&nbsp;in&nbsp;their judgment may be advisable for my well being.&nbsp;The nature of the operation has been explained to </font><font size=\"2\">me </font><font size=\"2\">and no warranty or guarantee has been made as to the results or outcome.</font></p>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-indent: -0.25in; margin: 0in 0in 0pt 0.25in\"><font size=\"2\">2.</font><span style=\"font: 7pt \'Times New Roman\'\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span><font size=\"2\">I&nbsp;hereby authorize and direct the above physician and / or her associates or assistants to provide </font></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt 0.25in\"><font size=\"2\">additional services for me as they deem reasonable and necessary.&nbsp;I understand that the following professionals may be acting on my behalf as independent contractors responsible to me.</font></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt 0.25in\"><font size=\"2\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Anesthesiologists or Certified Registered Nurse Anesthetists for the administration of anesthesia.</font></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt 0.25in\"><font size=\"2\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Radiologists for the interpretation of x-rays and performance of special tests.</font></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt 0.25in\"><font size=\"2\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pathologists for the examination of tissue.</font></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-indent: -0.25in; margin: 0in 0in 0pt 0.25in\"><font size=\"2\">3.</font><span style=\"font: 7pt \'Times New Roman\'\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span><font size=\"2\">I confirm the following:&nbsp;That my physician has explained to me the nature, purpose and possible </font></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt 0.25in\"><font size=\"2\">consequences of each operation or procedure, as well as risks involved possible complications and possible alternative methods of treatment. I understand that the information I have received is not exhaustive and that more remote risks and consequences may arise: that I have been advised that a more detailed and complete explanation of any of the forgoing matters will be given to me if I so desire.&nbsp;I do not desire further explanation.</font></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\"><font size=\"2\">&nbsp;</font></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-indent: -0.25in; margin: 0in 0in 0pt 0.25in\"><font size=\"2\">4.</font><span style=\"font: 7pt \'Times New Roman\'\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span><font size=\"2\">I understand that the Safe Medical Devices Act of 1990 mandates the center be able to locate patients</font></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt 0.25in\"><font size=\"2\">who have specified implantable devices.&nbsp;I authorize the utilization of my social security number if needed to locate me.</font></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-indent: -0.25in; margin: 0in 0in 0pt 0.25in\"><font size=\"2\">5.</font><span style=\"font: 7pt \'Times New Roman\'\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span><font size=\"2\">I hereby authorize a pathologist or my physician to use their discretion in the disposal of any tissue.</font></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-indent: -0.25in; margin: 0in 0in 0pt 0.25in\"><font size=\"2\">6.</font><span style=\"font: 7pt \'Times New Roman\'\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span><font size=\"2\">I hereby consent to the observation of this operation by persons approved by my surgeon.</font></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-indent: -0.25in; margin: 0in 0in 0pt 0.25in\"><font size=\"2\">7.</font><span style=\"font: 7pt \'Times New Roman\'\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span><font size=\"2\">I hereby consent to the use of any photographic equipment during my stay at SWAGEL WOOTTON EYE CENTER; that any photographs or films taken become property of SWAGEL WOOTTON EYE CENTER and will be used at the discretion of the physician.</font></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-indent: -0.25in; margin: 0in 0in 0pt 0.25in\"><font size=\"2\">8.</font><span style=\"font: 7pt \'Times New Roman\'\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span><font size=\"2\">EMERGENCY TRANSFER CONSENT: I hereby give my consent to be transferred from SWAGEL WOOTTON EYE CENTER to any appropriate emergency facility in the event that such transfer is required during or following my surgery at SWAGEL WOOTTON EYE CENTER.&nbsp;I understand that SWAGEL WOOTTON EYE CENTER is not responsible for any transportation expenses.</font></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-indent: -0.25in; margin: 0in 0in 0pt 0.25in\"><font size=\"2\">9.</font><span style=\"font: 7pt \'Times New Roman\'\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span><font size=\"2\">I consent to the release of information from my medical records at SWAGEL WOOTTON EYE CENTER to any insurance company(s) and/ or third party payers including Medicare, if applicable.</font></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\">&nbsp;{SIGNATURE}&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; {Witness Signature}&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;{DATE}&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\"><font size=\"2\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </font></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\"><font size=\"2\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</font></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\"><font size=\"2\">If Patient is unable to sign, complete the following: Patient is unable to sign because: Type statement here.</font></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\"><font size=\"2\">__________________________________________________________________________________</font></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\">&nbsp;{SIGNATURE}&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;{Witness Signature}&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;{DATE}&nbsp;&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\"><font size=\"2\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</font><font size=\"2\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</font></div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>','true'),
(59,'Yag laser Capsulotomy Consent','Capsulotomy',6,'<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center; margin: 0in 0in 0pt\" align=\"center\"><b><i><u><span style=\"font-size: 10pt\">Informed Consent for Surgical or Invasive Procedure</span></u></i></b></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-align: center; margin: 0in 0in 0pt\" align=\"center\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt\">(Cross and initial any paragraphs which do not apply)</span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-indent: -0.25in; margin: 0in 0in 0pt 0.25in; text-autospace: ideograph-numeric\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt\">1.<span style=\"font: 7pt \'Times New Roman\'\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt\">I hereby authorize and direct <strong>Dr.</strong>{SURGEON NAME} MD<strong>, </strong>my attending physician and/ or associates of their choice, to perform the following procedure (s) UPON ME: Yag Laser Capsulotomy&nbsp;{SITE}&nbsp;Eye. The operation has been explained to me and no warranty or guarantee has been made as to the results and or outcome.</span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-indent: -0.25in; margin: 0in 0in 0pt 0.25in; text-autospace: ideograph-numeric\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt\">2.<span style=\"font: 7pt \'Times New Roman\'\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt\">The Nd: Yag laser cuts or sections intraocular tissues non-invasively by focusing the laser beam on a small segment of tissue.&nbsp;Pulsed bursts of energy cause breakdown of the tissue.</span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-indent: -0.25in; margin: 0in 0in 0pt 0.25in; text-autospace: ideograph-numeric\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt\">3.<span style=\"font: 7pt \'Times New Roman\'\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt\">I understand that the Nd: yag laser will be used to lyse vitreous strands, band, membranes or Synechia.</span></div>\r\n<ol style=\"margin-top: 0in\" type=\"A\">\r\n    <li style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt; text-autospace: ideograph-numeric\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt\">Possible alternative methods to Nd: Yag Laser Surgery:</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt\">Use of a fine knife, vitrector, or other surgical instrument to physically cut the strand, band, membrane or synechia.</span></li>\r\n</ol>\r\n<div style=\"text-indent: -0.25in; margin: 0in 0in 0pt 0.25in; text-autospace: ideograph-numeric\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt\">4.<span style=\"font: 7pt \'Times New Roman\'\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt\">Discomforts and risks to be reasonably expected:</span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt 0.25in\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt\">Minimal chance of corneal, iris, or retinal impact resulting in a very slight chance of bleeding or decrease in visual acuity: possible pitting or cracking of an implanted intraocular lens, or formation of lens opacities or cataracts in phakic patients, resulting in a possible decrease in visual acuity:&nbsp;possible increase in intraocular pressure which may result in a slight change or decrease in visual acuity.&nbsp;Possible inflammation within the eye; possible clouding of the cornea.</span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt 0.25in\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-indent: -0.25in; margin: 0in 0in 0pt 0.25in; text-autospace: ideograph-numeric\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt\">5.<span style=\"font: 7pt \'Times New Roman\'\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt\">Possible benefits for patients: society:</span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt 0.25in\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt\">Increased visual acuity, qualitative visual acuity improvement and decreased risk of complications associated with invasive surgical techniques.</span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt 0.25in\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-indent: -0.25in; margin: 0in 0in 0pt 0.25in; text-autospace: ideograph-numeric\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt\">6.<span style=\"font: 7pt \'Times New Roman\'\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt\">I hereby authorize and direct the above physician and / or her associates or assistants to provide </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt 0.25in\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt\">additional services for me as they deem reasonable and necessary.&nbsp;I understand that the following professionals may be acting on my behalf as independent contractors responsible to me.</span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt 0.25in\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Anesthesiologists or Certified Registered Nurse Anesthetists for the administration of anesthesia.</span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt 0.25in\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Radiologists for the interpretation of x-rays and performance of special tests.</span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt 0.25in\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Pathologists for the examination of tissue.</span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-indent: -0.25in; margin: 0in 0in 0pt 0.25in; text-autospace: ideograph-numeric\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt\">7.<span style=\"font: 7pt \'Times New Roman\'\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt\">The basic procedure of sectioning intraocular tissue or membranes by the ND: Yag lager and the advantages and disadvantages, risk and possible complications or alternative treatments have been explained to me.&nbsp;Although it is impossible for the doctor to inform me of every possible complication that may occur, the doctor has answered all my questions to my satisfaction. In signing this informed consent for the lysis procedure by the Nd: Yag operation, I am stating I have read this informed consent (or it has been read to me.)&nbsp;and I fully understand it and the possible risks, complications and benefits (as explained to me by the doctor or as stated in this form) that can result form the surgery.</span></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-indent: -0.25in; margin: 0in 0in 0pt 0.25in; text-autospace: ideograph-numeric\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-indent: -0.25in; margin: 0in 0in 0pt 0.25in; text-autospace: ideograph-numeric\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt\">8.<span style=\"font: 7pt \'Times New Roman\'\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt\">I understand that the Safe Medical Devices Act of 1990 mandates the center be able to locate patients</span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt 0.25in\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt\">who have specified implantable devices.&nbsp;I authorize the utilization of my social security number if needed to locate me.</span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-indent: -0.25in; margin: 0in 0in 0pt 0.25in; text-autospace: ideograph-numeric\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt\">9.<span style=\"font: 7pt \'Times New Roman\'\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt\">I hereby authorize a pathologist or my physician to use their discretion in the disposal of any tissue.</span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-indent: -0.25in; margin: 0in 0in 0pt 0.25in; text-autospace: ideograph-numeric\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt\">10.&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt\">I hereby consent to the observation of this operation by persons approved by my surgeon.</span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-indent: -0.25in; margin: 0in 0in 0pt 0.25in; text-autospace: ideograph-numeric\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt\">11.&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt\">I hereby consent to the use of any photographic equipment during my stay at SWAGEL WOOTTON EYE CENTER; that any photographs or films taken become property of SWAGEL WOOTTON EYE CENTER and will be used at the discretion of the physician.</span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-indent: -0.25in; margin: 0in 0in 0pt 0.25in; text-autospace: ideograph-numeric\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt\">12.&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt\">EMERGENCY TRANSFER CONSENT: I hereby give my consent to be transferred from SWAGEL WOOTTON EYE CENTER to any appropriate emergency facility in the event that such transfer is required during or following my surgery at SWAGEL WOOTTON EYE CENTER.&nbsp;I understand that SWAGEL WOOTTON EYE CENTER is not responsible for any transportation expenses.</span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-indent: -0.25in; margin: 0in 0in 0pt 0.25in; text-autospace: ideograph-numeric\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt\">13.&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt\">I consent to the release of information from my medical records at SWAGEL WOOTTON EYE CENTER to any insurance company(s) and/ or third party payers including Medicare, if applicable.</span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt\">Patient\'s Signature&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Date&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size: 10pt\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt\">&nbsp;&nbsp;{SIGNATURE}&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;{DATE}&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\">{LAST NAME}&nbsp;{MIDDLE INITIAL}{PATIENT FIRST NAME}{DOB}</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\">\r\n<p>{SURGEON NAME}{DOS}&nbsp;{Surgeon\'s Signature}<font size=\"2\">{Witness Signature} </font></p>\r\n</div>','true'),
(56,'Anesthesia Consent Form','Anesthesia Consent Form',20,'<p style=\"text-align: center; margin: 0in 0in 0pt; mso-outline-level: 1\" class=\"MsoNormal\" align=\"center\"><b><span style=\"font-size: 14pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\">Anesthesia Informed Consent<o:p></o:p></font></span></b></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\" class=\"MsoNormal\"><b><span style=\"font-size: 14pt; mso-bidi-font-size: 12.0pt\"><o:p><font face=\"Times New Roman\">&nbsp;</font></o:p></span></b></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\" class=\"MsoBodyText\"><font size=\"5\"><font face=\"Times New Roman\">All forms of anesthesia involve some risk, and no guarantee can be made concerning the result of a procedure.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes\">&nbsp; </span>Strokes, damage to brain, liver, kidneys or heart, adverse drug reactions, or even death are rare complications.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes\">&nbsp; </span>These risks apply to all forms of anesthesia, and risks specific to cataract anesthesia are identified below.<o:p></o:p></font></font></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\" class=\"MsoBodyText\"><v:shapetype id=\"_x0000_t202\" path=\"m,l,21600r21600,l21600,xe\" o:spt=\"202\" coordsize=\"21600,21600\"><v:stroke joinstyle=\"miter\"></v:stroke><v:path o:connecttype=\"rect\" gradientshapeok=\"t\"></v:path></v:shapetype><v:shape style=\"z-index: 251655680; position: absolute; margin-top: 4.3pt; width: 112.2pt; height: 4in; margin-left: -9.35pt\" id=\"_x0000_s1026\" type=\"#_x0000_t202\"><v:textbox>\r\n<table cellspacing=\"0\" cellpadding=\"0\" width=\"100%\">\r\n    <tbody>\r\n        <tr>\r\n            <td style=\"border-bottom: #f0f0f0; border-left: #f0f0f0; background-color: transparent; border-top: #f0f0f0; border-right: #f0f0f0\">\r\n            <div>\r\n            <p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\" class=\"MsoNormal\"><o:p><font size=\"3\" face=\"Times New Roman\">&nbsp;</font></o:p></p>\r\n            <p style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\" class=