D THROUGH THE SIDE PORT PRIOR TO VISCOELASTIC INJECTION.</span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">A CORNEA TUNNEL INCISION WAS THEN PERFORMED WITH A STAINLESS STEEL KERATOME.&nbsp;AN ANTERIOR CAPSULOTOMY WAS PERFORMED.&nbsp; HYDRODISSECTION WAS THEN PERFORMED.&nbsp; THE NUCLEUS WAS REMOVED BY PHACOEMULSIFICATION.&nbsp; THE REMAINING CORTICAL MATERIAL WAS THEN ASPIRATED OUT USING THE IRRIGATION/ASPIRATION HAND-PIECE.&nbsp; VISCOELASTIC WAS THEN INJECTED INTO THE EYE TO INFLATE THE CAPSULAR BAG. A FOLDING POSTERIOR CHAMBER IMPLANT WAS INSERTED.&nbsp; THE VISCOELASTIC WAS THEN ASPIRATED FROM THE EYE.&nbsp; THE WOUND WAS CHECKED FOR ITS INTERGRITY.&nbsp; THERE WERE NO IMMEDIATE INTRA-OPERATIVE COMPLICATIONS.&nbsp; THE PATIENT TOLERATED THE PROCEDURE WELL.</span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">&nbsp;_____A PAIRED SET OF____ DEGREE LIMBAL RELAXING INCISIONS WERE PERFORMED AT THE STEEPEST CORNEAL AXIS PRIOR TO LENS INSERTIONS.</span></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">{SURGEON NAME}, M.D.</span></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">*CONSISTS OF A 3:1 MIXTURE OF BALANCED SALT SOLUTION AND 4% LIDOCAINE MPF (SOLUTION YIELDS A 1% SHUGARCAINE MIXTURE)</span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">**CONSISTS OF A 3:1 MIXTURE OF THE ABOVE SHUGARCAINE WITH EPINEPHINE 1:1,000 (SOLUTION YIELDS 1% SHUGARCAINE/250MCG EPINEPHRINE PER ML) (THE EPINEPHRINE USED IS PRESERVATIVE FREE AND METABISULFITE FREE)</span></span></p>',249,0,0),
(6,'Cataract','<p><strong><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">OPERATIVE REPORT</span></span></strong></p>\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">PATIENT:&nbsp; {PATIENT FIRST NAME} {MIDDLE INITIAL} {LAST NAME}</span></span></strong></p>\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">SURGEON: {SURGEON NAME}, MD&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; {DOS}</span></span></strong></p>\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">PRE-OPERATIVE DIAGNOSIS:&nbsp; </span></span></strong><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">{PRE-OP DIAGNOSIS}</span></span></p>\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">POST-OPERATIVE DIAGNOSIS:&nbsp;</span></span></strong><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman\"><span style=\"font-size: small\"> {POST-OP DIAGNOSIS}</span></span></p>\r\n<p><strong><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">OPERATION:&nbsp;</span></span></strong><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman\"><span style=\"font-size: small\"> {PROCEDURE},&nbsp;{SITE}<strong> </strong>eye {SECONDARY PROCEDURE}</span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">PROCEDURE:&nbsp; THE PATIENT WAS PREPPED AND DRAPED IN THE USUAL STERILE MANNER.&nbsp; A LID SPECULUM WAS PLACED INTO THE EYE.&nbsp; A SIDE-PORT INCISION WAS MADE IN THE CLEAR CORNEA WITH A DIAMOND BLADE.&nbsp; VISCOELASTIC WAS INJECTED INTO THE ANTERIOR CHAMBER.&nbsp; WHERE TOPICAL ANESTHESIA WAS USED, 1% INTRAOCULAR *SHUGARCAINE OR **EPI-SHUGARCAINE WAS INJECTED THROUGH THE SIDE PORT PRIOR TO VISCOELASTIC INJECTION.</span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">A CORNEA TUNNEL INCISION WAS THEN PERFORMED WITH A STAINLESS STEEL KERATOME.&nbsp;AN ANTERIOR CAPSULOTOMY WAS PERFORMED.&nbsp; HYDRODISSECTION WAS THEN PERFORMED.&nbsp; THE NUCLEUS WAS REMOVED BY PHACOEMULSIFICATION.&nbsp; THE REMAINING CORTICAL MATERIAL WAS THEN ASPIRATED OUT USING THE IRRIGATION/ASPIRATION HAND-PIECE.&nbsp; VISCOELASTIC WAS THEN INJECTED INTO THE EYE TO INFLATE THE CAPSULAR BAG. A FOLDING POSTERIOR CHAMBER IMPLANT WAS INSERTED.&nbsp; THE VISCOELASTIC WAS THEN ASPIRATED FROM THE EYE.&nbsp; THE WOUND WAS CHECKED FOR ITS INTERGRITY.&nbsp; THERE WERE NO IMMEDIATE INTRA-OPERATIVE COMPLICATIONS.&nbsp; THE PATIENT TOLERATED THE PROCEDURE WELL.</span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">&nbsp;_____A PAIRED SET OF____ DEGREE LIMBAL RELAXING INCISIONS WERE PERFORMED AT THE STEEPEST CORNEAL AXIS PRIOR TO LENS INSERTIONS.</span></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">{SURGEON NAME}, M.D.</span></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">*CONSISTS OF A 3:1 MIXTURE OF BALANCED SALT SOLUTION AND 4% LIDOCAINE MPF (SOLUTION YIELDS A 1% SHUGARCAINE MIXTURE)</span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">**CONSISTS OF A 3:1 MIXTURE OF THE ABOVE SHUGARCAINE WITH EPINEPHINE 1:1,000 (SOLUTION YIELDS 1% SHUGARCAINE/250MCG EPINEPHRINE PER ML) (THE EPINEPHRINE USED IS PRESERVATIVE FREE AND METABISULFITE FREE)</span></span></p>',252,0,0),
(7,'Phaco Dr. Wu','<p><span style=\"font-size: larger; \"><span style=\"font-family: Arial; \"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"-webkit-border-horizontal-spacing: 2px; -webkit-border-vertical-spacing: 2px; \">Procedure: {PROCEDURE}</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger; \"><span style=\"font-family: Arial; \"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"-webkit-border-horizontal-spacing: 2px; -webkit-border-vertical-spacing: 2px; \">Secondary procedure: {SECONDARY PROCEDURE}</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger; \"><span style=\"font-family: Arial; \"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"-webkit-border-horizontal-spacing: 2px; -webkit-border-vertical-spacing: 2px; \">Pre-op Diagnosis: {PRE-OP DIAGNOSIS}</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger; \"><span style=\"font-family: Arial; \"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"-webkit-border-horizontal-spacing: 2px; -webkit-border-vertical-spacing: 2px; \">Post-op Diagnosis: {POST-OP DIAGNOSIS}</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger; \"><span style=\"font-family: Arial; \">&nbsp;<b style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight:normal\"><u>FINDINGS/PROCEDURE:</u></b><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>\r\n<o:OfficeDocumentSettings>\r\n<o:AllowPNG />\r\n</o:OfficeDocumentSettings>\r\n</xml><![endif]--><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>\r\n<w:WordDocument>\r\n<w:Zoom>0</w:Zoom>\r\n<w:TrackMoves>false</w:TrackMoves>\r\n<w:TrackFormatting />\r\n<w:PunctuationKerning />\r\n<w:DrawingGridHorizontalSpacing>18 pt</w:DrawingGridHorizontalSpacing>\r\n<w:DrawingGridVerticalSpacing>18 pt</w:DrawingGridVerticalSpacing>\r\n<w:DisplayHorizontalDrawingGridEvery>0</w:DisplayHorizontalDrawingGridEvery>\r\n<w:DisplayVerticalDrawingGridEvery>0</w:DisplayVerticalDrawingGridEvery>\r\n<w:ValidateAgainstSchemas />\r\n<w:SaveIfXMLInvalid>false</w:SaveIfXMLInvalid>\r\n<w:IgnoreMixedContent>false</w:IgnoreMixedContent>\r\n<w:AlwaysShowPlaceholderText>false</w:AlwaysShowPlaceholderText>\r\n<w:Compatibility>\r\n<w:BreakWrappedTables />\r\n<w:DontGrowAutofit />\r\n<w:DontAutofitConstrainedTables />\r\n<w:DontVertAlignInTxbx />\r\n</w:Compatibility>\r\n</w:WordDocument>\r\n</xml><![endif]--><!--[if gte mso 9]><xml>\r\n<w:LatentStyles DefLockedState=\"false\" LatentStyleCount=\"276\">\r\n</w:LatentStyles>\r\n</xml><![endif]--><!--[if gte mso 10]>\r\n<style>\r\n/* Style Definitions */\r\ntable.MsoNormalTable\r\n{mso-style-name:\"Table Normal\";\r\nmso-tstyle-rowband-size:0;\r\nmso-tstyle-colband-size:0;\r\nmso-style-noshow:yes;\r\nmso-style-parent:\"\";\r\nmso-padding-alt:0in 5.4pt 0in 5.4pt;\r\nmso-para-margin:0in;\r\nmso-para-margin-bottom:.0001pt;\r\nmso-pagination:widow-orphan;\r\nfont-size:12.0pt;\r\nfont-family:\"Times New Roman\";\r\nmso-ascii-font-family:Cambria;\r\nmso-ascii-theme-font:minor-latin;\r\nmso-fareast-font-family:Cambria;\r\nmso-fareast-theme-font:minor-latin;\r\nmso-hansi-font-family:Cambria;\r\nmso-hansi-theme-font:minor-latin;\r\nmso-bidi-font-family:\"Times New Roman\";\r\nmso-bidi-theme-font:minor-bidi;}\r\n</style>\r\n<![endif]--><!--StartFragment--></span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><o:p><span style=\"font-size: larger; \"><span style=\"font-family: Arial; \">&nbsp;</span></span></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><span style=\"font-size: larger; \"><span style=\"font-family: Arial; \">The patient was identified and brought into the operating room and placed into the supine position. Topical anesthesia was instilled into the operative eye, and then the patient was prepped and draped in the usual sterile ophthalmic fashion. </span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\" style=\"text-align:justify\"><o:p><span style=\"font-size: larger; \"><span style=\"font-family: Arial; \">&nbsp;</span></span></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoBodyText\"><span style=\"font-size: larger; \"><span style=\"font-family: Arial; \">The lid speculum was placed into the operative eye, and 4% Lidocaine was instilled into the eye. A 15-degree Super-sharp blade was used to create the paracentesis, and then 1% intraocular Lidocaine was injected into the anterior chamber. The anterior chamber was then filled with Viscoat, and the 2.2 mm keratome blade was used to create the superior wound. The cystotome needle was then used to initiate the capsulorrhexis which was then completed using forceps in a continuous, curvilinear fashion. Hydrodissection was carried out using the BSS cannula. The nucleus was then removed using the phacoemulsification machine and the chopper in a horizontal chopping technique. The residual cortical material was then removed using irrigation and aspiration. The capsular bag was then reinflated using the provisc. The intraocular lens was then implanted into the capsular bag where it was noted to lay in good position. The residual viscoelastic material was removed using the irrigation and aspiration. The wounds were noted to be watertight after hydrating the wounds. The eye was shielded, and the patient was brought to the recovery room in a stable condition.</span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><o:p><span style=\"font-size: larger; \"><span style=\"font-family: Arial; \">&nbsp;</span></span></o:p></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: larger; \"><span style=\"font-family: Arial; \">______________________&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></span></p>\r\n<p class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: larger; \"><span style=\"font-family: Arial; \">Alexander Wu, M.D.</span></span></p>\r\n<!--EndFragment-->',239,0,0),
(8,'Dr. Wu Phaco','<p><span style=\"font-size: larger\">&nbsp;<span style=\"font-family: Arial; -webkit-border-horizontal-spacing: 2px; -webkit-border-vertical-spacing: 2px\" class=\"Apple-style-span\">Procedure: {PROCEDURE}</span></span></p>\r\n<div style=\"padding-bottom: 5px; background-color: rgb(255,255,255); margin: 0px; padding-left: 5px; padding-right: 5px; padding-top: 5px\">\r\n<p style=\"font-family: Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 12px\"><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"-webkit-border-horizontal-spacing: 2px; -webkit-border-vertical-spacing: 2px\" class=\"Apple-style-span\">Secondary procedure: {SECONDARY PROCEDURE}</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"font-family: Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 12px\"><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"-webkit-border-horizontal-spacing: 2px; -webkit-border-vertical-spacing: 2px\" class=\"Apple-style-span\">Pre-op Diagnosis: {PRE-OP DIAGNOSIS}</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"font-family: Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 12px\"><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"-webkit-border-horizontal-spacing: 2px; -webkit-border-vertical-spacing: 2px\" class=\"Apple-style-span\">Post-op Diagnosis: {POST-OP DIAGNOSIS}</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"font-family: Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 12px\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"font-family: Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 12px\"><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><b><u>FINDINGS/PROCEDURE:</u></b></span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"font-family: Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 12px\" class=\"MsoNormal\"><o:p><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">&nbsp;</span></span></o:p></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify; font-family: Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 12px\" class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">The patient was identified and brought into the operating room and placed into the supine position. Topical anesthesia was instilled into the operative eye, and then the patient was prepped and draped in the usual sterile ophthalmic fashion.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: justify; font-family: Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 12px\" class=\"MsoNormal\"><o:p><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">&nbsp;</span></span></o:p></p>\r\n<p style=\"font-family: Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 12px\" class=\"MsoBodyText\"><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">The lid speculum was placed into the operative eye, and 4% Lidocaine was instilled into the eye. A 15-degree Super-sharp blade was used to create the paracentesis, and then 1% intraocular Lidocaine was injected into the anterior chamber. The anterior chamber was then filled with Viscoat, and the 2.2 mm keratome blade was used to create the superior wound. The cystotome needle was then used to initiate the capsulorrhexis which was then completed using forceps in a continuous, curvilinear fashion. Hydrodissection was carried out using the BSS cannula. The nucleus was then removed using the phacoemulsification machine and the chopper in a horizontal chopping technique. The residual cortical material was then removed using irrigation and aspiration. The capsular bag was then reinflated using the provisc. The intraocular lens was then implanted into the capsular bag where it was noted to lay in good position. The residual viscoelastic material was removed using the irrigation and aspiration. The wounds were noted to be watertight after hydrating the wounds. The eye was shielded, and the patient was brought to the recovery room in a stable condition.</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"font-family: Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 12px\" class=\"MsoNormal\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"font-family: Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 12px\" class=\"MsoNormal\"><o:p></o:p></p>\r\n<p style=\"font-family: Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 12px\" class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">______________________&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"font-family: Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 12px\" class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">Alexander Wu, M.D.</span></span></p>\r\n</div>',260,0,0),
(26,'PHACO TRYPAN BLUE','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font: 12.0px Helvetica; min-height: 14.0px\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Procedure: {PROCEDURE}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Secondary procedure: {SECONDARY PROCEDURE}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Pre-op Diagnosis: {PRE-OP DIAGNOSIS}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Post-op Diagnosis: {POST-OP DIAGNOSIS}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">FINDINGS/PROCEDURE:</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">The patient was brought into the operating room and placed in the supine position on the</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">operating table. A peribulbar block was administered to the left eye. The patient was</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">prepped and draped in usual sterile fashion for intraocular surgery. An eyelid speculum was</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">placed into the operative eye.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">An eye-knife was used to create a paracentesis in the 6 o&rsquo;clock position. An air bubble</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">followed by trypan blue was injected into the anterior chamber. Viscoat was injected into the</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">anterior chamber. A temporal biplanar clear corneal incision was created using a keratome.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">A continuous curvilinear capsulorhexis was created using a cystotome and a capsulorhexis</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">forceps. BSS hydrodissection was used to ensure free rotation of the lens nucleus. The</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">lens nucleus was disassembled using divide-and-conquer technique. The entire nucleus and</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">epinucleus were removed from the eye. Residual cortical material was removed using single</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">handpiece irrigation and aspiration. Provisc was injected into the capsular bag. An SN60WF</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">lens of proper power was injected and well centered in the intact capsular bag. Vancomycin</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">was injected into the anterior chamber. Residual viscoelastic material was removed using</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">single handpiece irrigation and aspiration. BSS was used to hydrate the wounds, which</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">were inspected meticulously and found to be watertight. The eyelid speculum was removed</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">from the eye. TobraDex ointment was placed in the eye which was patched and closed. The</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">patient left the operating room in stable condition.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">__________________________</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Silas Wang M.D.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',272,0,0),
(9,'PHACO TRYPAN BLUE','<p><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">&nbsp;</span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\" class=\"Apple-style-span\"><span style=\"-webkit-border-horizontal-spacing: 2px; -webkit-border-vertical-spacing: 2px\" class=\"Apple-style-span\">Procedure: {PROCEDURE}</span></span></span></p>\r\n<div>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial; -webkit-border-horizontal-spacing: 2px; -webkit-border-vertical-spacing: 2px\" class=\"Apple-style-span\">Secondary procedure: {SECONDARY PROCEDURE}</span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial; -webkit-border-horizontal-spacing: 2px; -webkit-border-vertical-spacing: 2px\" class=\"Apple-style-span\">Pre-op Diagnosis: {PRE-OP DIAGNOSIS}</span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial; -webkit-border-horizontal-spacing: 2px; -webkit-border-vertical-spacing: 2px\" class=\"Apple-style-span\">Post-op Diagnosis: {POST-OP DIAGNOSIS}</span></span></p>\r\n<div style=\"padding-bottom: 5px; background-color: rgb(255,255,255); margin: 0px; padding-left: 5px; padding-right: 5px; padding-top: 5px\">\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">FINDINGS/PROCEDURE:</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">&nbsp;</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">After the risks, benefits and alternatives were explained, informed consent was obtained. The</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">patient was brought to the Operating Room, in stable condition and monitored anesthesia</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">care was provided by Anesthesiology. A drop of sterile Tetracaine was placed on the eye,</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">and the patient was prepped and draped in the usual sterile fashion for right ocular surgery.</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">The lid speculum was inserted and the microscope was rotated into place. An MVR blade</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">was used to create paracentesis at the 12:00 and 6:00 o&rsquo;clock positions. 1% nonpreserved</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">Lidocaine was infused into the anterior chamber. Viscoat elastic substance was then used to</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">deepen the anterior chamber. A 2.2 mm keratome was used to create a clear corneal wound</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">temporally. A cystotome and Utrata forceps was used to create a continuous curvilinear</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">capsulorrhexis. Balanced salt solution was used to hydrodissect and hydrodelineate the</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">nucleus from its epinuclear shell.</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">&nbsp;</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">Phacoemulsification followed by irrigation aspiration technique was used to remove the</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">nucleus in its entirety. ProVisc was then used to deepen the posterior chamber. An</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">intraocular lens of proper size and power was introduced into the eye via the Monarch</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">delivery system and dialed into place using the Sinskey hook. The remaining Viscoat elastic</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">was then irrigated and aspirated out of the eye. All wounds were checked and found to be</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">water tight after stromal hydration. 0.1cc of Vancomycin was injected in capsular bag upon</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">completion of case. Maxitrol ointment along with patch and shield were placed on the</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">eye., and the patient was instructed to return the following day for postoperative antibiotic</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">administration and care instructions.</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">&nbsp;</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">ADDENDUM: Dense cataract, inadequate red reflex. Therefore, air instilled in anterior chamber.</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">&nbsp;</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">Capsular dye instilled on the anterior capsule and left in place several seconds. Viscoelastic then used</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">in exchange for air. In this manner, the anterior capsule was better visualized for capsulotomy.</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">&nbsp;</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">&nbsp;</span></span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">&nbsp;</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">Anthony Napolitano, M.D.</span></span></div>',262,0,0),
