monitored anesthesia</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">care was provided by Anesthesiology. A drop of sterile Tetracaine was placed on the eye, and</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">the patient was prepped and draped in the usual sterile fashion for left ocular surgery. The lid</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">speculum was inserted and the microscope was rotated into place. An MVR blade was used</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">to create paracentesis at the 12:00 and 6:00 o&rsquo;clock positions. 1% nonpreserved Lidocaine</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">was infused into the anterior chamber. Viscoat elastic substance was then used to deepen</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">the anterior chamber. A keratome was used to create a clear corneal wound temporally. A</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">cystotome and Utrata forceps was used to create a continuous curvilinear capsulorrhexis.</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">Balanced salt solution was used to hydrodissect and hydrodelineate the nucleus from its</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">epinuclear shell.</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">&nbsp;</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">Phacoemulsification followed by irrigation aspiration technique was used to remove the</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">nucleus in its entirety. ProVisc was then used to deepen the posterior chamber. An</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">intraocular lens of proper size and power was introduced into the eye via the Monarch</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">delivery system and dialed into place using a Sinskey hook. The remaining Viscoat elastic</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">was then irrigated and aspirated out of the eye. All wounds were checked and found to be</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">water tight after stromal hydration. 0.1cc of Vancomycin was injected in capsular bag upon</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">completion of case. Maxitrol ointment along with patch and shield were placed on the</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">eye, and the patient was instructed to return the following day for postoperative antibiotic</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">administration and care instructions.</span></span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">________________________</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">&nbsp;</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">Anthony Napolitano, M.D.</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">&nbsp;</span></span></div>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">&nbsp;</span></span></p>',262,0,0),
(11,'PHACO','<p><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">&nbsp;<span style=\"-webkit-border-horizontal-spacing: 2px; -webkit-border-vertical-spacing: 2px\" class=\"Apple-style-span\">Procedure: {PROCEDURE}</span></span></span></p>\r\n<div style=\"padding-bottom: 5px; background-color: rgb(255,255,255); margin: 0px; padding-left: 5px; padding-right: 5px; padding-top: 5px\">\r\n<p style=\"font-family: Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 12px\"><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"-webkit-border-horizontal-spacing: 2px; -webkit-border-vertical-spacing: 2px\" class=\"Apple-style-span\">Secondary procedure: {SECONDARY PROCEDURE}</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"font-family: Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 12px\"><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"-webkit-border-horizontal-spacing: 2px; -webkit-border-vertical-spacing: 2px\" class=\"Apple-style-span\">Pre-op Diagnosis: {PRE-OP DIAGNOSIS}</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"font-family: Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 12px\"><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"-webkit-border-horizontal-spacing: 2px; -webkit-border-vertical-spacing: 2px\" class=\"Apple-style-span\">Post-op Diagnosis: {POST-OP DIAGNOSIS}</span></span></span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">&nbsp;</span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><br type=\"_moz\" />\r\n</span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">FINDINGS/PROCEDURE: The patient was prepped and draped in the</span></span><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">usual sterile manner. Following this, a disposable plastic&nbsp;</span></span><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">drape was used to isolate the eye encompassing the eyelashes&nbsp;</span></span><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">underneath them. An aluminum speculum was placed in the&nbsp;</span></span><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">fornicles of the eye. Using an eye knife blade, a paracentesis&nbsp;</span></span><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">was then performed at the 12 o\'clock position into the anterior&nbsp;</span></span><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">chamber. Viscoelastic solution was then injected into the&nbsp;</span></span><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">anterior chamber through this paracentesis filling the entire&nbsp;</span></span><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">chamber. After this, a 2.4 mm keratome was used to create a&nbsp;</span></span><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">clear corneal incision 2.0 mm in length. Viscoelastic was then&nbsp;</span></span><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">injected additionally into the anterior chamber. Using a bent&nbsp;</span></span><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">25 gauge needle, a continuous curvilinear capsulorrhexis was&nbsp;</span></span><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">performed. Using a 26 gauge needle and balanced salt solution,&nbsp;</span></span><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">hydrodissection and hydrodelineation was performed until the&nbsp;</span></span><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">cataractous lens was loose within its capsular bag. Using the&nbsp;</span></span><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">Alcon Infinity phacoemulsification unit, the cataract was then&nbsp;</span></span><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">phacoemulsified in its entirety and the remaining cortical&nbsp;</span></span><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">material was aspirated using the standard irrigating/aspirating&nbsp;</span></span><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">feature of the Alcon Infinity. Additional Viscoelastic was&nbsp;</span></span><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">then used to inflate the posterior capsular bag. A 6mm round&nbsp;</span></span><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">foldable posterior chamber intraocular lens was then inserted&nbsp;</span></span><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">without difficulty into the capsular bag. The Viscoelastic&nbsp;</span></span><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">material was then aspirated from the anterior chamber and the&nbsp;</span></span><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">posterior chamber using the aspiration feature of the Alcon&nbsp;</span></span><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">Infinity machine. The wound was then hydrated and tested&nbsp;</span></span><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">for watertightness and found to be water-tight. 0.1 cc of&nbsp;</span></span><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">Vancomycin was injected into the anterior chamber. The speculum&nbsp;</span></span><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">was removed. Maxitrol, and Alphagan 0.2% was instilled into&nbsp;</span></span><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">the eye. A sterile pad was put on to the eye and a shield was&nbsp;</span></span><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">applied. The patient tolerated the procedure well and left the&nbsp;</span></span><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">operating room in good condition.</span></span></p>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">&nbsp;</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">_______________________</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">&nbsp;</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">Allen Fishman, M.D.</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">&nbsp;</span></span></div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n</div>',263,0,0),
(27,'PHACO','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font: 12.0px Helvetica; min-height: 14.0px\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Procedure: {PROCEDURE}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Secondary procedure: {SECONDARY PROCEDURE}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Pre-op Diagnosis: {PRE-OP DIAGNOSIS}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Post-op Diagnosis: {POST-OP DIAGNOSIS}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">FINDINGS/PROCEDURE:</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">The patient was brought into the operating room and placed in the supine position on the</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">operating table. A peribulbar block was administered to the left eye. The patient was</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">prepped and draped in usual sterile fashion for intraocular surgery. An eyelid speculum was</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">placed into the operative eye.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">An eye-knife was used to create a paracentesis in the 6 o&rsquo;clock position. Viscoat was</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">injected into the anterior chamber. A temporal biplanar clear corneal incision was created</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">using a keratome. A continuous curvilinear capsulorhexis was created using a cystotome and</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">a capsulorhexis forceps. BSS hydrodissection was used to ensure free rotation of the lens</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">nucleus. The lens nucleus was disassembled using divide-and-conquer technique. The entire</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">nucleus and epinucleus were removed from the eye. Residual cortical material was removed</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">using single handpiece irrigation and aspiration. Provisc was injected into the capsular bag.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">An SN60WF lens of proper power was injected and well centered in the intact capsular</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">bag. Vancomycin was injected into the anterior chamber. Residual viscoelastic material</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">was removed using single handpiece irrigation and aspiration. BSS was used to hydrate the</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">wounds, which were inspected meticulously and found to be watertight. The eyelid speculum</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">was removed from the eye. TobraDex ointment was placed in the eye which was patched</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">and closed. The patient left the operating room in stable condition.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">__________________________</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Silas Wang M.D.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',272,0,0),
(12,'PHACO TRYPAN BLUE','<p><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">&nbsp;<span style=\"-webkit-border-horizontal-spacing: 2px; -webkit-border-vertical-spacing: 2px\" class=\"Apple-style-span\">Procedure: {PROCEDURE}</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"-webkit-border-horizontal-spacing: 2px; -webkit-border-vertical-spacing: 2px\" class=\"Apple-style-span\">Secondary procedure: {SECONDARY PROCEDURE}</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span style=\"-webkit-border-horizontal-spacing: 2px; -webkit-border-vertical-spacing: 2px\" class=\"Apple-style-span\">Pre-op Diagnosis: {PRE-OP DIAGNOSIS}</span></span></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;<span style=\"-webkit-border-horizontal-spacing: 2px; -webkit-border-vertical-spacing: 2px\" class=\"Apple-style-span\">Post-op Diagnosis: {POST-OP DIAGNOSIS}</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">&nbsp;</span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">PROCEDURE:</span></span></p>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">The patient was brought to the Operating Room and</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">placed on the Operating Room table in supine position. A mixture</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">of Marcaine 0.25% and Lidocaine 2% with Wydase was prepared and 8cc</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">were injected in divided doses--superonasally, inferotemporally,</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">peribulbar, for the operative eye under intravenous sedation.</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">Massage was applied to the operative eye for ten minutes and the</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">patient was then prepped and draped in the usual sterile fashion.</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">A lid speculum was placed into the operative eye and a 4-0 silk</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">traction suture passed beneath the superior rectus muscle insertion</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">and the clamp. A superior conjunctival peritomy was performed,</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">and bleeding was controlled with bipolar cautery. A posterior</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">limbal scleral groove was made with a crescent blade and dissected</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">anteriorly into clear cornea. The anterior chamber was entered</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">with a 2.5mm blade. Trypan blue injected into anterior chamber to</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">stain anterior capsule. Then replaced with viscoelastic. Under</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">viscoelastic an anterior capsulotomy was performed, with the use</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">of a cystotome. The anterior capsule flap was removed. The lens was</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">hydrodissected with BSS. Lens sculpting was performed with phaco</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">handpiece. The lens nucleus was prolapsed and emulsified.</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">Irrigation/aspiration unit was used to remove all remaining</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">cortical material. Following nucleus and cortex removal,</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">viscoelastic was injected between the iris and the anterior. Under</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">viscoelastic, a posterior chamber lens was implanted. Positioning</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">was ensured with the use of a Sinskey Hook.</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">Irrigation/aspiration used to remove viscoelastic. The wound was</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">tested and found to be water tight. Subconjunctival injections of</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">Decadron 1/2cc and Gentamicin 1/2cc were given, as well as topical</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">drops, Pilocarpine 2%, and Timoptic XE 0.5%. Bacitracin ointment</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">and Pilopine HS gel were applied into the eye which was then</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">patched and gently shielded. The patient tolerated the procedure</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">well and left the Operating Room in fair condition.</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">&nbsp;</span></span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">__________________</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">Avi Bitton, M.D.</span></span></div>',264,0,0),
(13,'PHACO ','<div>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px; min-height: 14px; font: 12px Helvetica\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">Procedure: {PROCEDURE}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">Secondary procedure: {SECONDARY PROCEDURE}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">Pre-op Diagnosis: {PRE-OP DIAGNOSIS}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">Post-op Diagnosis: {POST-OP DIAGNOSIS}</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><br type=\"_moz\" />\r\n</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><br type=\"_moz\" />\r\n</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">PROCEDURE:</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">The patient was brought to the Operating Room and&nbsp;placed on the Operating Room table in supine position.&nbsp;A&nbsp;mixture of Marcaine 0.25% and Lidocaine 2% with Wydase was&nbsp;prepared and 8cc were injected in divided doses--superonasally,&nbsp;</span></span><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">inferotemporally, peribulbar, for the operative eye under&nbsp;intravenous sedation. Massage was applied to the operative eye&nbsp;</span></span><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">for ten minutes and the patient was then prepped and draped in&nbsp;the usual sterile fashion.&nbsp;A lid speculum was placed into the operative eye and a 4-0&nbsp;silk traction suture passed beneath the superior rectus muscle&nbsp;insertion and the clamp.&nbsp;A superior conjunctival peritomy was&nbsp;performed, and bleeding was controlled with bipolar cautery.&nbsp;A posterior limbal scleral groove was made with a crescent&nbsp;blade and dissected anteriorly into clear cornea. The anterior&nbsp;chamber was entered with a 2.65mm blade and under viscoelastic&nbsp;an anterior capsulotomy was performed, with the use of a&nbsp;cystotome.&nbsp;The anterior capsule flap was removed.&nbsp;The lens&nbsp;was hydrodissected with BSS. Lens sculpting was performed&nbsp;with phaco handpiece. The lens nucleus was prolapsed and&nbsp;emulsified. Irrigation/aspiration unit was used to remove all&nbsp;remaining cortical material. The capsular bag was inflated&nbsp;with viscoelatis, and a posterior chamber lens was implanted.&nbsp;</span></span><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">Positioning was ensured with the use of a Sinskey Hook.&nbsp;Irrigation/aspiration used to remove viscoelastic. The wound was&nbsp;tested and found to be water tight. 0.1 ml vancomycin injected&nbsp;into anterior chamber. Subconjunctival injection of Decadron 1/2cc was given, as well as topical drops, Pilocarpine 2%, and&nbsp;Alphagan .12%.&nbsp;Bacitracin ointment and Pilopine HS gel were&nbsp;applied into the eye which was then patched and gently shielded.&nbsp;The patient tolerated the procedure well and left the Operating&nbsp;Room in fair condition.</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><br />\r\n</span></span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">___________________</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">Avi Bitton, M.D.</span></span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>',264,0,0),
(14,'PHACO','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px; min-height: 14px; font: 12px Helvetica\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">Procedure: {PROCEDURE}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">Secondary procedure: {SECONDARY PROCEDURE}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">Pre-op Diagnosis: {PRE-OP DIAGNOSIS}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">Post-op Diagnosis: {POST-OP DIAGNOSIS}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">FINDINGS/PROCEDURE:</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">The patient was brought to the operating room in good condition. Topical anesthetic was applied</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">to the operative eye. The patient was prepped and draped in the usual manner. A lid speculum</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">was inserted in the operative eye. The surgical operating microscope with coaxial illumination</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">was used for the entirety of the surgical procedure with assisted microscope attached. Peripheral</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">corneal stab incisions were made using a 75 Beaver at 8 o&rsquo;clock 160 degrees apart. Preservative</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">free Xylocaine 1% was injected into the anterior chamber for intraocular anesthesia. The anterior</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">chamber was filled with a viscoelastic (DuoVisc). Then a keratome 2.75 was used to enter the</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">anterior chamber beginning at the limbus and creating a clear cornea temporal tunnel in the</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">process. A bent tip #25 gauge needle was used to initiate an anterior capsulotomy. Forceps</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">Utrata were used to perform a circular capsulorrhexis. Hydrodissection and cortical cleavage</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">was performed with a #27-gauge cannula.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">The Mackool System ultrasonic hand-piece was then introduced through the incision and</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">used to emulsify and aspirate the entire nucleus within the posterior chamber. During the</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">phacoemulsification procedure a Chang chopper was inserted through one of the corneal limbal</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">incisions in order to position, fracture, chop, and or rotate the nucleus and continuously maintain</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">its location away from the corneal endothelium at all times.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">Following completion of the phacoemulsification, the irrigation/aspiration and the two hand-</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">pieces (bimanual aspiration/irrigation) was used to remove all remaining lens cortex. Any non-</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">fibrous opacification of the posterior capsule were then removed with a Kratz scratcher.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">Viscoelastic was again injected into anterior chamber. The intraocular lens was inserted into</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">the capsular bag using an injector mechanism. A proper size and power lens was used on the</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">patient. Contacts of all instruments with the corneal endothelium were carefully avoided. Viscoelastic</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">was then irrigated and or aspirated from the anterior chamber. The globe was inflated with the</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">BSS and the incisions were tested and noted to be water tight without leak. Vancomycin 0.1</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">cc was injected into the AC (1 mg). Postoperative drops, used Alphagan 0.15% one drop and</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">Maxitrol drops then applied bacitracin ointment. A patch and a shield applied to the operative</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">eye, and the patient tolerated the procedure well with no complications. The lid speculum</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">was removed, also Steri-Drapes were removed. The patient tolerated the procedure well. The</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">operating room table was turned to the upright chair position, the patient remain seated for a</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">short time in order to avoid any posterior circulatory disturbance. The patient tolerated the</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">procedure well, and was escorted to the recovery room in good condition.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">&nbsp;___________________________</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">Benjamin Mason, M.D.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',265,0,0),
(15,'PTERYGIUM','<p style=\"margin: 0px; min-height: 14px; font: 12px Helvetica\"><br />\r\n&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">Procedure: {PROCEDURE}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">Secondary procedure: {SECONDARY PROCEDURE}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">Pre-op Diagnosis: {PRE-OP DIAGNOSIS}</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-family: Arial\" class=\"Apple-style-span\">Post-op Diagnosis: {POST-OP DIAGNOSIS}</span>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><br type=\"_moz\" />\r\n</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><br type=\"_moz\" />\r\n</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger\">FINDINGS/PROCEDURE:</span></p>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><br />\r\n</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\">Under fractional anesthesia, the patient was prepped and draped</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\">in the usual sterile fashion for ophthalmic surgery. Attention</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\">was directed to the operative eye. A lid speculum was inserted.</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\">Topical Tetracaine was applied. The head of the pterygium was</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\">injected with Xylocaine 2% with epinephrine. A crescent blade</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\">and O.R forceps were used to outline the head of the pterygium,</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\">and a careful lamellar keratectomy was performed, excising the</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\">pterygium from the cornea in the process. The pterygium was</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\">then dissected free from conjunctiva and underlying sclera and</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\">excised. Wet field cautery was used for hemostasis. Mitomycin-</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\">C standard preparation applied locally for 30 seconds. Then</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\">washed Vigorously with 20cc of BSS. Tranpositional conjunctival</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\">graft created nasally and sutured with 7.0 vicryl to cover the</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\">surgical area. Maxitrol ointment was applied. A light patch</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\">and Fox shield were applied after removing the lid speculum.</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\">Specimen sent to lab for pathology. The patient tolerated the</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\">procedure well and was sent to the recovery room in stable</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\">condition.</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><br />\r\n</span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\">__________________________</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><br />\r\n</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\">Benjamin Mason, M.D.</span></div>',265,0,0),
(16,'PHACO','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px; min-height: 14px; font: 12px Helvetica\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">Procedure: {PROCEDURE}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">Secondary procedure: {SECONDARY PROCEDURE}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">Pre-op Diagnosis: {PRE-OP DIAGNOSIS}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">Post-op Diagnosis: {POST-OP DIAGNOSIS}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">PROCEDURE: The operative eye was marked by the surgeon, prior&nbsp;to prepping by the circulating nurse. The patient was brought to&nbsp;the operating room in good condition. Peribulbar anesthesia was&nbsp;administered by anesthesiologist. The patient was prepped and&nbsp;draped in the usual manner. A lid speculum was inserted. The&nbsp;surgical operating microscope with coaxial illumination was used&nbsp;for the entirety of the surgical procedure with the assistant&nbsp;microscope attachment. Peripheral corneal paracentesis&nbsp;incisions were made using a 75 Beaver or similar blade at 2&nbsp;o\'clock hours clockwise from the primary incision location.&nbsp;Preservative free Epinephrine was injected into the anterior&nbsp;chamber to dilate the pupil to 8mm. A 2.4mm keratome was used&nbsp;to enter the anterior chamber beginning at the limbus and&nbsp;creating a clear corneal tunnel in the process. Viscoelastic&nbsp;was instilled in the anterior chamber. A bent tipped #25 gauge&nbsp;needle was used to initiate an anterior capsulotomy. Forceps&nbsp;were used to perform a circular capsulorhexis. Hydrodissection&nbsp;and cortical cleavage, followed by viscodissection were&nbsp;performed.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">The ultrasonic handpiece was then introduced through the&nbsp;incision and used to emulsify and aspirate the entire nucleus&nbsp;within the posterior chamber. During the phaco-emulsification&nbsp;procedure, a Mackool chopper was inserted through the corneal&nbsp;incision in order to position, fracture, chop, and/or rotate the&nbsp;nucleus and continuously maintain its location away from the&nbsp;corneal endothelium at all times.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">Following completion of phacoemulsification, the irrigation/aspiration handpiece was used to remove all remaining lens&nbsp;cortex.&nbsp;Viscoelastic was injected into the anterior chamber and capsular&nbsp;sac and the intraocular lens was inserted into the capsular sac.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">Contact of all instruments with the corneal endothelium was&nbsp;carefully avoided.&nbsp;Viscoelastic was then irrigated and/or aspirated from the anterior chamber.&nbsp;The globe was&nbsp;inflated with BSS and the incisions were tested and noted to&nbsp;be watertight.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">0.1cc Vancomycin solution was injected into&nbsp;anterior chamber.&nbsp;The lid speculum and sterile drapes were&nbsp;removed. Gauze pad and Fox shield were taped over the eye.&nbsp;The operating room table was returned to the upright (chair)&nbsp;position, and the patient remained seated for a short time in&nbsp;order to avoid any postural circulatory disturbance.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">The patient tolerated the procedure well, and was escorted to&nbsp;the recovery room in good condition.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">Boris Ovodenko, M.D.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',266,0,0),
(17,'PHACO','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px; min-height: 14px; font: 12px Helvetica\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">Procedure: {PROCEDURE}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">Secondary procedure: {SECONDARY PROCEDURE}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">Pre-op Diagnosis: {PRE-OP DIAGNOSIS}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">Post-op Diagnosis: {POST-OP DIAGNOSIS}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">PROCEDURE:</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">After peribulbar block, the patient was prepped and draped in&nbsp;the usual fashion.&nbsp;A speculum was placed in the operative&nbsp;eye.&nbsp;A #4-0 silk suture was passed.&nbsp;A peritomy was done&nbsp;at the limbus.&nbsp;A 4mm groove was made at the limbus and the&nbsp;crescent knife was used to extend the incision anteriorly. The&nbsp;chamber was entered with a 2.6 mm keratome blade. A capsulotomy&nbsp;was done in a capsulorhexis fashion using Utrata forceps.&nbsp;Hydrodissection was then done, the nucleus was rotated.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">The&nbsp;phaco instrument was then inserted into the eye and the nucleus&nbsp;was removed by dividing it into quarters.&nbsp;Each quadrant was&nbsp;successively removed.&nbsp;The irrigation/aspiration unit was&nbsp;used to aspirate the cortical remnants.&nbsp;The capsular bag was&nbsp;noted to be clear and the intraocular lens was placed into the&nbsp;capsular bag under viscoelastic which was later removed.&nbsp;The&nbsp;pupil was constricted with Pilocarpine 2% and noted to be 4mm&nbsp;and round and central at the end of the case.&nbsp;Wound was left&nbsp;unsutured and noted to be watertight.&nbsp;0.1 cc Vancomycin was&nbsp;injected into the anterior chamber. Pilocarpine was placed on&nbsp;the cornea. The patch and shield were placed over the eye with&nbsp;Bacitracin ointment. Patient left the operating room in good&nbsp;condition without complications.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">_____________________</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">David Flug, M.D.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',267,0,0),
(18,'TRAB','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px; min-height: 14px; font: 12px Helvetica\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">Procedure: {PROCEDURE}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">Secondary procedure: {SECONDARY PROCEDURE}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">Pre-op Diagnosis: {PRE-OP DIAGNOSIS}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">Post-op Diagnosis: {POST-OP DIAGNOSIS}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">FINDINGS/PROCEDURE: After IV sedation and peribulbar anesthesia, the eye was</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">prepped and draped sterilely. The speculum was placed in the eye. A peritomy was</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">done at the limbus. Tenons was incised and the peritomy was raised in the curvilinear</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">fashion for approximately 2&frac12; clock hours. The conjunctiva was reflected forward as a</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">limbal based flap, and a triangle 3x3 flap of sclera was outlined with cautery and with a</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">57 blade. A crescent knife was used to raise the flap and a paracentesis was done with</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">a MVR blade. The MVR blade was used to enter the chamber at the anterior reflection</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">of the scleral flap. The trabeculectomy was used to make a 3x2 incision size of inner</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">scleral opening. Iridectomy was done with a forceps and a Vannas scissors. The flap</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">was closed with two 10-0 nylon sutures. The conjunctiva was closed with running,</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">locking 10-0 nylon sutures. The conjunctiva was closed with two 6-0 plain sutures.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">Balanced salt was injected into the paracentesis and the flap was noted to inflate, and</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">stay inflated. Garamycin and Solu-Medrol were injected subconjunctivally. Patch and</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">shield were placed over the eye with Bacitracin ointment. The patient left the OR in</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">good condition with out complications.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">____________________________</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">David Flug, M.D.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',267,0,0),
(19,'PHACO','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px; min-height: 14px; font: 12px Helvetica\"><span style=\"font-size: smaller\"><br />\r\n</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: smaller\">Procedure: {PROCEDURE}</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: smaller\">Secondary procedure: {SECONDARY PROCEDURE}</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: smaller\">Pre-op Diagnosis: {PRE-OP DIAGNOSIS}</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: smaller\">Post-op Diagnosis: {POST-OP DIAGNOSIS}</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>PROCEDURE: The operative eye was marked by the surgeon, prior to prepping by the</p>\r\n<div>circulating nurse. The patient was brought to the operating room in good condition. Topical</div>\r\n<div>anesthetic was applied. The patient was prepped and draped in the usual manner. A lid</div>\r\n<div>speculum was inserted. The surgical operating microscope with coaxial illumination was</div>\r\n<div>used for the entirety of the surgical procedure with the assistant microscope attachment.</div>\r\n<div>Peripheral corneal paracentesis incisions were made using a 2 MVR blade at 12 &amp; 6 o\'clock</div>\r\n<div>position. A 2.4mm keratome was used to enter the anterior chamber beginning at the limbus</div>\r\n<div>and creating a clear corneal tunnel in the process. Viscoat was instilled in the anterior</div>\r\n<div>chamber. A bent tipped #25 gauge needle was used to initiate an anterior capsulotomy.</div>\r\n<div>Forceps were used to perform a circular capsulorhexis. Hydrodissection and cortical</div>\r\n<div>cleavage, were performed.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>The ultrasonic handpiece was then introduced through the incision and used to emulsify and</div>\r\n<div>aspirate the entire nucleus within the posterior chamber. During the phaco-emulsification</div>\r\n<div>procedure, a chopper was inserted through the corneal incision in order to position, fracture,</div>\r\n<div>chop, and/or rotate the nucleus and continuously maintain its location away from the corneal</div>\r\n<div>endothelium at all times.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Following completion of phacoemulsification, the bimanual irrigation/aspiration handpiece</div>\r\n<div>was used to remove all remaining lens cortex.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Viscoelastic was injected into the anterior chamber and capsular sac and the intraocular lens</div>\r\n<div>was inserted into the capsular sac. Contact of all instruments with the corneal endothelium</div>\r\n<div>was carefully avoided. Viscoelastic was then irrigated and/or aspirated from the anterior</div>\r\n<div>chamber. The globe was inflated with BSS and the incisions were tested and noted to</div>\r\n<div>be watertight. 0.1cc Vancomycin solution was injected into anterior chamber. The lid</div>\r\n<div>speculum and sterile drapes were removed. The operating room table was returned to the</div>\r\n<div>upright (chair) position, and the patient remained seated for a short time in order to avoid any</div>\r\n<div>postural circulatory disturbance. The patient tolerated the procedure well, and was escorted</div>\r\n<div>to the recovery room in good condition.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>David Lee, M.D.</div>',268,0,0),
(20,'PHACO TORIC','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px; min-height: 14px; font: 12px Helvetica\"><span style=\"font-size: smaller\"><br />\r\n</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: smaller\">Procedure: {PROCEDURE}</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: smaller\">Secondary procedure: {SECONDARY PROCEDURE}</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: smaller\">Pre-op Diagnosis: {PRE-OP DIAGNOSIS}</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: smaller\">Post-op Diagnosis: {POST-OP DIAGNOSIS}</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;FINDINGS/PROCEDURE:</p>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>The patient was brought into the operating room and seated on</div>\r\n<div>the operating room table. Eye was then marked using sterile</div>\r\n<div>marker at 0, 180, and 90 degrees. The patient was then placed</div>\r\n<div>in the supine position on the operating room table. The patient</div>\r\n<div>was given a peribulbar block by anesthesia.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>After adequate anesthesia, an akinesia was obtained. An</div>\r\n<div>operating microscope was brought into place and the lid speculum</div>\r\n<div>was placed into the operative eye. Eye was then marked with</div>\r\n<div>astigmatic marker. A temporal peritomy was then performed using</div>\r\n<div>Westcott scissors. Local hemostasis was achieved with wet-</div>\r\n<div>field cautery. A beveled incision was then initiated with a</div>\r\n<div>crescent blade and anterior chamber was entered with a 2.65</div>\r\n<div>keratome. Viscoelastic was then placed into the anterior</div>\r\n<div>chamber. A paracentesis was then made using the Micro-Sharp</div>\r\n<div>blade. A circular capsulorrhexis was then performed using</div>\r\n<div>the pre-bent cystotome and Utrata forceps without difficulty.</div>\r\n<div>Hydrodissection was then performed using BSS and air injection</div>\r\n<div>syringe. The nucleus was then rotated using an air injection</div>\r\n<div>syringe. Phacoemulsification was then initiated and completed</div>\r\n<div>without difficulty using a two handed phaco-chop technique using</div>\r\n<div>the Mackool chopper for rotation and tracking. Irrigation and</div>\r\n<div>aspiration of all cortical material was obtained using automated</div>\r\n<div>irrigation and aspiration without difficulty. Viscoelastic was</div>\r\n<div>then instilled into the anterior chamber.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>A posterior chamber toric intraocular lens was then placed</div>\r\n<div>into the capsular bag and dialed into place using the Mackool</div>\r\n<div>chopper. Viscoelastic was then removed from the operative</div>\r\n<div>eye. Toric lens was then readjusted into perfect position using</div>\r\n<div>irrigation and aspiration as well as Mackool chopper. A 1 mg of</div>\r\n<div>vancomycin was then instilled into the operative eye.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>The wound was hydrated using BSS and a 30-gauge cannula. The</div>\r\n<div>wound was found to be in perfect position. Conjunctiva was then</div>\r\n<div>brought into place using wet-field cautery. The lid speculum</div>\r\n<div>was then removed from the operative eye. Iopidine and Vigamox</div>\r\n<div>were instilled into the operative eye. Bacitracin ophthalmic</div>\r\n<div>ointment, one patch and a shield were placed over the operative</div>\r\n<div>eye. The patient was transported into the recovery room in</div>\r\n<div>excellent condition.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>________________________</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Frank Titone, M.D.</div>',269,0,0),
(21,'PHACO','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px; min-height: 14px; font: 12px Helvetica\"><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><br />\r\n</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">Procedure: {PROCEDURE}</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">Secondary procedure: {SECONDARY PROCEDURE}</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">Pre-op Diagnosis: {PRE-OP DIAGNOSIS}</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">Post-op Diagnosis: {POST-OP DIAGNOSIS}</span></span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><br type=\"_moz\" />\r\n</span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">FINDINGS/PROCEDURE: The patient was brought into the operating&nbsp;room and placed in a supine position on the operating room&nbsp;table. The patient was given peribulbar block by anesthesia.&nbsp;After adequate anesthesia and akinesia was obtained, operating&nbsp;microscope was brought into place and a lid speculum was placed&nbsp;into the operative eye. A superior peritomy was then performed&nbsp;using westcott scissors.&nbsp;Local hemostasis was achieved with&nbsp;a wet field cautery.&nbsp;A beveled incision was initiated with a&nbsp;crescent blade and anterior chamber was entered with a 2.65&nbsp;keratome. Viscoelastic was placed into the anterior chamber.&nbsp;A paracentesis was made using a Microsharp blade.&nbsp;A circular&nbsp;capsulorrhexis was performed using a pre-bent cystotome and&nbsp;Utrata forceps without difficulty. Hydrodissection was then&nbsp;performed using BSS on air injection syringe.&nbsp;The nucleus was&nbsp;then rotated using air injection syringe. Phacoemulsification&nbsp;was then initiated and completed without difficulty using a two-handed phaco-chop technique using a Mackool chopper for rotation&nbsp;and tracking. Irrigation and aspiration of all cortical material&nbsp;was obtained using automated irrigation and aspiration without</span></span></p>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">difficulty. Viscoelastic was then instilled into anterior&nbsp;chamber.&nbsp;A posterior chamber intraocular lens was then placed</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">into the capsular bag and dialed into place using a Mackool&nbsp;chopper. Viscoelastic was then removed from the eye.&nbsp;1 mg of&nbsp;Vancomycin was then instilled into the anterior chamber.&nbsp;The&nbsp;wound was then hydrated using BSS on a 30 gauge cannula.&nbsp;The&nbsp;wound was found to be in perfect position.&nbsp;Conjunctiva was&nbsp;then brought back into place with a wet field cautery. The lid&nbsp;speculum was then removed from the operative eye.&nbsp;Bacitracin&nbsp;ophthalmic ointment, Vigamox, Iopidine, one patch and a shield&nbsp;were placed over the operative eye. The patient was transported&nbsp;to the recovery room in excellent condition.</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><br />\r\n</span></span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">________________________</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><br />\r\n</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">Frank Titone, M.D.</span></span></div>\r\n<div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n</div>',269,0,0),
(22,'PTERYGIUM','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px; min-height: 14px; font: 12px Helvetica\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">Procedure: {PROCEDURE}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">Secondary procedure: {SECONDARY PROCEDURE}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">Pre-op Diagnosis: {PRE-OP DIAGNOSIS}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">Post-op Diagnosis: {POST-OP DIAGNOSIS}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">FINDINGS/PROCEDURE:</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">The patient was given peribulbar block&nbsp;by Anesthesiology. After adequate anesthesia and akinesia wa&nbsp;obtained, the patient was prepped and draped in the usual steril&nbsp;fashion. A lid speculum was then placed in the operative eye.&nbsp;An additional 1/2 cc of 2% Lidocaine with epinephrine was given&nbsp;at the site of pterygium and superiorly. The pterygium as well&nbsp;as underlying scar tissue was removed using a crescent blade&nbsp;and Bonn forceps. The remaining pterygium was removed from the&nbsp;site using Westcott scissors. Local hemostasis was achieved with&nbsp;wet field cautery. Conjunctival graft was then harvested from&nbsp;superior conjunctiva. The conjunctival graft was then sutured&nbsp;into place at site of pterygium medially using 5-6 interrupted 8-0 Vicryl sutures. The graft was found to be in perfect position&nbsp;at site of previous pterygium. Lid speculum was removed.&nbsp;Bacitracin ophthalmic ointment was instilled over lashes. One&nbsp;patch and a shield was placed over the operative eye. The patient&nbsp;was discharged to the recovery room in excellent condition.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">________________________</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">Frank Titone, M.D.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',269,0,0),
(23,'PHACO','<p style=\"margin: 0px; min-height: 14px; font: 12px Helvetica\"><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><br />\r\n</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">Procedure: {PROCEDURE}</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">Secondary procedure: {SECONDARY PROCEDURE}</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">Pre-op Diagnosis: {PRE-OP DIAGNOSIS}</span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\">Post-op Diagnosis: {POST-OP DIAGNOSIS}</span>&nbsp;</span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><br type=\"_moz\" />\r\n</span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><br type=\"_moz\" />\r\n</span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">FINDINGS/PROCEDURE:</span></span></p>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\"><br />\r\n</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">After being given a mini periorbital anesthesia, the patient&nbsp;was brought to the O.R. and was prepped and draped in the usual&nbsp;sterile fashion. The microscope was brought in and focused on&nbsp;the eye.&nbsp;A lid speculum was placed in the eye.&nbsp;The anterior&nbsp;chamber was entered through clear cornea 2.60 mm blade.&nbsp;Viscoat was instilled in the anterior chamber.&nbsp;An anterior&nbsp;capsulorrhexis was performed.&nbsp;Side ports were placed with an&nbsp;MVR blade.&nbsp;The nucleus was hydrodissected.&nbsp;The nucleus was&nbsp;emulsified with ultrasound. Cortical material was removed with&nbsp;irrigation and aspiration.&nbsp;The eye was filled with Provisc.&nbsp;The wound was opened to 3.5 mm.&nbsp;A foldable type intraocular&nbsp;lens was placed into the capsular bag. The Provisc was removed&nbsp;from the eye.&nbsp;The wound was checked for leaks and there were&nbsp;none. Iopidine 0.5% TobraDex solution drops was instilled. Lid&nbsp;speculum was removed from the eye. Bacitracin ointment applied&nbsp;over lashes. The patient was removed from the O.R. in good&nbsp;condition.</span></span></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">_________________________ </span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">Gary S. Hirshfield,</span></span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\">M.D.</span></span></div>',270,0,0),
(24,'PHACO LRI','<div>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px; min-height: 14px; font: 12px Helvetica\"><span style=\"font-size: smaller\"><br />\r\n</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: smaller\">Procedure: {PROCEDURE}</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: smaller\">Secondary procedure: {SECONDARY PROCEDURE}</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: smaller\">Pre-op Diagnosis: {PRE-OP DIAGNOSIS}</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: smaller\">Post-op Diagnosis: {POST-OP DIAGNOSIS}</span></p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>The patient was brought to the operating room and after being given peribulbar</div>\r\n<div>anesthesia was prepped and draped in the usual sterile fashion. A lid speculum was</div>\r\n<div>placed and the microscope was focused. A temporal clear corneal incision was made</div>\r\n<div>and the anterior chamber was filled with viscoelastic. A corneal side-port incision was</div>\r\n<div>made. An anterior capsulorrhexis was performed. A hydrodissection was performed.</div>\r\n<div>Viscoat dissection was performed with viscoelastic. The nucleus was emulsified.</div>\r\n<div>Residual cortical material was aspirated. Next, the posterior and anterior chambers</div>\r\n<div>were filled with Viscoelastic. The multifocal RESTOR implant was placed and centered.</div>\r\n<div>The viscoelastic was kept in the eye and additional viscoelastic was put in the eye</div>\r\n<div>to bring the eye into a firm pressure. Next, two opposing penetrating limbal relaxing</div>\r\n<div>incisions were made at the appropriate axes and at a depth of 600 microns with a fixed</div>\r\n<div>micron knife. The limbal relaxing incisions were investigated and shown to be not full</div>\r\n<div>thickness, of appropriate depth, and clean. Next, the viscoelastic was removed from the</div>\r\n<div>eye. Miochol was instilled and it was noted that the pupil came down symmetrically and</div>\r\n<div>the intraocular lens was relatively well-centered. Vancomycin was then put into the eye.</div>\r\n<div>The temporal clear corneal wound as well as the side-port wound were hydrated and</div>\r\n<div>checked for leaks and there were none. The lid speculum was removed and the patient</div>\r\n<div>was removed from the operating room in good condition.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>____________________________</div>\r\n<div>Gary Hirshfield, M.D.</div>',270,0,0),
(25,'PHACO','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px; min-height: 14px; font: 12px Helvetica\"><span style=\"font-size: smaller\"><br />\r\n</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: smaller\">Procedure: {PROCEDURE}</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: smaller\">Secondary procedure: {SECONDARY PROCEDURE}</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: smaller\">Pre-op Diagnosis: {PRE-OP DIAGNOSIS}</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: smaller\">Post-op Diagnosis: {POST-OP DIAGNOSIS}</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>FINDINGS/PROCEDURE:&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>The operative eye was marked by the surgeon, prior to prepping by the circulating nurse.</p>\r\n<div>The patient was brought to the operating room and placed on the OR table. Retrobulbar and</div>\r\n<div>peribulbar blocks were given with Lidocaine 2% without Epinephrine. After adequate akinesia</div>\r\n<div>and anesthesia were obtained the patient was prepped and draped in the usual sterile manner. A</div>\r\n<div>wire lid speculum was placed into the interpalpebral fissure, a superior peritomy was performed</div>\r\n<div>at the 10 o&rsquo;clock and 2 o&rsquo;clock positions. Hemostatis was obtained using the bipolar cautery.</div>\r\n<div>Using a crescent blade, a 4mm scleral tunnel incision was made, 2mm from the surgical limbus</div>\r\n<div>and carried into clear cornea. Prior to entering the anterior chamber, two paracentesis were</div>\r\n<div>made at the 2 o&rsquo;clock and the 9 o&rsquo;clock positions. Healon was then used to inflate the anterior</div>\r\n<div>chamber. The scleral tunnel incision was re-entered and the cornea was puckered and entered,</div>\r\n<div>creating a triplanar incision.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>Using a 25 gauge cystitome, the anterior capsular flap was fashioned and a smooth continuous</div>\r\n<div>capsulorrhexis was performed using the intraocular forceps. Balanced salt solution was used</div>\r\n<div>for hyro-dissection and hydro-delineation of the nuclear and cortical contents. Using the phaco-</div>\r\n<div>emulsification apparatus, a two-handed, divide and conquer phacoemulsificaton was performed</div>\r\n<div>and the conclusion of the phaco-emulsification, the posterior capsule was seen to be intact.</div>\r\n<div>Residual cortex was irrigated and aspirated from the eye and at the conclusion of the cortical</div>\r\n<div>clean up, the posterior capsule was seen to be intact. The wound was then opened to its 4mm</div>\r\n<div>length using the 3.75mm keratome and a foldable SOFLEX lens was placed into the bag and</div>\r\n<div>dialed into position using a Sinskey hook. Residual Healon was irrigated and aspirated from</div>\r\n<div>the eye. The wound was inspected and found to be watertight. However, one interrupted 10-</div>\r\n<div>0 nylon suture was used to bisect the wound. The knot was then buried. The wound was then</div>\r\n<div>reinspected and found to be watertight. The conjunctiva was cauterized into position and the eye</div>\r\n<div>was irrigated with Solu-Medrol and Gentamicin solution. The patient tolerated the procedure</div>\r\n<div>well, and was escorted to the recovery room in good condition.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>__________________________</div>\r\n<div>Jacqueline Dauhajre, M.D.</div>',271,0,0),
(28,'PHACO','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font: 12.0px Helvetica; min-height: 14.0px\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Procedure: {PROCEDURE}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Secondary procedure: {SECONDARY PROCEDURE}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Pre-op Diagnosis: {PRE-OP DIAGNOSIS}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Post-op Diagnosis: {POST-OP DIAGNOSIS}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">FINDINGS/PROCEDURE: The patient\'s operative eye was prepped</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">and draped in the usual manner. A block was obtained using</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">2% Xylocaine with lid block maintained by anesthesia. Using</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">microsurgical technique, a speculum was inserted and a temporal</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">approach used to the operative eye. A 3.5mm groove was made</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">at the temporal corneal scleral border. The anterior chamber</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">was entered with a 2.6 mm diamond blade. The chamber was then</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">filled with Viscoat and a separate stab incision made. A</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">disposable cystotome and capsulorhexis forceps were used to</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">create a continuous tear capsulotomy. The nucleus was loosened</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">with hydrodissection. The phacoemulsifier was introduced into</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">the eye and the nucleus was divided into quadrants and removed.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">The irrigation/aspiration unit was used to remove the remaining</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">cortical material. The posterior capsule was cleaned with a</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">capsular polish setting. The capsular bag was then filled with</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">provisc. The intraocular lens was then taken from its wrapping</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">and placed in the injector. It was then passed into the eye</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">and allowed to release inside the capsular bag. Irrigation-</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">aspiration unit was used again to remove remaining Viscoelastic.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">The wound was hydrated and the anterior chamber filled. .1cc of</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">vancomycin was injected into the stab wound. No sutures were</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">used. Maxitrol ointment and Vigamox drops were instilled on the</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">eye. The speculum removed and a sterile dressing and shield</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">placed above that. The patient tolerated the procedure well and</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">left the operating room in good condition.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">____________________</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Leslie Shapiro, M.D.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>',273,0,0),
(29,'PHACO TRYPAN BLUE','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font: 12.0px Helvetica; min-height: 14.0px\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Procedure: {PROCEDURE}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Secondary procedure: {SECONDARY PROCEDURE}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Pre-op Diagnosis: {PRE-OP DIAGNOSIS}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Post-op Diagnosis: {POST-OP DIAGNOSIS}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">PROCEDURE:&nbsp;The patient was brought to the operating room in&nbsp;good condition.&nbsp;Topical tetracaine was applied.&nbsp;The patient&nbsp;was prepped and draped in the usual manner. A lid speculum&nbsp;was inserted.&nbsp;The surgical operating microscope with coaxial&nbsp;illumination was used for the entirety of the surgical procedure&nbsp;with the assistant microscope attachment. Peripheral corneal&nbsp;stab incisions were made. Preservative free Xylocaine 1% was&nbsp;injected into the anterior chamber for intraocular anesthesia.&nbsp;BSS was injected in the anterior chamber. A keratome was used&nbsp;to enter the anterior chamber beginning at the limbus and&nbsp;creating a clear corneal tunnel in the process. Viscoelastic&nbsp;was instilled in the anterior chamber. Trypan blue was injected&nbsp;onto the anterior capsule to allow visualization secondary to&nbsp;a mature cataract. A bent tipped #25 gauge needle was used to&nbsp;initiate an anterior capsulotomy. Forceps were used to perform&nbsp;a circular capsulorhexis. Hydrodissection and cortical cleavage&nbsp;was performed with a #27 gauge cannula.The Mackool System ultrasonic handpiece was then introduced&nbsp;through the incision and used to emulsify and aspirate the&nbsp;entire nucleus within the posterior chamber. During the phaco-&nbsp;emulsification procedure, a chopper was inserted through one of&nbsp;the corneal limbal incisions in order to position, fracture,&nbsp;chop, and/or rotate the nucleus and continuously maintain its&nbsp;location away from the corneal endothelium at all times.Following completion of the phacoemulsification, the irrigation/&nbsp;aspiration handpiece was used to remove all remaining lens&nbsp;cortex.Viscoelastic was again injected into the anterior chamber.&nbsp;The intraocular lens was inserted into the capsule bag in one&nbsp;motion, using the injector mechanism.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Contact of all instruments with the corneal endothelium was&nbsp;carefully avoided.&nbsp;Viscoelastic was then aspirated from the&nbsp;anterior chamber.&nbsp;The globe was inflated with BSS and the&nbsp;incisions were tested and noted to be watertight, without&nbsp;leak.&nbsp;0.1cc Vancomycin solution injected into anterior&nbsp;chamber. Antibiotic and Maxitrol ointment was applied. The&nbsp;lid speculum was removed.&nbsp;Sterile drapes were removed.&nbsp;The&nbsp;patient tolerated the procedure well. The operating room table&nbsp;was returned to the upright (chair) position, and the patient&nbsp;remained seated for a short time in order to avoid any postural&nbsp;circulatory disturbance.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">The patient was then assisted in ambulating to the recovery room&nbsp;in good condition.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">_________________________</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Maurice Mosseri, M.D</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',274,0,0),
(30,'PHACO ','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font: 12.0px Helvetica; min-height: 14.0px\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Procedure: {PROCEDURE}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Secondary procedure: {SECONDARY PROCEDURE}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Pre-op Diagnosis: {PRE-OP DIAGNOSIS}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Post-op Diagnosis: {POST-OP DIAGNOSIS}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">PROCEDURE:</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">The patient was brought to the operating room in&nbsp;good condition.&nbsp;Topical tetracaine was applied.&nbsp;The patient&nbsp;was prepped and draped in the usual manner. A lid speculum&nbsp;was inserted.&nbsp;The surgical operating microscope with coaxial&nbsp;illumination was used for the entirety of the surgical procedure&nbsp;with the assistant microscope attachment. Peripheral corneal&nbsp;stab incisions were made. Preservative free Xylocaine 1% was&nbsp;injected into the anterior chamber for intraocular anesthesia.&nbsp;BSS was injected in the anterior chamber. A keratome was used&nbsp;to enter the anterior chamber beginning at the limbus and&nbsp;creating a clear corneal tunnel in the process. Viscoelastic&nbsp;was instilled in the anterior chamber. A bent tipped #25 gauge&nbsp;needle was used to initiate an anterior capsulotomy. Forceps&nbsp;were used to perform a circular capsulorhexis. Hydrodissection&nbsp;and cortical cleavage was performed with a #27 gauge cannula.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">The Mackool System ultrasonic handpiece was then introduced&nbsp;through the incision and used to emulsify and aspirate the&nbsp;entire nucleus within the posterior chamber. During the phaco-&nbsp;emulsification procedure, a chopper was inserted through one of&nbsp;the corneal limbal incisions in order to position, fracture,&nbsp;chop, and/or rotate the nucleus and continuously maintain its&nbsp;location away from the corneal endothelium at all times.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Following completion of the phacoemulsification, the irrigation/&nbsp;aspiration handpiece was used to remove all remaining lens&nbsp;cortex.&nbsp;Viscoelastic was again injected into the anterior chamber.&nbsp;The intraocular lens was inserted into the capsule bag in one&nbsp;motion, using the injector mechanism.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Contact of all instruments with the corneal endothelium was&nbsp;carefully avoided.&nbsp;Viscoelastic was then aspirated from the&nbsp;anterior chamber.&nbsp;The globe was inflated with BSS and the&nbsp;incisions were tested and noted to be watertight, without&nbsp;leak.&nbsp;0.1cc Vancomycin solution injected into anterior&nbsp;chamber. Antibiotic and Maxitrol ointment was applied. The&nbsp;lid speculum was removed.&nbsp;Sterile drapes were removed.&nbsp;The&nbsp;patient tolerated the procedure well. The operating room table&nbsp;was returned to the upright (chair) position, and the patient&nbsp;remained seated for a short time in order to avoid any postural&nbsp;circulatory disturbance.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">The patient was then assisted in ambulating to the recovery room&nbsp;in good condition.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">_________________________</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Maurice Mosseri, M.D</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',274,0,0),
(31,'PHACO TRYPAN BLUE','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font: 12.0px Helvetica; min-height: 14.0px\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Procedure: {PROCEDURE}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Secondary procedure: {SECONDARY PROCEDURE}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Pre-op Diagnosis: {PRE-OP DIAGNOSIS}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Post-op Diagnosis: {POST-OP DIAGNOSIS}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">FINDINGS/PROCEDURE:</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">The patient was placed on the operating room table in the&nbsp;supine position. After adequate anesthesia and akinesia of the&nbsp;operative eye had been achieved with the use of a peribulbar&nbsp;block, the patient was prepped and draped in the usual sterile&nbsp;manner for ophthalmic surgery.&nbsp;A 15 degree blade was used&nbsp;to create two paracentesis at the corneoscleral limbus.&nbsp;Viscoelastic substance was instilled into the anterior chamber.&nbsp;An air bubble and trypan blue were instilled into the anterior&nbsp;chamber. After several seconds, BSS was then irrigated into the&nbsp;anterior chamber to remove the trypan blue from the AC. A 2.65&nbsp;scleral tunnel was created. A bent-needle cystotome and Utrata&nbsp;forceps were used to create a continuous tear capsulorrhexis in&nbsp;the anterior lens capsule. Balanced salt solution was injected&nbsp;into the lens capsule for hydrodissection to hydrodelineate the&nbsp;lens nucleus. The lens nucleus was phacoemulsified in a divide-and-conquer manner with the use of the phacoemulsification&nbsp;needle. The lens was cracked into two halves and then the two&nbsp;halves were then elevated into the iris plane with the use of&nbsp;a Pisacano spatula.&nbsp;In this manner, the two halves were then&nbsp;emulsified.&nbsp;Residual cortical and epinuclear material was&nbsp;removed with the use of the two-piece I&amp;A system.&nbsp;The lens&nbsp;capsule was filled with Provisc viscoelastic substance.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">The incision was widened to a 3.5 mm clear coreal incision with&nbsp;the use of the short cut blade. Next, an intraocular lens was&nbsp;opened, inspected and found to be in good condition.&nbsp;This was&nbsp;folded and then was inserted into the capsular bag with the use&nbsp;of the insertion forceps.&nbsp;The lens was rotated into position&nbsp;with the use of the Sinskey hook.&nbsp;Residual cortical material&nbsp;and Viscoelastic material was removed from the eye with the&nbsp;use of the irrigation/aspiration handpiece.&nbsp;The wound was&nbsp;checked for water-tightness and was found to be so.&nbsp;0.1 cc&nbsp;of Vancomycin solution, equivalent of 1 mg of Vancomycin was&nbsp;instilled into the anterior chamber.&nbsp;The speculum and drapes&nbsp;were removed from the eye and the eye was seen to remain formed.&nbsp;The eye was patched and shielded with Maxitrol ointment and the&nbsp;patient brought back to the recovery room in excellent condition&nbsp;having tolerated the procedure well.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">______________________</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Paul D. Sforza, M.D.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',275,0,0),
(32,'PHACO','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font: 12.0px Helvetica; min-height: 14.0px\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Procedure: {PROCEDURE}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Secondary procedure: {SECONDARY PROCEDURE}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Pre-op Diagnosis: {PRE-OP DIAGNOSIS}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Post-op Diagnosis: {POST-OP DIAGNOSIS}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">FINDINGS/PROCEDURE:</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">The patient was placed on the operating room table in the&nbsp;supine position.&nbsp;After adequate anesthesia and akinesia&nbsp;of the operative eye had been achieved with the use of a&nbsp;peribulbar block, the patient was prepped and draped in the&nbsp;usual sterile manner for ophthalmic surgery.&nbsp;A 15 degree&nbsp;blade was used to create two paracentesis at the corneoscleral&nbsp;limbus. Viscoelastic substance was instilled into the anterior&nbsp;chamber.&nbsp;A 2.65 scleral tunnel was created.&nbsp;A bent-needle&nbsp;cystotome and Utrata forceps were used to create a continuous&nbsp;tear capsulorrhexis in the anterior lens capsule. Balanced salt&nbsp;solution was injected into the lens capsule for hydrodissection&nbsp;to hydrodelineate the lens nucleus.&nbsp;The lens nucleus was&nbsp;phacoemulsified in a divide-and-conquer manner with the use&nbsp;of the phacoemulsification needle.&nbsp;The lens was cracked into&nbsp;two halves and then the two halves were then elevated into&nbsp;the iris plane with the use of a Pisacano spatula.&nbsp;In this&nbsp;manner, the two halves were then emulsified. Residual cortical&nbsp;and epinuclear material was removed with the use of the two-piece I&amp;A system.&nbsp;The lens capsule was filled with Provisc&nbsp;viscoelastic substance.&nbsp;The incision was widened to a 3.5 mm&nbsp;clear coreal incision with the use of the short cut blade.&nbsp;Next, an intraocular lens was opened, inspected and found to&nbsp;be in good condition.&nbsp;This was folded and then was inserted&nbsp;into the capsular bag with the use of the insertion forceps.&nbsp;The lens was rotated into position with the use of the Sinskey&nbsp;hook.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Residual cortical material and Viscoelastic material was&nbsp;removed from the eye with the use of the irrigation/aspiration&nbsp;handpiece.&nbsp;The wound was checked for water-tightness and was&nbsp;found to be so. 0.1 cc of Vancomycin solution, equivalent of 1&nbsp;mg of Vancomycin was instilled into the anterior chamber.&nbsp;The&nbsp;speculum and drapes were removed from the eye and the eye was&nbsp;seen to remain formed.&nbsp;The eye was patched and shielded with&nbsp;Maxitrol ointment and the patient brought back to the recovery&nbsp;room in excellent condition having tolerated the procedure well.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">______________________</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Paul D. Sforza, M.D.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',275,0,0),
(33,'DSAEK','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font: 12.0px Helvetica; min-height: 14.0px\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Procedure: {PROCEDURE}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Secondary procedure: {SECONDARY PROCEDURE}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Pre-op Diagnosis: {PRE-OP DIAGNOSIS}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Post-op Diagnosis: {POST-OP DIAGNOSIS}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">FINDINGS/PROCEDURE:</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">The operative eye was marked by the surgeon, prior to prepping by the circulating nurse. The</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">patient was brought to the operating room in good condition. IV sedation was administered by the</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">anesthesiologist. Retrobulbar anesthesia was administered by the anesthesiologist. The patient</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">was prepped and draped in the usual sterile fashion with attention to the operative eye. Operating</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">microscope with the assistance facility used for entirety of the procedure, lid speculum inserted.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">A limbal puncture was made at the superior and nasal limbus and a #20-gauge chamber maintainer</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">attached to BSS was inserted through the superior incision. A 7-mm corneal marker was used to</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">mark the central cornea. A 90-degree reverse Sinskey hook was then used to incise the underlying</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Descemet&rsquo;s membrane at the 7mm location and the membrane was removed using a Price Descemet&rsquo;s</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">stripper. A temporal limbal incision was then created with a keratome. The pre-cut donor tissue was</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">then placed on a trephine block and an 8.5 mm trephine was used to punch the donor tissue. The</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">donor graft was then placed endothelial side up on a Busin glide. Viscoelastic was placed on the</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">endothelium and the graft was transferred into the anterior chamber through the temporal incision by</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">pulling it with a Busin microforceps inserted across the anterior chamber through the nasal limbal</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">incision. Air was injected into the anterior chamber and the Mackool-Bechert spatula was inserted</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">through a limbal puncture and used to position the donor graft centrally. Additional air was then</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">injected beneath the donor tissue, forcing it against the host cornea. A continuous 10-0 nylon suture</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">was then used to close the primary incision. The wire lid speculum was removed and the soft patch</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">and Fox shield were applied after the instillation of topical vancomycin. The patient tolerated the</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">procedure well, and was maintained in the supine position for one hour in the recovery room</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">____________________________</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Richard J. Mackool, M.D.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',276,0,0),
(34,'PHACO TORIC','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px; min-height: 14px; font: 12px Helvetica\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">Procedure: {PROCEDURE}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">Secondary procedure: {SECONDARY PROCEDURE}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">Pre-op Diagnosis: {PRE-OP DIAGNOSIS}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">Post-op Diagnosis: {POST-OP DIAGNOSIS}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">PROCEDURE: The operative eye was marked by the surgeon, prior&nbsp;to prepping by the circulating nurse. The patient was brought&nbsp;to the operating room in good condition. Topical tetracaine&nbsp;was applied. The patient was prepped and draped in the usual&nbsp;manner. A lid speculum was inserted. The surgical operating&nbsp;microscope with coaxial illumination was used for the entirety&nbsp;of the surgical procedure with the assistant microscope&nbsp;attachment. Peripheral corneal paracentesis incisions were made&nbsp;using a 75 Beaver or similar blade at 2 o\'clock hours clockwise&nbsp;from the primary incision location. Preservative free Xylocaine&nbsp;1% was injected into the anterior chamber for intraocular&nbsp;anesthesia. A keratome was used to enter the anterior chamber&nbsp;beginning at the limbus and creating a clear corneal tunnel&nbsp;in the process. Viscoelastic was instilled in the anterior&nbsp;chamber. A bent tipped #25 gauge needle was used to initiate an&nbsp;anterior capsulotomy. Forceps were used to perform a circular&nbsp;capsulorhexis. Hydrodissection and cortical cleavage, followed&nbsp;by viscodissection were performed.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">The ultrasonic handpiece was then introduced through the&nbsp;incision and used to emulsify and aspirate the entire nucleus&nbsp;within the posterior chamber. During the phaco-emulsification&nbsp;procedure, a Mackool chopper was inserted through the corneal&nbsp;incisions in order to position, fracture, chop, and/or rotate&nbsp;the nucleus and continuously maintain its location away from the&nbsp;corneal endothelium at all times.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">Following completion of the phacoemulsification, the irrigation/&nbsp;aspiration handpiece was used to remove all remaining lens&nbsp;cortex.&nbsp;Viscoelastic was injected into the anterior chamber and&nbsp;capsular sac and the intraocular Toric lens was inserted into&nbsp;the capsular sac. Contact of all instruments with the corneal&nbsp;endothelium was carefully avoided. Viscoelastic was then&nbsp;irrigated and/or aspirated from the anterior chamber. The&nbsp;globe was inflated with BSS and the incisions were tested and&nbsp;noted to be watertight. 0.1cc Vancomycin solution was injected&nbsp;into anterior chamber. The lid speculum and sterile drapes were&nbsp;removed. The operating room table was returned to the upright&nbsp;(chair) position, and the patient remained seated for a short&nbsp;time in order to avoid any postural circulatory disturbance. The&nbsp;patient tolerated the procedure well, and was escorted to the&nbsp;recovery room in good condition.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">ADDENDUM: The axis desired for positioning of the toric IOL&nbsp;was marked as follows. With the patient sitting upright prior&nbsp;to beginning the procedure, the limbus was marked at 3, 6 and&nbsp;9 o&rsquo;clock. With the patient then supine, prepped and draped,&nbsp;the correct axis was marked using an axis marker. The IOL was&nbsp;aligned along this axis after its insertion.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">Richard J. Mackool, M.D.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',276,0,0),
(35,'WOUND REVISION','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font: 12.0px Helvetica; min-height: 14.0px\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Procedure: {PROCEDURE}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Secondary procedure: {SECONDARY PROCEDURE}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Pre-op Diagnosis: {PRE-OP DIAGNOSIS}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Post-op Diagnosis: {POST-OP DIAGNOSIS}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">FINDINGS/PROCEDURE:</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">The patient was taken to the operating room and placed supine on the operating room</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">table. After adequate topical anesthesia, the patient was prepped and draped in the</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">standard surgical fashion. A speculum was placed in the operative eye. Probable</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">intermediate wound leak noted inferotemporal. A 10-0 prolene x-type suture was</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">placed. No wound leak noted. Regular postoperative drops applied. Patient to recovery</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">room in stable condition. Regular postoperative drops applied. The patient returned to</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">the recovery room in stable condition.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">____________________________</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Richard J. Mackool, M.D.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',276,0,0),
(36,'PHACO','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font: 12.0px Helvetica; min-height: 14.0px\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Procedure: {PROCEDURE}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Secondary procedure: {SECONDARY PROCEDURE}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Pre-op Diagnosis: {PRE-OP DIAGNOSIS}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Post-op Diagnosis: {POST-OP DIAGNOSIS}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">FINDINGS/PROCEDURE:</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">After risks, benefits and alternatives were explained, informed consent was obtained from the</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">patient. Patient was brought to the operating room in good condition. IV, EKG and blood</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">pressure monitor were placed by the anesthesiologist. Patient was prepped and draped in</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">standard eye surgery fashion. A lid speculum was placed into the right eye. Using MVR blade,</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">paracentesis wounds were made at 6 o&rsquo;clock and 12 o&rsquo;clock. Nonpreserved lidocaine was</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">injected into the anterior chamber and viscoelastic was injected into the operative eye. Using</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">keratome blade, clear corneal temporal wound was made. Using cystotome and Utrata forceps,</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">a continuous curvilinear capsulorhexis was made. Hydrodissection was performed and the</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">lens was rotated. Lens was then sculpted and cracked and phacoemulsified on the iris plane.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">The intraocular lens was injected into the capsular bag and I/A was performed to remove the</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">viscoelastic from the eye. All the wounds were hydrated for watertight seal and intraocular lens</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">was noted to be in central position. Intraocular pressure was noted to be good. Vancomycin 1</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">mg and 0.1 cc was injected into eye. Patient tolerated the procedure well and was brought to the</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">recovery room in stable condition.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">_________________________</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Jannet Ung, M.D</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',277,0,0),
(37,'PHACO TRYPAN BLUE','<p style=\"margin: 0px; min-height: 14px; font: 12px Helvetica\"><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><br />\r\n</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Procedure: {PROCEDURE}</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Secondary Procedure: {SECONDARY PROCEDURE}</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">Pre-op Diagnosis: {PRE-OP DIAGNOSIS}</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: small\"><span style=\"font-family: Arial\" class=\"Apple-style-span\">Post-op Diagnosis: {POST-OP DIAGNOSIS}</span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><br type=\"_moz\" />\r\n</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger\">FINDINGS/PROCEDURE:</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><br />\r\n</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger\">This is a patient with decreased vision. The purpose of surgery&nbsp;is to increase vision as well as allow for a better view of&nbsp;the posterior pole.&nbsp;The risks and benefits of the procedure&nbsp;including possible hemorrhage, infection, loss of vision and&nbsp;poor eyesight were explained to the patient and understood.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger\">The patient was brought to the operating room after being&nbsp;dilated. The patient was prepped and draped in the usual&nbsp;manner after a peribulbar block had been given. A speculum&nbsp;was inserted under microscopic control and superior peritomy&nbsp;was made. Cautery was achieved near the limbus. The sclera was&nbsp;tunnel forward with a keratome and eye entered. Air was injected&nbsp;into the anterior chamber and then trypan blue was used to coat&nbsp;the capsule. Healon was injected to deep in the chamber and a&nbsp;paracentesis site was made laterally. Circular tear capsulotomy&nbsp;was made. Hydrodissection was performed with BSS. The nucleus&nbsp;was divided into four quardrants for phacoemulsification and&nbsp;separated. Each quadrant was removed separately. Posterior&nbsp;capsule was intact at the end of this procedure and irrigation-&nbsp;aspiration removed remaining cortex, leaving a clean posterior&nbsp;capsule. Under Healon a folding lens was placed in the bag and&nbsp;allowed to open and dialed into position. Healon was removed.&nbsp;The chamber was deepened with BSS through a paracentesis&nbsp;incision and the wound tested and found to be dry and firm. The&nbsp;conjunctiva was cauterized closed. Gentamicin and Decadron were&nbsp;injected in the inferior fornix. The speculum was removed and&nbsp;the eye was patched and shielded with Maxitrol ointment. The&nbsp;patient was instructed to take Diamox 250 mg tablets today and&nbsp;tomorrow and to be seen in the office for follow-up in the next&nbsp;day. The patient tolerated the procedure well.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><br />\r\n</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px\" class=\"Apple-style-span\"><br />\r\n</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><br />\r\n</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger\">Marc Rosenblatt, M.D.&nbsp;</span></p>',278,0,0),
(38,'PHACO ','<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font: 12.0px Helvetica; min-height: 14.0px\"><span style=\"font-size: larger; \"><br />\r\n</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">Procedure: {PROCEDURE}</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">Secondary procedure: {SECONDARY PROCEDURE}</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">Pre-op Diagnosis: {PRE-OP DIAGNOSIS}</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger; \"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: Arial; \">Post-op Diagnosis: {POST-OP DIAGNOSIS}</span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger; \"><br type=\"_moz\" />\r\n</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">FINDINGS/PROCEDURE:</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger; \"><br />\r\n</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">This is a patient with decreased vision. The purpose of surgery&nbsp;is to increase vision as well as allow for a better view of&nbsp;the posterior pole.&nbsp;The risks and benefits of the procedure&nbsp;including possible hemorrhage, infection, loss of vision and&nbsp;poor eyesight were explained to the patient and understood.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">The patient was brought to the operating room after being&nbsp;dilated.&nbsp;The patient was prepped and draped in the usual&nbsp;manner after a peribulbar block had been given.&nbsp;A speculum&nbsp;was inserted under microscopic control and superior peritomy&nbsp;was made.&nbsp;Cautery was achieved near the limbus. The sclera&nbsp;was tunneled forward with a keratome and eye entered.&nbsp;Healon&nbsp;was injected to deepen the chamber and a paracentesis site&nbsp;was made laterally.&nbsp;Circular tear capsulotomy was made.&nbsp;Hydrodissection was performed with BSS. The nucleus was divided&nbsp;into four quardrants for phacoemulsification and separated.&nbsp;Each quadrant was removed separately.&nbsp;Posterior capsule was&nbsp;intact at the end of this procedure and irrigation-aspiration&nbsp;removed remaining cortex, leaving a clean posterior capsule.&nbsp;Under Healon a folding lens was placed in the bag and allowed to&nbsp;open and dialed into position. Healon was removed. The chamber&nbsp;was deepened with BSS and vancomycin through a paracentesis&nbsp;incision and the wound tested and found to be dry and firm. The&nbsp;conjunctiva was cauterized closed.&nbsp;Decadron were injected in&nbsp;the inferior fornix.&nbsp;The speculum was removed and the eye was&nbsp;patched and shielded with Maxitrol ointment.&nbsp;The patient was&nbsp;instructed to be seen in the office for follow-up in the next&nbsp;day. The patient tolerated the procedure well.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger; \"><br />\r\n</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">Marc Rosenblatt, M.D.&nbsp;</span></p>',278,0,0),
(39,'PHACO TRYPAN BLUE','<p><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: Arial; font-size: 14px; \">Procedure: {PROCEDURE}</span></p>\r\n<p><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: Arial; font-size: 14px; \">Secondary procedure: {SECONDARY PROCEDURE}</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Pre-op Diagnosis: {PRE-OP DIAGNOSIS}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Post-op Diagnosis: {POST-OP DIAGNOSIS}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">FINDINGS/PROCEDURE:</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">The patient was seen in the preoperative area. The risks,&nbsp;benefits, and alternatives to surgery were discussed and all&nbsp;questions were answered. An informed operative consent was&nbsp;then obtained. The correct operative site was identified and&nbsp;marked. Attention was turned to that eye and dilating drops were&nbsp;instilled.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">The patient was transferred to the operating room. The patient&nbsp;and correct operative sites were re identified. The eye was&nbsp;prepped and draped in a sterile surgical fashion. Both upper and&nbsp;lower eyelashes were isolated with Tegaderm tape and the lids&nbsp;were held open with an adjustable speculum. An I-knife was used&nbsp;to create a paracentesis approximately 75 degrees to the left of&nbsp;the intended temporal incision site. 1% non preserved lidocaine&nbsp;was injected into the anterior chamber through the paracentesis.&nbsp;An air bubble was then injected into the anterior chamber with a&nbsp;blunted cannula through the paracentesis. Next, trypan blue was&nbsp;injected into the anterior chamber and then washed out with BSS&nbsp;on a blunted cannula approximately 30 seconds later. Viscoat was&nbsp;then injected into the anterior chamber through the paracentesis.&nbsp;Next, using a 2.2 mm sharp-tipped keratome, the anterior chamber&nbsp;was reentered via a temporal beveled clear corneal incision.&nbsp;Provisc was then injected into the eye through the new opening.&nbsp;A continuous curvilinear capsulorrhexis was created with the aid&nbsp;of a cystotome and Utrata forceps. Hydrodissection was carried&nbsp;out with a BSS and a cannula. The crystalline lens was then&nbsp;phacoemulsified and aspirated using a stop-and-chop technique.&nbsp;The I/A handpiece was next used to remove the remaining cortical&nbsp;material. Provisc was then injected into the capsular bag to&nbsp;deepen it.&nbsp;A lens of the appropriate power was placed in the capsular bag.&nbsp;The I/A handpiece was used to remove the residual viscoelastic.&nbsp;The eye was then palpated for appropriate pressure and adjusted&nbsp;accordingly with BSS. The self-healing clear corneal and&nbsp;paracentesis incisions were hydrated with BSS and a blunted&nbsp;cannula. The incisions were then tested for leaks and found to be&nbsp;negative. Topical Vigamox and Pred Forte 1% were instilled. All&nbsp;drapes were carefully removed and the eye was then covered with&nbsp;a protective shield. The patient tolerated the procedure well&nbsp;and was escorted to the recovery room in stable condition. The&nbsp;patient received standard postoperative instructions and informed&nbsp;to follow-up in the office the next day or to call sooner should&nbsp;they need arise.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Michael Ahdoot, M.D.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>',279,0,0),
