solated with Tegaderm tape</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">and the lids were held open with an adjustable speculum. An</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">I-knife was used to create a paracentesis, approximately 75</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">degrees to the left of the intended temporal incision site.</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">1% non preserved Lidocaine was injected into the anterior</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">chamber through the paracentesis followed by Viscoat. Next,</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">using a 2.2 mm sharp-tipped keratome, the anterior chamber</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">was reentered via a temporal beveled clear corneal incision.</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">Provisc was then injected into the eye through the new opening.</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">A continuous curvilinear capsulorrhexis was created with the aid</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">of cystotome and Utrata forceps. Hydrodissection was carried</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">out with BSS and a cannula. The crystalline lens was then</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">phacoemulsified and aspirated using a stop-and-chop technique.</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">The I/A handpiece was next used to remove the remaining cortical</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">material. Provisc was then injected into the capsular bag</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">to deepen it. A lens of appropriate power was placed in the</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">capsular bag. The I/A handpiece was used to remove the residual</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">viscoelastic. The eye was then palpated for appropriate</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">pressure and adjusted accordingly with BSS.</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">The self healing clear corneal and paracentesis incisions</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">were hydrated with BSS and a blunted cannula. The incisions</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">were then tested for leaks and found to be negative. Topical</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">Vigamox and Pred Forte 1% drops were instilled. All drapes were</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">carefully removed and the eye was covered with a protective</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">shield. The patient tolerated the procedure well and was</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">transferred to the recovery room on stable condition. The</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">patient received standard postoperative instructions and</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">informed to follow up in the office the next day or to call up</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">sooner should the need arise.</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger; \"><br />\r\n</span></div>\r\n<div><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-size: 14px;\"><br />\r\n</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger; \"><br type=\"_moz\" />\r\n</span></div>\r\n<div><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">Michael Ahdoot, M.D.</span></div>',279,0,0),
(41,'PHACO','<p><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: Arial; font-size: 14px; \">Procedure: {PROCEDURE}</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Secondary procedure: {SECONDARY PROCEDURE}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Pre-op Diagnosis: {PRE-OP DIAGNOSIS}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Post-op Diagnosis: {POST-OP DIAGNOSIS}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">FINDINGS/PROCEDURE:</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">The patient was brought to operating room and placed on OR table in supine position. The</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">patient was given a retrobulbar block consisting of lidocaine 2% and Marcaine 0.75% by the</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">anesthesiologist. The patient was then prepped and draped in sterile fashion. A lid speculum</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">was placed in the right eye. A conjunctival peritomy was performed using Westcott scissors.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Hemostasis was achieved using a light wet field cautery. A groove incision was made with</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">a crescent blade and two side-port incisions were made with an MVR blade. Aqueous humor</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">was replaced with Viscoat. The anterior chamber was entered using a 2.75-mm keratome.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">The lens nucleus was then hydrodissected with BSS on the irrigating cannula. The lens</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">nucleus was then phacoemulsified in a divide-and-conquer fashion. Nucleus cracking was</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">facilitated with the use of a Connor wand. Nuclear quadrants were then removed with</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">the phaco handpiece on increased vacuum setting. Epinuclear and cortical remnants were</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">removed with the I/A handpiece. To allow lens implantation, the capsular bag was inflated</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">with Provisc. An SN60WF 22.5-diopter posterior chamber lens implant was inserted using</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">the Monarch delivery system and the lens was dialed into the capsular bag with a Connor</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">wand. Residual viscoelastic was removed with the I/A handpiece. Miochol was instilled for</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">miosis and to maintain chamber depth. The side-port incisions were closed with BSS and</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">the wound was tested and was watertight. The conjunctiva was draped over the wound and</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">topical vancomycin was applied to the eye. The lid speculum was removed and the soft eye</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">pad and eye shield were placed over the eye and taped to the skin. Maxitrol ointment was</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">applied to the eye prior to the patching. The patient tolerated the procedure well and was</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">taken to the recovery room in stable condition.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">________________________</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Peter D&rsquo;Arienzo, M.D.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',280,0,0),
(42,'PHACO','<p><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: Arial; font-size: 14px; \">Procedure: {PROCEDURE}</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Secondary procedure: {SECONDARY PROCEDURE}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Pre-op Diagnosis: {PRE-OP DIAGNOSIS}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Post-op Diagnosis: {POST-OP DIAGNOSIS}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">FINDINGS/PROCEDURE: After obtaining informed consent and appropriate medical&nbsp;clearance, the patient was brought to the operating room and placed on the operating&nbsp;room table. A peribulbar block was performed and the patient was prepped and draped&nbsp;in the usual sterile manner for intraocular surgery. The operative eye was addressed.&nbsp;A lid speculum was placed and a superior limbal peritomy was performed. Hemostasis&nbsp;was obtained with wet field cautery. The paracentesis site was placed at the 2:30&nbsp;position. A scleral tunnel was fashioned to just anterior to the corneal arcade and the&nbsp;anterior chamber was entered in a dimple-down fashion forming a self-sealing corneal&nbsp;valve incision. Viscoelastic was used to fill the anterior chamber and continuous&nbsp;curvilinear capsulorrhexis was created. Hydro-dissection of the cortical-capsular and&nbsp;cortical-nuclear attachments was then performed. Two handed phacoemulsification&nbsp;with removal of the nucleus was performed without incident. Residual cortex was&nbsp;removed with irrigation/aspiration. Vitreous was seen presenting around the capsular&nbsp;bag and a limited anterior vitrectomy was performed. The posterior capsular bag was&nbsp;reinflated and a posterior chamber lens was injected into the posterior capsular bag and&nbsp;dialed into position. Residual Viscoelastic was removed. The anterior chamber was&nbsp;filled with balanced salt solution. The wound was tested and found to be water-tight.&nbsp;Conjunctiva was closed with cautery.&nbsp;Solu-Medrol and Gentamicin solution was used to irrigate the wound. TobraDex drops&nbsp;were placed in the eye and a pressure patch and Fox shield were placed. Iopidine&nbsp;was placed in the eye and the patient was sent to the recovery room. The patient is to&nbsp;follow-up with Dr. Richard Najac in 24 hours.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">__________________________</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Richard D. Najac, M.D.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',281,0,0),
(43,'PHACO','<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">Procedure: {PROCEDURE}</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">Secondary procedure: {SECONDARY PROCEDURE}</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">Pre-op Diagnosis: {PRE-OP DIAGNOSIS}</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger; \"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: Arial; \">Post-op Diagnosis: {POST-OP DIAGNOSIS}</span>&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger; \"><br type=\"_moz\" />\r\n</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">FINDINGS/PROCEDURE:</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger; \"><br />\r\n</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">The patient was brought to the operating room and put on the operating table in</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">the supine position. EKG, IV, blood pressure monitor were administered by the</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">anesthesiologist. The patient was dilated previously and topical anesthetics were</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">given. The patient was prepped and draped in the usual manner and lid speculum and</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">operating microscope were placed on the operative eye. A paracentesis tract was created</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">at the 6 and 12 o\'clock hours. Non-preserved lidocaine and epinephrine were instilled</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">followed by Viscoat and Provisc. A 2-mm clear corneal dissection was then created</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">temporally. A circular continuous capsulorrhexis was followed by hydrodissection and</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">hydrodelineation. The nucleus was then phacoemulsified and all cortical material was</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">irrigated and aspirated. The capsular bag was then inflated with Provisc and a foldable</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">6 mm acrylic lens was placed in the bag. The Provisc was irrigated and aspirated and</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">the wound was strongly hydrated. The wounds were ascertained to be watertight. The</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">lid speculum was removed and topical Betadine and TobraDex drops were instilled. The</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">patient tolerated the procedure well and left the operating room in excellent condition.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger; \"><br />\r\n</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">________________________</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">Laurence Weissman, M.D.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',282,0,0),
(44,'PHACO ','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px; min-height: 14px; font: 12px Helvetica\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">Procedure: {PROCEDURE}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">Secondary Procedure: {SECONDARY PROCEDURE}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">Pre-op Diagnosis: {PRE-OP DIAGNOSIS}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">Post-op Diagnosis: {POST-OP DIAGNOSIS}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">FINDINGS/PROCEDURE:</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">The patient was brought in the operating room in stable</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">condition. Patient was placed in the supine position.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">Proparacaine eyedrops were added. The operative eye was then</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">prepped with Betadine soap and solution and draped in the</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">usual sterile manner. A wire lid speculum was placed. A 5 mm</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">incision to one-third corneal depth was performed at the limbus</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">in a tangential manner using the 15 degree superblade. A clear</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">corneal incision was completed using the 2.65 mm keratome.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">Lidocaine 1% PF was injected followed by viscoat. A circular</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">continuous capsulorrhexis was performed using the bent 25</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">gauge needle. Hydrodissection with BSS with a flat cannula.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">The nucleus was then emulsified using the Alcon system.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">Cortical remnants were aspirated using the IA handpiece. The</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">incision was enlarged to 3.0 mm using the keratome and the</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">posterior chamber foldable IOL was implanted in the bag without</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">difficulty. The Viscoelastic was then aspirated using the</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">IA handpiece. 1 mg of Vancomycin was left in the anterior</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">chamber. BSS was added for the proper intraocular pressure.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">The wound was tested and found to be water-tight. Maxitrol eye</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">ointment was added and the eye was covered with an aluminum</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">shield. The patient tolerated the procedure well. There were</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">no complications. The patient left the operating room in stable</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">condition with instructions to follow up in one day.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">_____________________</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\">Marcel Admoni, M.D.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',283,0,0),
(45,'PHACO','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font: 12.0px Helvetica; min-height: 14.0px\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Procedure: {PROCEDURE}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Secondary procedure: {SECONDARY PROCEDURE}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Pre-op Diagnosis: {PRE-OP DIAGNOSIS}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Post-op Diagnosis: {POST-OP DIAGNOSIS}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">FINDINGS/PROCEDURE:</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">After risks, benefits and alternatives were discussed with the patient and all questions answered,</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">an informed consent was obtained. The patient was then brought to the operating room and</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">placed supine on the operating room table. EKG, IV, blood pressure monitoring and oxygen</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">were administered by the anesthesiologist. The eye was then anesthetized using topical</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">proparacaine solution. The eyelids were then prepped and draped in the usual standard fashion</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">for eye surgery. A lid speculum and operating microscope were then placed over the operative</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">eye. Two paracentesis tracts are created at the 6 and 12 o\'clock positions using a diamond MVR</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">blade. The anterior chamber was then instilled with 1% preservative-free lidocaine. The anterior</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">chamber was then filled with Viscoat. Corneal wound was then created temporally using a</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">2.3 mm diamond blade. A cystotome and Utrata forceps were then used to create a round</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">and curvilinear capsulorrhexis. The lens was then hydrodissected and hydrodelineated using</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">balanced salt solution. The lens was then phacoemulsified in a heminuclear fashion. All cortical</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">material was then irrigated and aspirated by way of the two-piece irrigation/aspiration system.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Provisc was then used to fill the capsular bag and an injectable SN60WF lens was placed in the</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">capsular bag and rotated into place. The remaining viscoelastic material was then irrigated and</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">aspirated from the eye. All wounds were stromally hydrated and ascertained to be watertight.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Vancomycin 1 mg was then instilled into the anterior chamber at the conclusion of the case. The</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">lid speculum and drapes were then removed from the eye. Vigamox and prednisolone acetate</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">solution were then placed over the eye. The patient tolerated the procedure well and returned</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">to the recovery room in good condition. The patient has instructions for followup in the office</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">within 24 hours&rsquo; time.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">________________________</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Nancy Cheng, M.D.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',284,0,0),
(46,'PTERYGIUM','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font: 12.0px Helvetica; min-height: 14.0px\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Procedure: {PROCEDURE}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Secondary procedure: {SECONDARY PROCEDURE}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Pre-op Diagnosis: {PRE-OP DIAGNOSIS}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Post-op Diagnosis: {POST-OP DIAGNOSIS}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">FINDINGS/PROCEDURE:</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">After risk and benefits and alternatives were discussed with the patient and all questions</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">answered, informed consent was obtained. The patient was then brought to the</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">operating room and placed spine on the operating room table. EKG, IV, blood pressure</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">monitoring and oxygen were administered by the anesthesiologist. The eye was</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">then prepped and draped in the usual sterile fashion for eye surgery. A lid speculum</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">and operating microscope were then placed over the operative eye. The pterygium</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">was then marked with a marking pen. The body of the pterygium was injected with</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">2% lidocaine with epinephrine. The pterygium was then excised using blunt Westcott</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">scissors and the head excised in a lamellar fashion. The corneal scleral junction was</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">smoothed with a diamond bur as well as a Beaver blade. All bleeders were lightly</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">cauterized. Next, mitomycin C 0.2 mg/mL concentration was placed on the area of the</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">scleral bed for a total of two minutes. The eye was then copiously irrigated with two</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">bottles of balanced salt solution. Next, attention was turned to the superior conjunctiva</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">where an appropriately-sized conjunctival autograft was measured and cut leaving</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">careful dissection of all Tenons behind. This conjunctival autograft was then rotated</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">into place and secured using Tisseel fibrin glue. The glue was allowed to set for a total</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">of 30 seconds and was noted to be in good position with secured placement.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">The eye was then irrigated with balanced salt solution. Any excess glue was excised</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">from the eye and conjunctival fornices. The lid speculum and drapes were then</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">removed from the eye. Maxitrol ointment, one-eye patch were then placed over the</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">patient&rsquo;s operative eye. The patient tolerated the procedure well and returned to</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">recovery room in good condition.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">__________________________</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Nancy Cheng, M.D.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',284,0,0),
(47,'PHACO','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font: 12.0px Helvetica; min-height: 14.0px\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Procedure: {PROCEDURE}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Secondary procedure: {SECONDARY PROCEDURE}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Pre-op Diagnosis: {PRE-OP DIAGNOSIS}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Post-op Diagnosis: {POST-OP DIAGNOSIS}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">FINDINGS/PROCEDURE:</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">The patient was brought to the operating room table. A 4 cc</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">mixture of 3% Lidocaine was given as a posterior peribulbar</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">block administered by anesthesiologist. The patient was then</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">prepped and draped in the usual sterile manner for ophthalmic</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">surgery. A lid speculum was placed on the operative eye.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Conjunctival peritomy was performed from the 11 o\'clock to the 1</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">o\'clock position and the bleeders were cauterized. A groove was</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">made for 4 mm along the surgical limbus and a scleral tunnel was</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">formed to clear cornea.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Side port incisions were made at the 1 o\'clock and 3 o&rsquo;clock</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">positions with the blade. Viscoat was injected into the eye.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Keratome was used to enter the eye through the scleral tunnel.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">A 360&deg; anterior capsulorrhexis was performed along the margin of</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">the pupil and the anterior capsular flap was retracted out of</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">the eye.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Hydrodissection was performed with BSS in order to loosen</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">and rotate the nucleus. The phacoemulsification machine was</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">introduced into the eye and the nucleus was sculpted and</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">emulsified along the vertical meridian, rotated to 180 degrees</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">and further sculpted. Using the nuclear chopper, and the phaco</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">port, nucleus was cracked in half; the heminucleus was brought</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">into the midchamber, ant that was cracked in half as well as the</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">other heminucleus.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">The remaining quadrants were brought into the center of the</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">anterior chamber and further emulsified. The I/A machine was</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">then used to remove residual cortical material from the anterior</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">and posterior chamber. Provisc was injected along the posterior</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">capsule. The intraocular lens was folded and placed into the</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">capsule bag. The IOL was well centered. The viscoelastic was</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">removed with the I/A machine. One mg of vancomycin in 0.1cc of</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">BSS was injected into the eye through the side port incision.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">The wound was tested for integrity. There was no leak. The</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">conjuntiva was apposed with cautery. One drop of Maxitrol was</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">applied. A patch and shield applied. The patient tolerated the</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">procedure well.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Raphael Aharon, M.D.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',285,0,0),
(48,'CAT LRI','<p><span style=\"font-size: larger\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px; min-height: 14px; font: 12px Helvetica\"><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><br />\r\n</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: larger\">Procedure: {PROCEDURE}</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: larger\">Secondary procedure: {SECONDARY PROCEDURE}</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: larger\">Pre-op Diagnosis: {PRE-OP DIAGNOSIS}</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0px 0px 12px; font: 14px Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: larger\">Post-op Diagnosis: {POST-OP DIAGNOSIS}</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><br type=\"_moz\" />\r\n</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger\">PROCEDURE: The patient was marked at the 3,6 and 9 o&rsquo;clock positions</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger\">prior to entering the room in a standing position. The patient was</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger\">brought to the operating room. Routine cardiopulmonary monitoring</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger\">was applied. The patient received light sedation and was prepped and</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger\">draped in the usual sterile fashion. A wire lid speculum was placed</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger\">in the appropriate eye. The microscope was moved into position.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger\">Topical Tetracaine was instilled over the eye. A stab incision</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger\">was made at the appropriate position, 90 degree from the temporal</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger\">incision. 1% Lidocaine (preservative free) was injected into the</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger\">anterior chamber. Through the same side port, Viscoelastic material</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger\">was injected into the anterior chamber. Using a 2.2mm Keratome,</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger\">a clear corneal temporal incision was made in beveled fashion.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger\">Using the cystotome, a circular capsulorrhexis was performed. The</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger\">nucleus was then hydrodissected using BSS on a 27-gauge cannula.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger\">Using the phaco probe, the nucleus was removed in a divide and</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger\">conquer technique without complication. Using the I&amp;A, the cortex</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger\">was removed without complications. The capsular bag was filled with</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger\">Healon. A folding SN60 lens, which was preloaded into the shooter,</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger\">was injected into the capsular bag and rotated into position using</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger\">the Sinskey hook. After insertion of the lens, using a 2.75mm</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger\">keratome at the appropriate axis and incision was made at the</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger\">limbal corneal region. Using the I&amp;A, the viscoelastic material was</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger\">removed. The wound was hydrated. The chamber was deep and the IOL</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger\">was well positioned. The wire lid speculum was removed. Topical</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger\">PreForte and Ocuflux was instilled on the eye. The patient was sent</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger\">to the recovery room in good condition.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger\"><br />\r\n</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 14px\" class=\"Apple-style-span\">________________________</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger\">Lawrence Blum, M.D.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',286,0,0),
(49,'PHACO','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font: 12.0px Helvetica; min-height: 14.0px\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Procedure: {PROCEDURE}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Secondary procedure: {SECONDARY PROCEDURE}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Pre-op Diagnosis: {PRE-OP DIAGNOSIS}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Post-op Diagnosis: {POST-OP DIAGNOSIS}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">PROCEDURE: The patient was brought to the operating room. Routine</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">cardiopulmonary monitoring was applied. The patient received light</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">sedation and was prepped and draped in the usual sterile fashion. A</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">wire lid speculum was placed in the appropriate eye. The microscope</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">was moved into position. Topical Tetracaine was instilled over the</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">eye. A stab incision was made at the appropriate position, 90 degree</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">from the temporal incision. 1% Lidocaine (preservative free) was</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">injected into the anterior chamber. Through the same side port,</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Viscoelastic material was injected into the anterior chamber. Using</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">a 2.2mm Keratome, a clear corneal temporal incision was made in</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">beveled fashion. Using the cystotome, a circular capsulorrhexis was</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">performed. The nucleus was then hydrodissected using BSS on a 27-</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">gauge cannula. Using the phaco probe, the nucleus was removed in a</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">divide and conquer technique without complication. Using the I&amp;A,</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">the cortex was removed without complications. The capsular bag was</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">filled with Healon. A folding SN60 lens, which was preloaded into</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">the shooter, was injected into the capsular bag and rotated into</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">position using the Sinskey hook. Using the I&amp;A, the viscoelastic</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">material was removed. The wound was hydrated. The chamber was deep</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">and the IOL was well positioned. The wire lid speculum was removed.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Topical PreForte and Ocuflux was instilled on the eye. The patient</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">was sent to the recovery room in good condition.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">________________________</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Lawrence Blum, M.D.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: Arial, Verdana, sans-serif; font-size: 12px; \">&nbsp;</span></p>',286,0,0),
(50,'PHACO','<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font: 12.0px Helvetica; min-height: 14.0px\"><span style=\"font-size: larger; \"><br />\r\n</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">Procedure: {PROCEDURE}</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">Secondary procedure: {SECONDARY PROCEDURE}</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">Pre-op Diagnosis: {PRE-OP DIAGNOSIS}</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger; \"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: Arial; \">Post-op Diagnosis: {POST-OP DIAGNOSIS}</span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger; \"><br type=\"_moz\" />\r\n</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">FINDINGS/PROCEDURE:</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger; \"><br />\r\n</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">After informed consent was obtained, the patient was taken to the OR and laid on the OR in</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">supine position. After IV sedation, local anesthesia was achieved using topical lidocaine.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">The patient was prepped and draped in the usual sterile fashion exposing the left eye. A lid</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">speculum was placed in the left eye. A Supersharp blade was used to create a stab incision</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">with the left hand. Intracameral lidocaine without preservative was injected into the anterior</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">chamber followed by viscoelastic. A 2.4-mm keratome was used to create a temporal clear</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">corneal incision with the right hand. A bent tip cystotome was used to create a continuous</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">curvilinear capsulorrhexis. BSS in a syringe was used for hydrodissection. The lens was rotated</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">and removed using phacoemulsification. All remaining cortical material was removed using the</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">irrigation aspiration tip. The viscoelastic was injected into the anterior chamber so as to fill the</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">capsular bag and an intraocular lens was placed in the capsular bag. The irrigation aspiration</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">tip was used to remove viscoelastic from the eye. Intracameral antibiotic was injected into the</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">anterior chamber. BSS in a syringe was used to irrigate the wounds. The wounds were checked</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">for leaks, which there were none. The patient was taken to the recovery room and instructed no</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">bending, lifting or straining, and to follow up the following day in Dr. Hornfeld&rsquo;s office.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger; \"><br />\r\n</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">__________________________</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">Mark Hornfeld M.D.&nbsp;</span></p>',287,0,0),
(51,'PHACO','<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font: 12.0px Helvetica; min-height: 14.0px\"><span style=\"font-size: larger; \"><br />\r\n</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">Procedure: {PROCEDURE}</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">Secondary procedure: {SECONDARY PROCEDURE}</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">Pre-op Diagnosis: {PRE-OP DIAGNOSIS}</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger; \"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: Arial; \">Post-op Diagnosis: {POST-OP DIAGNOSIS}</span></span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger; \"><br type=\"_moz\" />\r\n</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">FINDINGS/PROCEDURE:</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger; \"><br />\r\n</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">The patient was brought to the operating room in stable condition. EKG, blood pressure,</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">IV fluid and oxygen were administered by the anesthesiologist. Anesthesia was obtained</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">using tetracaine. The patient was then prepped and draped in the usual sterile fashion. The</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">lid speculum inserted in the operative eye and operating room microscope was then placed.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">Anterior paracenteses were created at 12 and 6 o\'clock positions. Additional anesthesia was</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">obtained using 1% MPF Lidocaine. The anterior chamber fluid was then replaced by Viscoat.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">A 2.6-mm keratome was used to reconstruct temporal clear corneal wound. Capsulorrhexis</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">performed. Hydrodissection carried out. Using divide and conquer technique with the phaco</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">handpiece, the nucleus was removed followed by cleaning of the cortex material. After the</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">cataract has been removed, Provisc was used to inflate the capsular bag. Acrylic foldable lens,</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">SN60WF, was then inserted into the capsular bag. Provisc removed. Wound was inspected and</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">found to be watertight. Postoperative injection given. Lid speculum removed. Antibiotic drop</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">was then given. Shield placed. The patient tolerated the procedure well, to be seen on the next</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">day.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger; \"><br />\r\n</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">__________________________</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">Panus Romsaitong, M.D.&nbsp;</span></p>',288,0,0),
(59,'Phaco with Trypan Blue','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div>\r\n<div><b>Procedure: {PROCEDURE}</b></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><b>Secondary Procedure: {SECONDARY&nbsp;PROCEDURE}&nbsp;</b></div>\r\n<div align=\"center\">\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><b>PREOPERATIVE DIAGNOSIS:</b>&nbsp;Mature cataract or Dense anterior subcapsular opacity<b>, {SITE}</b></div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><b>POSTOPERATIVE DIAGNOSIS:</b> Same</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><b>OPERATION:&nbsp;</b>Phacoemulsification of complex cataract, insertion of&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; intraocular lens,&nbsp;<strong>{SITE}</strong> Capsular dye</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><b>PROCEDURE:&nbsp;</b>The operative eye was marked by the surgeon, prior to prepping by the circulating nurse. The patient was brought to the operating room in good condition.&nbsp;Topical anesthetic was applied.&nbsp;The patient was prepped and draped in the usual manner.&nbsp;A lid speculum was inserted. The surgical operating microscope with coaxial illumination was used for the entirety of the surgical procedure with the assistant microscope attachment.&nbsp;Peripheral corneal paracentesis incisions were made using a 75 Beaver or similar blade at 2 o\'clock hours clockwise from the primary incision location.&nbsp;Preservative free Xylocaine 1% was injected into the anterior chamber for intraocular anesthesia.&nbsp;A keratome was used to enter the anterior chamber beginning at the limbus and creating a clear corneal tunnel in the process.&nbsp;Viscoelastic was instilled in the anterior chamber.&nbsp;A bent tipped #25 gauge needle was used to initiate an anterior capsulotomy.&nbsp;Forceps were used to perform a circular capsulorhexis.&nbsp;Hydrodissection and cortical cleavage, followed by viscodissection were performed.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div align=\"left\">The ultrasonic handpiece was then introduced through the incision and used to emulsify and aspirate the entire nucleus within the posterior chamber.&nbsp;During the phaco-emulsification procedure, a Mackool chopper was inserted through the corneal incision in order to position, fracture, chop, and/or rotate the nucleus and continuously maintain its location away from the corneal endothelium at all times.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div align=\"left\">Following completion of phacoemulsification, the irrigation/</div>\r\n<div align=\"left\">aspiration handpiece was used to remove all remaining lens cortex.&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <b>(clear cornea)</b>&nbsp;</div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;Viscoelastic was injected into the anterior chamber and capsular sac and the intraocular lens was inserted into the capsular sac.</div>\r\n<div>Contact of all instruments with the corneal endothelium was carefully avoided.&nbsp;Viscoelastic was then irrigated and/or aspirated from the anterior chamber.&nbsp;The globe was inflated with BSS and the incisions were tested and noted to be watertight.&nbsp;0.1cc Vancomycin solution was injected into anterior chamber.&nbsp;The lid speculum and sterile drapes were removed.&nbsp;The operating room table was returned to the upright (chair) position, and the patient remained seated for a short time in order to avoid any postural circulatory disturbance. The patient tolerated the procedure well, and was escorted to the recovery room in good condition.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div><b><u>ADDENDUM:</u></b> Dense cataract and or anterior subcapsular opacity, inadequate red reflex. Therefore, air instilled in anterior chamber. Capsular dye instilled on the anterior capsule and left in place several seconds. Viscoelastic then used in exchange for air. In this manner, the anterior capsule was better visualized for capsulotomy.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;Richard J. Mackool, M.D.</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>D: {DATE}</div>\r\n<div>T: {TEXTBOX_MEDIUM}</div>\r\n<div>&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div>{Surgeon\'s Signature}</div>',276,0,0),
(60,'Cat. Ext./ Cap. Polish','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0in -0.5in 0pt 0in; mso-outline-level: 1\" class=\"MsoNormal\"><b style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">Preoperative Diagnosis</span></b><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">:<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; {PRE-OP DIAGNOSIS}{SITE}</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0in -0.5in 0pt 0in; mso-outline-level: 1\" class=\"MsoNormal\"><b style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">Postoperative Diagnosis</span></b><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">:<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;{POST-OP DIAGNOSIS} {SITE}</span></span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-indent: 0.75in; margin: 0in -0.5in 0pt -0.75in\" class=\"MsoNormal\"><b style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">Operative Procedure</span></b><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">:<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes\">&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><span style=\"mso-tab-count: 2\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; {PROCEDURE}</span></span><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\"> {SITE}</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"text-indent: 0.75in; margin: 0in -0.5in 0pt -0.75in\" class=\"MsoNormal\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\" class=\"MsoNormal\"><b style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">Description</span></b><b style=\"mso-bidi-font-weight: normal\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Book Antiqua\',\'serif\'\">:</span></b><span style=\"font-family: \'Book Antiqua\',\'serif\'\"> </span><span style=\"font-family: \'Book Antiqua\',\'serif\'; font-size: 11pt\">The patient was admitted to the surgery center.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes\">&nbsp; </span>Eye drops were instilled as ordered</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\" class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-family: \'Book Antiqua\',\'serif\'; font-size: 11pt\">on arrival. </span><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">The patient was taken to the operating room and prepped and draped in the usual </span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\" class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">sterile technique. <span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes\">&nbsp;</span>The operating microscope was positioned and the lid speculum was inserted.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\" class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\"><span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes\">&nbsp; </span>At the onset of the procedure, the eye was </span><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">irrigated with balanced salt solution and the fornices </span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\" class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">swabbed with a Weck sponge.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes\">&nbsp; </span>Paracentesis was performed at approximately 2 o&rsquo;clock. </span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\" class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">Viscoelastic was instilled in the anterior chamber to deepen it. A shelved self-sealing incision </span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\" class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">made with a Diamond keratome blade at the 10 o&rsquo;clock position quadrant.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes\">&nbsp; </span>Capsulotomy was </span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\" class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">performed with a bent-tipped 25-gauge needle for 360 degrees in a circular continuous tear </span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\" class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">technique.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes\">&nbsp; </span>Hydro dissection was performed with balanced salt solution using an angled hydro </span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\" class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">dissection needle. The phacoemulsification procedure was performed creating approximately </span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\" class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">90% thickness grooves going from the incision to 180 degrees opposite the incision and then </span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\" class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">cracking the groove with a Grayson chopper held with the surgeon&rsquo;s left hand and the phaco tip </span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\" class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">with the right hand.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes\">&nbsp; </span>The lens was rotated in 90 degrees quadrants with each quadrant being </span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\" class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">grooved and cracked until all four quadrants had been similarly prepared and the </span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\" class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">phacoemulsification tip used to remove each of the four quadrants.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes\">&nbsp; </span>I&amp;A was used to remove </span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\" class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">soft cortex for 360 degrees by a peeling technique.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes\">&nbsp; </span>The posterior capsule was polished centrally</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\" class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">and in any area that residual cortical tags remained. The posterior surface of the anterior </span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\" class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">capsule was polished in the 270 degrees opposite the incision.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes\">&nbsp; </span>The anterior chamber was </span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\" class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">deepened with viscoelastic.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes\">&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>The injector was loaded with the lens implant.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes\">&nbsp; </span>The tip of the </span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\" class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">injector was inserted into the incision with gentle pressure on the plunger.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes\">&nbsp; </span>The lens was then</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\" class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">inserted into the capsule bag and rotated into position. The I&amp;A tip was used to remove the </span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\" class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">viscoelastic for 360 degrees in the anterior and posterior chambers.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes\">&nbsp; </span>At the end of the procedure, </span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\" class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">balanced salt solution was used to hydrate the incision along its ends and and centrally and the </span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\" class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">anterior chamber was deepened with balanced salt solution and pressurized. No sutures were </span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\" class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">placed at this point as testing of the wound showed it to be watertight because of the internal </span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\" class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">flap mechanism.<span style=\"mso-spacerun: yes\">&nbsp;&nbsp; </span>One drop of Pilocarpine 2%&nbsp;was instilled in the operative eye at the end of the</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\" class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">&nbsp;case. All instruments and drapes were removed from the eye. Antibiotic ointment was applied on </span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\" class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">the ocular surface. The patient was sent to the recovery room in good condition, having tolerated </span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\" class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">the procedure well. Instructions were given to see Dr. Hiatt the day following the procedure for </span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\" class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">follow-up evaluation, at which time further directions will be given.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0in -0.5in 0pt 40px\" class=\"MsoNormal\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0in -0.5in 0pt -0.75in\" class=\"MsoNormal\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;{LAST NAME}{MIDDLE INITIAL}{PATIENT FIRST NAME}{DOB}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0in -0.5in 0pt -0.75in\" class=\"MsoNormal\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; {SURGEON NAME}{DOS}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0in -0.5in 0pt -0.75in\" class=\"MsoNormal\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\"><o:p>&nbsp;</o:p></span></p>',307,0,0),
(52,'PHACO','<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font: 12.0px Helvetica; min-height: 14.0px\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Procedure: {PROCEDURE}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Secondary procedure: {SECONDARY PROCEDURE}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Pre-op Diagnosis: {PRE-OP DIAGNOSIS}</p>\r\n<p><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: Arial; font-size: 14px; \">Post-op Diagnosis: {POST-OP DIAGNOSIS}</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;PROCEDURE: The operative eye was marked by the surgeon, prior&nbsp;to prepping by the circulating nurse. The patient was brought to the operating room in good condition. Topical anesthetic&nbsp;was applied. The patient was prepped and draped in the usual&nbsp;manner. A lid speculum was inserted. The surgical operating&nbsp;microscope with coaxial illumination was used for the entirety&nbsp;of the surgical procedure with the assistant microscope&nbsp;attachment. Peripheral corneal paracentesis incisions were made&nbsp;using a 75 Beaver or similar blade at 2 o\'clock hours clockwise&nbsp;from the primary incision location. Preservative free Xylocaine 1% was injected into the anterior chamber for intraocular&nbsp;anesthesia. A keratome was used to enter the anterior chamber&nbsp;beginning at the limbus and creating a clear corneal tunnel&nbsp;in the process. Viscoelastic was instilled in the anterior&nbsp;chamber. A bent tipped #25 gauge needle was used to initiate an&nbsp;anterior capsulotomy. Forceps were used to perform a circulard&nbsp;capsulorhexis. Hydrodissection and cortical cleavage, followed&nbsp;by viscodissection were performed.</p>\r\n<p>The ultrasonic handpiece was then introduced through the&nbsp;incision and used to emulsify and aspirate the entire nucleus&nbsp;within the posterior chamber. During the phaco-emulsification&nbsp;procedure, a Mackool chopper was inserted through the corneal&nbsp;incision in order to position, fracture, chop, and/or rotate the&nbsp;nucleus and continuously maintain its location away from the&nbsp;corneal endothelium at all times.</p>\r\n<p>Following completion of phacoemulsification, the irrigation/&nbsp;aspiration handpiece was used to remove all remaining lens&nbsp;cortex.&nbsp;Viscoelastic was injected into the anterior chamber and capsular&nbsp;sac and the intraocular lens was inserted into the capsular sac.&nbsp;Contact of all instruments with the corneal endothelium was&nbsp;carefully avoided.&nbsp;Viscoelastic was then irrigated and/&nbsp;or aspirated from the anterior chamber.&nbsp;The globe was&nbsp;inflated with BSS and the incisions were tested and noted to&nbsp;be watertight.&nbsp;0.1cc Vancomycin solution was injected into&nbsp;anterior chamber.&nbsp;The lid speculum and sterile drapes were&nbsp;removed.&nbsp;The operating room table was returned to the upright&nbsp;(chair) position, and the patient remained seated for a short&nbsp;time in order to avoid any postural circulatory disturbance.</p>\r\n<p>The patient tolerated the procedure well, and was escorted to&nbsp;the recovery room in good condition.</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Richard Jonathan Mackool,</p>\r\n<p>M.D.</p>',289,0,0),
(53,'PHACO','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font: 12.0px Helvetica; min-height: 14.0px\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Procedure: {PROCEDURE}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Secondary procedure: {SECONDARY PROCEDURE}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Pre-op Diagnosis: {PRE-OP DIAGNOSIS}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Post-op Diagnosis: {POST-OP DIAGNOSIS}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">FINDINGS/PROCEDURE:</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">With the patient prepped and draped in the usual manner and under fractional anesthesia with</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">intravenous sedative, peribulbar block was performed using Xylocaine. The surgical operating</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">microscope was used for the entirety of the procedure with the assistant micro-surgical facility.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">A Lieberman lid speculum was placed. A superior clear cornea 2.50 incision was made and</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">under viscoat, continuous tear capsulorrhexis capsulotomy was carried out. Hydrodissection and</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">hydrodelineation was performed and ultrasonic handpiece of the phaco-emulsification unit was</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">introduced into the eye and used to emulsify and remove the nucleus in the posterior chamber.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">The ultrasonic handpiece was removed. Irrigation-aspiration handpiece was introduced and used</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">to remove all remaining lens cortex. A foldable posterior chamber intraocular lens was placed</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">in the capsular bag, with care taken to avoid contact with corneal endothelium. Vancomycin</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">was instilled intracamerally. The lid speculum was removed. Antibiotic ointment and a shield</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">applied. The patient tolerated the procedure well and left the operating room in good condition.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">____________________________</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">William Boozan, M.D.</p>\r\n</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>',291,0,0),
(54,'PHACO TRYPAN BLUE','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font: 12.0px Helvetica; min-height: 14.0px\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Procedure: {PROCEDURE}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Secondary procedure: {SECONDARY PROCEDURE}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Pre-op Diagnosis: {PRE-OP DIAGNOSIS}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Post-op Diagnosis: {POST-OP DIAGNOSIS}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">FINDINGS/PROCEDURE:</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">With the patient prepped and draped in the usual manner and under fractional anesthesia with</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">intravenous sedative, peribulbar block was performed using Xylocaine. The surgical operating</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">microscope was used for the entirety of the procedure with the assistant micro-surgical facility.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">A Lieberman lid speculum was placed. A superior clear cornea 2.50 incision was made and</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">trypan blue introduced after Viscoat exchange, continuous tear capsulorrhexis capsulotomy was</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">carried out. Hydrodissection and hydrodelineation was performed and ultrasonic handpiece of</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">the phaco-emulsification unit was introduced into the eye and used to emulsify and remove the</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">nucleus in the posterior chamber. The ultrasonic handpiece was removed. Irrigation-aspiration</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">handpiece was introduced and used to remove all remaining lens cortex. A foldable posterior</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">chamber intraocular lens was placed in the capsular bag, with care taken to avoid contact with</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">corneal endothelium. Vancomycin was instilled intracamerally. The lid speculum was removed.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Antibiotic ointment and a shield applied. The patient tolerated the procedure well and left the</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">operating room in good condition.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">____________________________</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">William Boozan, M.D.</p>\r\n</p>',291,0,0),
(55,'PHACO','<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font: 12.0px Helvetica; min-height: 14.0px\"><span style=\"font-size: larger; \"><br />\r\n</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">Procedure: {PROCEDURE}</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">Secondary procedure: {SECONDARY PROCEDURE}</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">Pre-op Diagnosis: {PRE-OP DIAGNOSIS}</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger; \"><span class=\"Apple-style-span\" style=\"font-family: Arial; \">Post-op Diagnosis: {POST-OP DIAGNOSIS}</span>&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger; \"><br type=\"_moz\" />\r\n</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger; \"><br type=\"_moz\" />\r\n</span></p>\r\n<p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">FINDINGS/PROCEDURE:</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger; \"><br />\r\n</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">Prior to going to the surgery, all risks, benefits and alternatives were discussed in detail with the</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">patient. All questions were answered. Informed consent was obtained and placed in the medical</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">record. The patient was brought to the operating room in stable condition and placed into the supine</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">position. Following mild sedation, the anesthesiologist administered a peribulbar anesthetic block. The</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">operated was then prepped and draped in the usual sterile fashion.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger; \"><br />\r\n</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">A sterile lid speculum was inserted and removed at the end of the case. Superior paracentesis was</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">created, followed by injection of Viscoat to inflate the anterior chamber. A clear corneal incision</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">was made temporally with a 2.4-mm keratome in a biplanar fashion. A cystotome was used to start</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">a continuous circular capsulorrhexis, which was finished using Utrata forceps. BSS was used to</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">hydrodissect the lens nucleus away from capsular bag. Complete nucleus mobility was achieved.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">Phacoemulsification probe and a chopper were used in concert to divide the lens nucleus into smaller</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">pieces, which were then removed without difficulties.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger; \"><br />\r\n</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">Next, irrigation and aspiration handpiece was used to clean up the capsular bag from cortical material.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">The capsular bag was re-inflated with Provisc and a single-piece foldable lens implant (SN60WF) was</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">then injected into the capsular bag without incident. The lens implant was seen to be in good position</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">and well centered. Viscoelastic device was removed with the IA probe. Intracameral vancomycin was</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">injected. The incisions were then stromally hydrated with BSS. All wounds were checked for leaks</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">and none were noted. Intraocular pressure was brought to physiologic level. The eye was then dressed</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">with vigamox and prednisolone acetate 1% drops, patched and shielded. The patient tolerated the</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">procedure well and was transferred to the recovery room in excellent condition.</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger; \"><br />\r\n</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">___________________________</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">Suzanna Airiani, M.D.</span></p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n</p>',292,0,0),
(56,'DSAEK','<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font: 12.0px Helvetica; min-height: 14.0px\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Procedure: {PROCEDURE}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Secondary procedure: {SECONDARY PROCEDURE}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Pre-op Diagnosis: {PRE-OP DIAGNOSIS}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Post-op Diagnosis: {POST-OP DIAGNOSIS}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">FINDINGS/PROCEDURE:</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">A peribulbar anesthetic block was administered with anesthesia &amp; akinesia, the wire lid speculum was</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">placed. With the patient prepped and draped in the usual manner, A 7 mm superficial corneal marking</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">made on the anterior corneal surface. Two incisions were created, one small paracentesis nasally and</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">triplana clear corneal incision was created 3.2mm temporally. The chamber maintainer was inserted</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">and a 90&deg; spatula was then used to initiate, score and complete removal of Descemet&rsquo;s membrane.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">The precut cornea for DSAEK from the eyebank (cut to specifications) was excised endothelial side up</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">and stromal side down (marked). This was positioned in the Busim cartridge endothelium up (stromal</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">side on contact to cartridge). The forceps were passed nasally through the paracentesis, then through</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">the anterior chamber and the corneal incision. The Busim cartridge was rotated 180&deg; so the stromal</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">side faced anterior. The transplant was then pulled into the anterior chamber with the forceps. A</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">running 10-0 nylon suture was used to close the corneal incision. The chamber maintainter was then</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">slowly infused for a sufficient chamber. A 30 gauge air syringe (self-sealed) was used to centralize and</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">tamponade the endothelium transplant against the host stroma. Option: four vertical stromal incisions</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">was placed to remove intra stromal fluid. The wire lid speculum was removed and a soft patch and Fox</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">shield were applied after installation of topical medications. The patient tolerated the procedure well,</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">and was maintained in the supine position for one hour in order to promote adherence, and check IOP.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Following a slit lamp exam, patient was examined and sent home.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">_________________________</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Wilson Ko, M.D.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n</p>',293,0,0),
(57,'PHACO','<p><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font: 12.0px Helvetica; min-height: 14.0px\"><span style=\"font-size: larger; \"><br />\r\n</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">Procedure: {PROCEDURE}</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">Secondary procedure: {SECONDARY PROCEDURE}</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">Pre-op Diagnosis: {PRE-OP DIAGNOSIS}</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">Post-op Diagnosis: {POST-OP DIAGNOSIS}</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: larger; \"><br type=\"_moz\" />\r\n</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: larger; \"><br type=\"_moz\" />\r\n</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">PROCEDURE:</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: larger; \"><br />\r\n</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">The patient was brought to the operating room in good condition.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">Topical tetracaine was applied. The patient was prepped and draped</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">in the usual manner. A lid speculum was inserted. The surgical</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">operating microscope with coaxial illumination was used for the</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">entirety of the surgical procedure with the assistant microscope</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">attachment. Peripheral corneal stab incisions were made by using</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">a 75 Beaver blade. Preservative free Xylocaine 1% was injected</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">into the anterior chamber for intraocular anesthesia. BSS was</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">injected in the anterior chamber. A keratome 2.6 - 2.75mm was used</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">to enter the anterior chamber beginning at the temporal limbus and</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">creating a clear corneal tunnel in the process. Viscoelastic was</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">instilled in the anterior chamber. Forceps were used to perform a</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">circular capsulorhexis. Hydrodissection was performed with a #27</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">gauge cannula. The Infinity handpiece was then introduced through</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">the incision with reverse flow in order to automatically inflate</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">the anterior chamber upon insertion. The ultrasonic handpiece</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">was used to emulsify and aspirate the entire nucleus within the</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">posterior chamber. During the phacoemulsification procedure,</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">a phaco chopper was inserted through one of the corneal limbal</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">incisions in order to position, fracture, chop, and/or rotate</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">the nucleus and continuously maintain its location away from the</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">corneal endothelium at all times.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: larger; \"><br />\r\n</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">Following completion of the phacoemulsification, the irrigation/</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">aspiration handpiece was used to remove all remaining lens cortex.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">Any non fibrous opacifications of the posterior capsule were then</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">removed with the Kratz scratcher.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: larger; \"><br type=\"_moz\" />\r\n</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">Viscoelastic was again injected into the anterior chamber.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">The intraocular lens was inserted into the capsule bag in one</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">motion, using the injector mechanism or forceps.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: larger; \"><br />\r\n</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">Contact of all instruments with the corneal endothelium was</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">carefully avoided. Viscoelastic was then irrigated and/or</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">aspirated from the anterior chamber. The globe was inflated</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">with BSS and the wound was tested and noted to be watertight.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">0.1cc Vancotmycin (theraputically dilated) was injected via</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">the cannula thru the paracentesis. Two drops of Tobradex,</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">pilo 2 iopidine were applied topically. The lid speculum was</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">removed. Sterile drapes were removed. The patient tolerated</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">the procedure well. The operating room table was returned to</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">the upright (chair) position, and the patient remained seated</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">for a short time in order to avoid any postural circulatory</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">disturbance. The patient tolerated the procedure well, and was</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">escorted to the recovery room in good condition.</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: larger; \"><br />\r\n</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">_</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: larger; \"><br />\r\n</span></p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\"><span style=\"font-size: larger; \">Wilson Ko, M.D.</span></p>\r\n</p>',293,0,0),
(58,'PHACO','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px 0.0px; font: 12.0px Helvetica; min-height: 14.0px\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Procedure: {PROCEDURE}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Secondary procedure: {SECONDARY PROCEDURE}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Pre-op Diagnosis: {PRE-OP DIAGNOSIS}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Post-op Diagnosis: {POST-OP DIAGNOSIS}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">FINDINGS/PROCEDURE:</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">The patient was seen in the preoperative area and properly identified. The patient had received</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">dilation and antibiotic eye drops. The eye was then prepped and draped in a sterile surgical</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">fashion. Both upper and lower eyelashes were isolated with Tegaderm tape and the eyelids</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">were held open with a speculum. First, using a MVR blade, a paracentesis port was created.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Preservative-free lidocaine 1% followed by Viscoat was injected into the anterior chamber.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Next, using a 2.6-mm keratome the anterior chamber was reentered via clear corneal incision. A</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">continuous curvilinear capsulorhexis was created with the aid of a cystotome and capsulorhexis</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">forceps. Hydrodissection was performed with BSS until nucleus was freely mobile. Crystal lens</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">was then phacoemulsified and aspirated using a divide and conquer technique. Irrigation and</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">aspiration hand piece was next used to remove the cortical material. Provisc was then injected</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">into the capsular bag to deepen it. Posterior chamber intraocular lens of proper size and power</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">was placed in the capsular bag with the aid of a shooter. Irrigation and aspiration hand piece was</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">used to remove the residual viscoelastic material. Miochol was then injected into the anterior</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">chamber to constrict the pupil and the main incision was hydrated by BSS. The speculum was</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">then carefully removed. Maxitrol ophthalmic ointment and eye patch were placed over the eye.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Patient tolerated the procedure well and was transferred to the recovery room in stable condition.</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">_________________________</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin: 0.0px 0.0px 12.0px 0.0px; font: 14.0px Arial\">Ted Du, M.D.</p>\r\n</p>',294,0,0),
(82,'Cataract/IFIS/ LARK/ Provisc','<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\"><span style=\"font-size: small\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman\">PREOPERATIVE DIAGNOSIS:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; {PRE-OP DIAGNOSIS}, {SITE}</span></span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\"><span style=\"font-size: small\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Alpha-1 adrenergic receptor antagonist use</span></span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\"><span style=\"font-size: small\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman\">POSTOPERATIVE DIAGNOSIS: {POST-OP DIAGNOSIS},{SITE}</span></span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\"><span style=\"font-size: small\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Floppy iris syndrome</span></span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\"><span style=\"font-size: small\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman\">OPERATIVE PROCEDURE:<strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</strong>{PROCEDURE} <span style=\"font-size: 12pt\">{SITE}<strong>&nbsp;</strong></span></span></span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\"><span style=\"font-size: small\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman\">\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in -0.25in 0pt 0in\">&nbsp;\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in -0.25in 0pt 0in\"><b><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">DESCRIPTION: </span></b><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">The patient was admitted to the surgery center.&nbsp;Eye drops were instilled as ordered on arrival. Betadine solution diluted 1:1 with normal balanced salt solution was instilled.&nbsp;The peri-bulbar block administered by anesthesia. Refer to anesthesia record for medications used and amounts. The Honan balloon was placed on the eye at a pressure level of 30mm of mercury prior to surgery.&nbsp;The eye was tested and found to have good anesthesia and akinesia.&nbsp;The patient was taken to the operating room and prepped and draped in the usual sterile manner.&nbsp;The operating microscope was positioned and the lid speculum introduced.&nbsp;A stab paracentesis was placed at approximately 12 o&rsquo;clock position in clear cornea using the Diamond blade fully extended. Viscoelastic was instilled in the eye. A marker was used and marks were placed at the limbus at the _____degree axis with the diamond blade set at 600 microns for a length of _____ and _____limbal &ndash;relaxing incision(s) was made. A groove incision was made with the Diamond blade at 0 .25mm at approximately 10 o&rsquo;clock position just anterior to the limbal vessels.&nbsp;The Diamond blade fully extended was inserted into the clear cornea up to the shoulder of the blade and then the angle of the blade is changed so that it is in the plane of the iris and then the anterior chamber is entered. A 27 gauge bent-tipped needle was used to make a continuous tear capsulorrhexis.&nbsp;A 27-gauge cannula attached to a syringe filled with balanced salt solution was then introduced to perform hydrodissection of the nucleus from the posterior layer of cortex.&nbsp;The phacoemulsification handpiece was inserted and phacoemulsification was performed.&nbsp;The nucleus was emulsified primarily in the posterior chamber.&nbsp;Cortical materials were removed using the irrigating and aspirating unit. The iris was noted to be &ldquo;floppy&rdquo; with a tendency to prolaspse from the paracentisis and the incision. The capsule appeared entirely intact with an intact capsulorrhexis and an intact posterior capsular bag.&nbsp;The delivery tip for the lens was introduced into the corneal incision just into the anterior chamber and then the intraocular lens implant was slowly injected into the posterior capsular bag. The residual Viscoelastic material was removed with the I&amp;A tip. Balanced salt solution was injected into the eye to fill it to the normal pressure.&nbsp;The eye was tested by pressing on the eye and the incision was noted to be watertight.&nbsp;The chamber remained deep.&nbsp;One drop of Pilocarpine 2% was applied to the eye.&nbsp;Antibiotic ointment was applied.&nbsp;The patient was taken to the recovery area in good condition. </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\"><b>&nbsp;</b></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\"><b>&nbsp;</b></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in -0.25in 0pt 0in\">\r\n<p>{LAST NAME}{MIDDLE INITIAL}{PATIENT FIRST NAME}{DOB}</p>\r\n<p>{SURGEON NAME}{DOS}</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in -0.25in 0pt 0in\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\"><b>&nbsp;</b></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\"><b>&nbsp;</b></div>\r\n</span></span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\">&nbsp;</div>',311,0,0),
(83,'Complicated Cat.Ext/ Vision Blue','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in -0.5in 0pt 0in\"><b><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">Preoperative Diagnosis</span></b><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">:&nbsp; &nbsp;{PRE-OP DIAGNOSIS},{SITE}</span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in -0.5in 0pt 0in\"><b><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">Postoperative Diagnosis</span></b><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">: {POST-OP DIAGNOSIS}, {SITE}</span></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-indent: 0.75in; margin: 0in -0.5in 0pt -0.75in\"><b><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">Operative Procedure</span></b><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; {PROCEDURE},</span><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\"> {SITE}</span></div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">Description: The patient was admitted to the surgery center.&nbsp;Eye drops were instilled as ordered arrival. The peri-bulbar block was administered by the C.R.N A.&nbsp;Refer to anesthesia record for medications used and amounts.&nbsp;Following the injection, one drop of Betadine solution which was diluted with balanced salt solution 1:1 was instilled.&nbsp;The Honan balloon was placed on the operative eye at a pressure level of 20mm of mercury for approximately 20 minutes.&nbsp;The eye was tested and found to have good anesthesia and akinesia. The patient was taken to the operating room and prepped and draped in the usual sterile technique.&nbsp;The operating microscope was positioned and the lid speculum was inserted.&nbsp;At the onset of the procedure, the eye was irrigated with balanced salt solution and the fornices swabbed with a Weck sponge.&nbsp;Paracentesis was performed at approximately 2 o&rsquo;clock. A shelved self-sealing incision made with a Diamond keratome blade at the 10 o&rsquo;clock position quadrant.&nbsp;&nbsp; Filtered air was injected into the anterior chamber.&nbsp;Beneath the air, Vision Blue was injected over the anterior lens capsule in order to stain the capsule for capsulotomy. 3cc&rsquo;s of Balanced Salt solution was used to rinse the anterior chamber free of Vision Blue. Viscoelastic was instilled in the anterior chamber to deepen it cornea. Capsulotomy was performed with a bent-tipped 25-gauge needle for 360 degrees in a circular continuous tear technique.&nbsp;Hydro dissection was performed with balanced salt solution using an angled hydro dissection needle. The phacoemulsification procedure was performed creating approximately 90% thickness grooves going from the incision to 180 degrees opposite the incision and then cracking the groove with a Grayson chopper held with the surgeon&rsquo;s (site) hand and the phaco tip with the right hand.&nbsp;The lens was rotated in 90 degrees quadrants with each quadrant being grooved and cracked until all four quadrants had been similarly prepared and the phacoemulsification tip used to remove each of the four quadrants.&nbsp;I&amp;A was used to remove soft cortex for 360 degrees by a peeling technique.&nbsp;The posterior capsule was polished centrally and in any area that residual cortical tags remained. The posterior surface of the anterior capsule was polished in the 270 degrees opposite the incision.&nbsp;The anterior chamber was deepened with viscoelastic.&nbsp;&nbsp; The injector was loaded with the lens implant.&nbsp;The tip of the injector was inserted into the incision with gentle pressure on the plunger.&nbsp;The lens was then inserted into the capsule bag and rotated into position. The I&amp;A tip was used to remove the viscoelastic for 360 degrees in the anterior and posterior chambers.&nbsp;At the end of the procedure, balanced salt solution was used to hydrate the incision along its ends and and centrally and the anterior chamber was deepened with balanced salt solution and pressurized. No sutures were placed at this point as testing of the wound showed it to be watertight because of the internal flap mechanism.&nbsp;&nbsp; One drop of Pilocarpine 2% was instilled in the operative eye at the end of the case. All instruments and drapes were removed from the eye. Antibiotic ointment was applied on the ocular surface. The patient was sent to the recovery room in good condition, having tolerated the procedure well. Instructions were given to see Dr. Hiatt the day following the procedure for follow-up evaluation, at which time further directions will be given.</span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in -0.5in 0pt -0.75in\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<p>{LAST NAME}{MIDDLE INITIAL}{PATIENT FIRST NAME}{DOB}</p>\r\n<p>{SURGEON NAME}{DOS}</p>',307,0,0),
(84,'Cat. Ext./Miochol','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in -0.5in 0pt 0in\"><b><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">Preoperative Diagnosis</span></b><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">:&nbsp; &nbsp;{PRE-OP DIAGNOSIS}{SITE}</span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in -0.5in 0pt 0in\"><b><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">Postoperative Diagnosis</span></b><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">: {POST-OP DIAGNOSIS} {SITE}</span></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-indent: 0.75in; margin: 0in -0.5in 0pt -0.75in\"><b><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">Operative Procedure</span></b><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; {PROCEDURE}</span><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\"> {SITE}</span></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-indent: 0.75in; margin: 0in -0.5in 0pt -0.75in\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\"><b><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">Description</span></b><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">:&nbsp;In the holding area, the patient was dilated with Cyclogyl 1% and Neosynephrine</span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">2.5%.&nbsp;In addition, drops of Tetracaine, Nevanec and Vigamox were given on arrival by the </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">admitting nurse.&nbsp;The peri-bulbar block was administered by the C.R.N A.&nbsp;Refer to anesthesia </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">record for medications used and amounts.&nbsp;Following the injection, one drop of Betadine solution </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">which was diluted with balanced salt solution 1:1 was instilled.&nbsp;The honan</span> <span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">balloon was placed </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">on the operative eye at a pressure level of 20mm of mercury for approximately 20 minutes.&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">The eye was tested and found to have good anesthesia and akinesia. The patient was taken </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">to the operating room and prepped and draped in the usual sterile technique.&nbsp;The operating </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">microscope was positioned and the lid speculum was inserted.&nbsp;At the onset of the procedure, the </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">eye was irrigated with balanced salt solution and the fornices swabbed </span><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">with a Weck sponge.</span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">&nbsp;Paracentesis was performed at approximately 2 o&rsquo;clock. Viscoelastic was instilled in the </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">anterior chamber to deepen it cornea from drying and to keep the visual clarity of the cornea at its </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">optimum. A shelved self-sealing incision made with a Diamond keratome blade at the 10 0&rsquo;clock </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">position quadrant.&nbsp;Capsulotomy was performed with a bent-tipped 25-gauge needle for </span><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">360 degrees </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">in a circular continuous tear technique.&nbsp;Hydro dissection was performed with </span><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">balanced salt solution </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">using an angled hydro dissection needle. The phacoemulsification </span><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">procedure was performed creating approximately 90% thickness grooves going from the incision</span><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">to 180 degrees opposite the incision and</span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\"> then cracking the groove with a Grayson chopper held </span><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">with the surgeon&rsquo;s left hand and the phaco tip </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">with the right hand.&nbsp;The lens was rotated in </span><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">90 degrees quadrants with each quadrant being grooved </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">and cracked until all four quadrants </span><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">had been similarly prepared and the phacoemulsification tip used to remove each of the four </span><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">quadrants.&nbsp;I&amp;A was used to remove soft cortex for 360 degrees by a peeling technique.&nbsp;The </span><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">posterior capsule was polished centrally and in any area that residual cortical tags remained. The </span><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">posterior surface of the anterior capsule was polished at 270 degrees opposite the incision.&nbsp;The </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">anterior chamber was deepened with viscoelastic.&nbsp;The injector was loaded with the lens implant.&nbsp;The</span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">tip of the injector was inserted into the incision with gentle pressure on the plunger.&nbsp;The lens </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">was then inserted into the capsule bag and rotated into position. The I&amp;A tip was used to </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">remove the viscoelastic for 360 degrees in the anterior and posterior chambers. 1 cc of Miochol </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">was instilled into the anterior chamber.&nbsp;At the end of the procedure, balanced salt solution was </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">used to hydrate the incision along its ends and and centrally and the anterior chamber was </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">deepened with balanced salt solution and pressurized. No sutures were placed at this point </span><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">as testing </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">of the wound showed it to be watertight because of the internal flap mechanism.&nbsp;One </span><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">drop of</span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\"> Pilocarpine 2%&nbsp; was instilled in the operative eye at the end of the case. All instruments </span><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">and drapes </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">were removed from the eye. Antibiotic ointment was applied on the ocular surface. </span><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">The patient was </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">sent to the recovery room in good condition, having tolerated the procedure well. </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">Instructions were given to see Dr. Hiatt the day following the procedure for follow-up evaluation, </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">at which time further </span><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">directions will be given.</span></div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>{LAST NAME}{MIDDLE INITIAL}{PATIENT FIRST NAME}{DOB}</p>\r\n<p>{SURGEON NAME}{DOS}</p>',307,0,0),
(85,'Cat.Ext/zonular dehiscence/Morcher Capsular Tension Ring','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in -0.5in 0pt 0in\"><b><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">Preoperative Diagnosis</span></b><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">:&nbsp; &nbsp;{PRE-OP DIAGNOSIS}{SITE}</span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in -0.5in 0pt 0in\"><b><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">Postoperative Diagnosis</span></b><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">: {POST-OP DIAGNOSIS} {SITE}</span></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-indent: 0.75in; margin: 0in -0.5in 0pt -0.75in\"><b><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">Operative Procedure</span></b><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;{PROCEDURE}</span><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\"> {SITE}</span></div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\"><b><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">Description</span></b><b>:</b> <span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">The patient was admitted to the surgery center.&nbsp;Eye drops were instilled as ordered </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">on arrival. </span><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">The peri-bulbar block was administered by the C.R.N A.&nbsp;Refer to anesthesia record for </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">medications used and amounts.&nbsp;Following the injection, one drop of Betadine solution which was</span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">diluted with balanced salt solution 1:1 was instilled.&nbsp;The Honan balloon was placed on the </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">operative eye at a pressure level of 20mm of mercury for approximately 20 minutes.&nbsp;The eye </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">was tested and found to have good anesthesia and akinesia. The patient was taken to the </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">operating room and prepped and draped in the usual sterile technique.&nbsp;The operating microscope</span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">was positioned and the lid speculum was inserted.&nbsp;At the onset of the procedure, the eye was</span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">irrigated with balanced salt solution and the fornices swabbed with a Weck sponge.&nbsp;Paracentesis was performed at approximately 2 o&rsquo;clock. Viscoelastic was instilled in the anterior chamber to </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">deepen it. A shelved self-sealing incision made with a Diamond keratome blade at the 10 o&rsquo;clock </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">position quadrant.&nbsp;Capsulotomy was performed with a bent-tipped 25-gauge needle for</span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">360 degrees in a circular continuous tear technique.&nbsp;Hydro dissection was performed with </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">balanced salt solution using an angled hydro dissection needle. The phacoemulsification </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">procedure was performed creating approximately 90% thickness grooves going from the incision </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">to 180 degrees opposite the incision and then cracking the groove with a Grayson chopper held </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">with the surgeon&rsquo;s left hand and the phaco tip with the right hand.&nbsp;The lens was rotated in </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">90 degrees quadrants with each quadrant being grooved and cracked until all four quadrants </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">had been similarly prepared and the phacoemulsification tip used to remove each of the four quadrants.&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">I&amp;A was used to remove soft cortex for 360 degrees by a peeling technique.&nbsp;The </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">posterior capsule was polished centrally and in any area that residual cortical tags remained. </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">The posterior surface of the anterior capsule was polished in the 270 degrees opposite the </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">incision.&nbsp;The anterior chamber was deepened with viscoelastic.&nbsp;&nbsp; The injector was loaded with </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">the lens implant.&nbsp;The tip of the injector was inserted into the incision with gentle pressure on the </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">plunger.&nbsp;The lens was then inserted into the capsule bag and rotated into position.&nbsp;After lens </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">implantation, a small amount of zonular dehiscence, approximately 2 o&rsquo;clock hour was noted </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">inferiorly and the lens was noted not to be well centered.&nbsp;More viscoelastic was used to fill the </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">capsular bag.&nbsp;A Morcher capsular tension ring was loaded into the shooter and inserted via the </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">clear corneal incision, into the capsular bag, after which, the capsular bag was noted to be well </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">approximated and the intraocular lens was noted to be well centered. The I&amp;A tip was used to </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">remove the viscoelastic for 360 degrees in the anterior and posterior chambers.&nbsp;At the end of the </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">procedure, balanced salt solution was used to hydrate the incision along its ends and and </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">centrally and the anterior chamber was deepened with balanced salt solution and pressurized. </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">No sutures were placed at this point as testing of the wound showed it to be watertight because </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">of the internal flap mechanism.&nbsp;&nbsp; One drop of Pilocarpine 2%&nbsp;was instilled in the operative eye </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">at the end of the case. All instruments and drapes were removed from the eye. Antibiotic </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">ointment was applied on the ocular surface. The patient was sent to the recovery room in good </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">condition, having tolerated the procedure well. Instructions were given to see Dr. Hiatt the day </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">following the procedure for follow-up evaluation, at which time further directions will be given.</span></div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;{LAST NAME} {MIDDLE INITIAL} {LAST NAME}</p>\r\n<p>{SURGEON NAME}: {DOS}</p>',307,0,0),
