n, having tolerated the procedure well. Instructions were given </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">to see Dr. Hiatt the day following the procedure for follow-up evaluation, at which time further </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">directions</span><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">&nbsp;will be given.</span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in -0.5in 0pt -0.75in\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; &nbsp;{LAST NAME}{MIDDLE INITIAL}{PATIENT FIRST NAME}{DOB}</div>\r\n<p>{SURGEON NAME}{DOS}</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',307,0,0),
(64,'Crystalen ','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in -0.5in 0pt 0in\"><span style=\"font-size: small\"><b>Preoperative Diagnosis</b>:</span><span style=\"font-size: small\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;{PRE-OP DIAGNOSIS}</span><span style=\"font-size: small\"> {SITE}</span></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-indent: 0.75in; margin: 0in -0.5in 0pt -0.75in\"><span style=\"font-size: small\"><b>Postoperative Diagnosis</b>:&nbsp;&nbsp;{POST-OP DIAGNOSIS}{SITE}</span></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-indent: 0.75in; margin: 0in -0.5in 0pt -0.75in\"><span style=\"font-size: small\"><b>Operative Procedure</b>:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;{PROCEDURE}</span><span style=\"font-size: small\"> {SITE} </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-indent: 27pt; margin: 0in -0.5in 0pt -0.75in\"><span style=\"font-size: small\">&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size: small\"><b>Description:</b> </span>The patient was admitted to the surgery center.&nbsp;Eye drops were instilled as ordered</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\">on arrival. The peri-bulbar block was administered by the C.R.N. A.&nbsp;Refer to anesthesia record for medications used and amounts.&nbsp;Following the injection, one drop of Betadine solution which wasdiluted with balanced salt solution 1:1 was</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\">instilled.&nbsp;The Honan balloon was placed on theoperative eye at a pressure level of 20mm of mercury for approximately 20 minutes.&nbsp;The eye wastested and found to have good anesthesia and akinesia. The patient was taken to the operating</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\">room and prepped and draped in the usual sterile technique.&nbsp;The operating microscope waspositioned and the lid</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\">speculum was inserted.&nbsp;At the onset of the procedure, the eye wasirrigated with balanced salt solution and the fornices</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\">swabbed with a Weck sponge.&nbsp;Paracentesis was performed at approximately 2 o&rsquo;clock. Viscoelastic was instilled in the</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\">anterior chamber todeepen it. A shelved self-sealing incision made with a Diamond keratome blade at the</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\">10 0&rsquo;clock position quadrant.&nbsp;Capsulotomy was performed with a bent-tipped 25-gaugeneedle for 360 degrees in a circular continuous tear technique.&nbsp;Hydro dissection was performedwith balanced salt solution using an angled hydro dissection</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\">needle. The phacoemulsificationprocedure was performed creating approximately 90% thickness grooves going from the</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\">incision to 180 degrees opposite the incision and then cracking the groove with a Graysonchopper held with the surgeon&rsquo;s</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\">left hand and the phaco tip with the right hand.&nbsp;The lens wasrotated in 90 degrees quadrants with each quadrant being</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\">grooved and cracked until all four quadrants had been similarly prepared and the phacoemulsification tip used to remove</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\">each of the four quadrants.&nbsp;I&amp;A was used to remove soft cortex for 360 degrees by a peeling technique.&nbsp;The posterior</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\">capsule was polished centrally and in any area that residual cortical tags remained.The posterior surface of the anterior</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\">capsule was polished at 270 degrees opposite the incision.&nbsp;The&nbsp;anterior chamber was deepened with viscoelastic.&nbsp;&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\">The injector was loaded with the Crystalens implant.&nbsp;The tip of the injector was inserted into the incision with gentle</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\">pressure on the plunger.&nbsp;The lens was then inserted into the capsule bag and rotatedinto position. The I&amp;A tip was used</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\">to remove the viscoelastic for 360 degrees in theanterior and posterior chambers.&nbsp;At the end of the procedure, balanced</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\">salt solutionwas used to hydrate the incision along its ends and and centrally and the anteriorchamber was deepened</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\">with balanced salt solution and pressurized. No sutures wereplaced at this point as testing of the wound showed it to be</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\">watertight because of the internal flap mechanism.&nbsp;&nbsp; One drop of Pilocarpine 2%&nbsp;was instilled in the operative eye</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\">at the end of the case. All instruments and drapes were removed from the eye. Antibiotic ointment was applied on</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\">the ocular surface. The patient was sent to the recovery roomin good condition, having tolerated the procedure well.</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\">Instructions were given to see Dr. Hiatt the day following the procedure for follow-up evaluation, at which time further</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\">directions will be given.</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in -0.5in 0pt -0.75in\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-indent: 27pt; margin: 0in -0.5in 0pt -0.75in\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;{LAST NAME}{MIDDLE INITIAL}{PATIENT FIRST NAME}{DOB}</p>\r\n<p>{SURGEON NAME}{DOS}</p>',307,0,0),
(109,'ICL','<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\"><span style=\"font-size: small\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman\">PREOPERATIVE DIAGNOSIS: {PRE-OP DIAGNOSIS}, {SITE}</span></span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\"><span style=\"font-size: small\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman\">POSTOPERATIVE DIAGNOSIS: {POST-OP DIAGNOSIS},{SITE}</span></span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\"><span style=\"font-size: small\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman\">OPERATIVE PROCEDURE:<strong> </strong>{PROCEDURE}{SITE}\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in -0.25in 0pt 0in\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in -0.25in 0pt 0in\"><b><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">DESCRIPTION:</span></b><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\"> In the holding area, the patient was dilated with Mydriacyl 1% and AK Dilate 10% Every 5 minutes x 3 on arrival. Also, a drop of Nevanec, Vigamox and Tetracaine were given on arrival. They patient received I.V. sedation and a peri-bulbar block which was administered by anesthesia. Refer to anesthesia record for medications used and amounts administered. Betadine solution diluted 1:1 with normal balanced salt solution was instilled. The Honan balloon was placed on the eye at a pressure level of 30mm of mercury prior to surgery. The eye was tested and found to have good anesthesia and akinesia. The patient was taken to the operating room and prepped and draped in the usual sterile manner. The operating microscope was used to load the ICL into the shooter and the microscope was repositioned and the lid speculum introduced. A stab paracentesis was placed at approximately 12 o&rsquo;clock position and Occucoat was instilled into the eye. A second stab paracentisis was made at 6:00 o&rsquo;clock and a 0.25mm groove made for the incision at 10:00 o&rsquo;clock. A keratome blade was used to slightly enlarge this incision. The ICL was slowly injected into the anterior chamber, verifying that the positioning hole was on top, centered, and the orientation hole on the right leading haptic was on the right to ensure the lens was being inserted into the eye in the correct orientation. Once the lens was in, additional Occucoat was instilled into the eye. The ICL manipulator was used to tuck the leading and trailing haptic into the ciliary sulcus, under the iris. Viscoelastic was removed by flushing the anterior chamber with 9cc of BSS. Miochol was instilled to reduce the pupil over the haptics. The lens implant appeared to be stable and centered. The speculum and drape were removed and a drop of Moxeza was instilled. Antibiotic ointment was applied. The patient was taken to the recovery area in good condition. </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n</span></span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\"><span style=\"font-size: small\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman\">\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in -0.25in 0pt 0in\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt\">{LAST NAME}{MIDDLE INITIAL}{PATIENT FIRST NAME}{DOB}</span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in -0.25in 0pt 0in\">\r\n<p>{SURGEON NAME}{DOS}</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in -0.25in 0pt 0in\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in -0.25in 0pt 0in\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n</span></span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',312,0,0),
(110,'Entropion Repair','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in -167.25pt 0pt 0in\">Preoperative Diagnosis: Entropian {SITE} Lower Lid</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in -167.25pt 0pt 0in\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in -167.25pt 0pt 0in\">Postoperative Diagnosis: Same</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in -167.25pt 0pt 0in\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\">Operative Procedure: Entropian Repair {SITE} Lower Lid</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\">Description: The patient was admitted to the surgery center and given 5mg of Valium orally. The patient was taken to the operating room and prepped and draped in the usual sterile manner. The operating microscope was positioned. Drops of Tetracaine were instilled into the operative eye. Xylocaine 2% PF, approximately 1 ml was injected along the lower eye lid. Double armed 5-0 Chromic Gut suture was placed with the suture going in from the inside of the eyelid below the inferior tarsal plate, exiting just inferior to the lid margin. Two sutures were passed right next to each other and tied. Three of these sutures were placed in the right lower eyelid and two were placed on the left to create an ectropian. Tobradex ointment was placed along the lower lid line. The patient was taken to the recovery room in good condition. Post-operative instructions were given to the patient prior to discharge.</div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>{LAST NAME}{MIDDLE INITIAL}{PATIENT FIRST NAME}{DOB}</p>\r\n<p>{SURGEON NAME}{DOS}</p>',312,0,0),
(133,'Refloat Graft','<p style=\"text-align: center\">ReVision Advanced Surgery Center</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left\">&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left\">Patient Name: {PATIENT FIRST NAME} {MIDDLE INITIAL} {LAST NAME}</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left\">Date of Surgery: {DOS}</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left\">Pre-Op Diagnosis: {PRE-OP DIAGNOSIS}</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left\">Post-Op Diagnosis: {POST-OP DIAGNOSIS}</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left\">Procedure(s):</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left\">Primary: {PRIMARY PROCEDURE}</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left\">Secondary: {SECONDARY PROCEDURE}</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left\">Tertiary: {TERTIARY PROCEDURE}</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left\">Surgeon Name: {SURGEON NAME}, M.D.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left\">Operative Note:</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left\">The patient was taken to the operating room and placed in the supine postion.&nbsp; After adequate anesthesia was determined, the patient was prepped and draped in the usual sterile manner.&nbsp; A wire lid speculum was placed into the eye.&nbsp; Air on a 3cc syringe with a 30g needle was used to enter the anterior.&nbsp; A large air bubble was placed into the anterior chamber forcing the donor tissue to be opposed to the posterior aspect of the patient\'s cornea.&nbsp; A large air bubble was allowed to remain in place for 15 minutes adjusting the intraocular pressure to be sure that the retina had adequate profusion.&nbsp; The majority of the air bubble was allowed to remain in the anterior chamber.&nbsp; The patient will remain supine for the rest of today.&nbsp; The lid speculum was removed.&nbsp; The patient was discharged in stable condition.</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left\">Discharge Summary:</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left\">The patient was given post-operative instructions and a follow up appointment.&nbsp; The patient was then released from ReVison in good ambulatory condition.</p>',350,0,0),
