o&rsquo;clock. A keratome blade was used to slightly enlarge this incision.&nbsp;The ICL was slowly injected into the anterior chamber, verifying that the positioning hole was on top, centered, and the orientation hole on the right leading haptic was on the right to ensure the lens was being inserted into the eye in the correct orientation.&nbsp;Once the lens was in, additional Occucoat was instilled into the eye.&nbsp;The ICL manipulator was used to tuck the leading and trailing haptic into the ciliary sulcus, under the iris. Viscoelastic was removed by flushing the anterior chamber with 9cc of BSS.&nbsp;Miochol was instilled to reduce the pupil over the haptics.&nbsp;The lens implant appeared to be stable and centered.&nbsp;The speculum and drape were removed and a drop of Moxeza was instilled. Antibiotic ointment was applied.&nbsp;The patient was taken to the recovery area in good condition. </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\"><b>&nbsp;</b></div>\r\n</span></span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\"><span style=\"font-size: small\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman\">\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in -0.25in 0pt 0in\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt\">{LAST NAME}{MIDDLE INITIAL}{PATIENT FIRST NAME}{DOB}</span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in -0.25in 0pt 0in\">\r\n<p>{SURGEON NAME}{DOS}</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in -0.25in 0pt 0in\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in -0.25in 0pt 0in\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n</span></span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',311,0,0),
(102,'Iridotomy','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10pt\">&nbsp;{PRE-OP DIAGNOSIS}&nbsp;{SITE}&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 10pt\">{PROCEDURE}{SITE}</span></p>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt\">{POST-OP DIAGNOSIS}{SITE}</span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt\">Upon admission the patient the patient received on drop of Alcaine. The operative eye was constricted with one drop (Pilocarpine 2%). Immediately prior to the procedure the patient received one drop of Alcaine in both eyes. The patient was positioned carefully at the Zeiss YAG Laser with the head fixed in the correct position, the chin being in the chin rest and the forehead against the forehead band. Alcaine drops were instilled in both eyes to eliminate the blink reflex. A YAG Iridotomy contact lens was applied to the operative eye. The YAG laser machine was set as indicated and the laser was properly activated. A scan of the iris was performed to find a peripheral indentation or crypt and at this point the laser was focused appropriately and fired. Additional burns were applied as needed to make sure of the patency of the hole. The procedure was completed without complication or discomfort.&nbsp;The patient was discharged to home under self-care with instructions to return to the clinic postoperatively for intraocular pressure and absence of other symptoms in approximately one hour.&nbsp;The patient was given post-procedure instructions and instructed to return to the clinic in approximately one week for follow-up evaluation.</span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt\">{LAST NAME}{PATIENT FIRST NAME}{MIDDLE INITIAL}</span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt\">{SURGEON NAME}{DOS}</span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\">&nbsp;</div>',311,0,0),
(107,'Cataract Provisc','<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\"><span style=\"font-size: small\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman\">PREOPERATIVE DIAGNOSIS: {PRE-OP DIAGNOSIS}, {SITE}</span></span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\"><span style=\"font-size: small\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman\">Alpha 1-adrenergic receptor antagonist use</span></span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\"><span style=\"font-size: small\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman\">POSTOPERATIVE DIAGNOSIS: {POST-OP DIAGNOSIS},{SITE}</span></span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\"><span style=\"font-size: small\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman\">Floppy iris syndrome</span></span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\"><span style=\"font-size: small\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman\">OPERATIVE PROCEDURE:<strong> </strong>{PROCEDURE}{SITE}</span></span></div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in -0.25in 0pt 0in\"><b><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">DESCRIPTION:</span></b><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\"> The patient was admitted to the surgery center. Eye drops were instilled as ordered on arrival. Betadine solution diluted 1:1 with normal balanced salt solution was instilled. The peri-bulbar block administered by anesthesia. Refer to anesthesia record for medications used and amounts. The Honan balloon was placed on the eye at a pressure level of 30mm of mercury prior to surgery. The eye was tested and found to have good anesthesia and akinesia. The patient was taken to the operating room and prepped and draped in the usual sterile manner. The operating microscope was positioned and the lid speculum introduced. A stab paracentesis was placed at approximately 12 o&rsquo;clock position in clear cornea using the Diamond blade fully extended. Healon 5 viscoelastic was instilled in the eye. A groove incision was made with the Diamond blade at 0 .25mm at approximately 10 o&rsquo;clock position just anterior to the limbal vessels. The Diamond blade fully extended was inserted into the clear cornea up to the shoulder of the blade and then the angle of the blade is changed so that it is in the plane of the iris and then the anterior chamber is entered. A 27 gauge bent-tipped needle was used to make a continuous tear capsulorrhexis. A 27-gauge cannula attached to a syringe filled with balanced salt solution was then introduced to perform hydrodissection of the nucleus from the posterior layer of cortex. The phacoemulsification handpiece was inserted and phacoemulsification was performed. The nucleus was emulsified primarily in the posterior chamber. Cortical materials were removed using the irrigating and aspirating unit. The iris was noted to be &ldquo;floppy&rdquo; with a tendency to prolaspse from the paracentisis and the incision. The capsule appeared entirely intact with an intact capsulorrhexis and an intact posterior capsular bag. The delivery tip for the lens was introduced into the corneal incision just into the anterior chamber and then the intraocular lens implant was slowly injected into the posterior capsular bag. The residual Viscoelastic material was removed with the I&amp;A tip. Balanced salt solution was injected into the eye to fill it to the normal pressure. The eye was tested by pressing on the eye and the incision was noted to be watertight. The chamber remained deep. One drop of Pilocarpine 2% was applied to the eye. Antibiotic ointment was applied. The patient was taken to the recovery area in good condition. </span></div>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 12pt\">{LAST NAME}{MIDDLE INITIAL}{PATIENT FIRST NAME}{DOB}</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 12pt\">{SURGEON NAME}{DOS}</span></p>',312,0,0),
(68,'Cat/Sulcus placement','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in -0.5in 0pt 0in\"><b><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">Preoperative Diagnosis</span></b><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; {PRE-OP DIAGNOSIS}{SITE}</span></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-indent: 0.75in; margin: 0in -0.5in 0pt -0.75in\"><b><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">Postoperative Diagnosis</span></b><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;{POST-OP DIAGNOSIS}{SITE}</span></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-indent: 0.75in; margin: 0in -0.5in 0pt -0.75in\"><b><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">Operative Procedure</span></b><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>&nbsp;{PROCEDURE}{SITE}</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-indent: 0.75in; margin: 0in -0.5in 0pt -0.75in\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\"><b><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">Description</span></b><b>:</b> <span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">The patient was admitted to the surgery center.&nbsp;Eye drops were instilled as ordered </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">on arrival. </span><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">The peri-bulbar block was administered by the C.R.N A.&nbsp;Refer to anesthesia </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">{PROCEDURE}ecord for medications used and amounts.&nbsp;Following the injection, one drop of </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">Betadine solution which was diluted with balanced salt solution 1:1 was instilled.&nbsp;The Honan </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">balloon was placed on the operative eye at a pressure level of 20mm of mercury for approximately 20 minutes.&nbsp;The eye was tested and found to have good anesthesia and akinesia. The patient was </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">taken to the operating room and prepped and draped in the usual sterile technique.&nbsp;The operating </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">microscope was positioned and the lid speculum was inserted.&nbsp;At the onset of the procedure, the </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">eye was irrigated with balanced salt solution and the fornices swabbed with a Weck sponge.&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">Paracentesis was performed at approximately 2 o&rsquo;clock. Viscoelastic was instilled in the anterior </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">chamber to deepen it cornea from drying. A shelved self-sealing incision made with a Diamond </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">keratome blade at the 10 0&rsquo;clock position quadrant.&nbsp;Capsulotomy was performed with a </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">bent-tipped 25-gauge needle for 360 degrees in a circular continuous tear technique.&nbsp;Hydro </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">dissection was performed with balanced salt solution using an angled hydro dissection needle. </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">The phacoemulsification procedure was performed creating approximately 90% thickness </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">grooves going from the incision to 180 degrees opposite the incision and then cracking the groove </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">with a Grayson chopper held with the surgeon&rsquo;s left hand and the phaco tip with the right hand.&nbsp;The </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">lens was rotated in 90 degrees quadrants with each quadrant being grooved and cracked until all four </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">quadrants had been similarly prepared and the phacoemulsification tip used to remove each </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">of the four quadrants.&nbsp;I&amp;A was used to remove soft cortex for 360 degrees by a peeling technique.&nbsp;The posterior capsule was polished centrally and in any area that residual cortical tags remained. </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">The posterior surface of the anterior capsule was polished at 270 degrees opposite the incision.&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">The anterior chamber was deepened with viscoelastic.&nbsp;&nbsp; The injector was loaded with the lens implant.&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">The tip of the injector was inserted into the incision with gentle pressure on the plunger.</span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">&nbsp;The lens was then inserted into the ciliary sulcus and rotated into position. The I&amp;A tip was used to </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">remove Occucoat for 360 degrees in the anterior and posterior chambers.&nbsp;At the end of the </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">procedure, balanced salt solution was used to hydrate the incision along its ends and and </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">centrally and the anterior chamber was deepened with balanced salt solution and pressurized. </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">No sutures were placed at this point as testing of the wound showed it to be watertight because </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">of the internal flap mechanism.&nbsp;&nbsp; One drop of Pilocarpine 2%&nbsp;was instilled in the operative eye at</span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">the end of the case. All instruments and drapes were removed from the eye. Antibiotic ointment </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">was applied on the ocular surface. The patient was sent to the recovery room in good condition, </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">having tolerated the procedure well. Instructions were given to see Dr. Hiatt the day following the </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">procedure for follow-up evaluation, at which time further directions will be given.</span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in -0.5in 0pt -0.75in\">&nbsp;\r\n<p style=\"margin-left: 80px\">&nbsp;{LAST NAME}{MIDDLE INITIAL}{PATIENT FIRST NAME}{DOB}</p>\r\n<p style=\"margin-left: 80px\">SURGEON NAME} { DOS}</p>\r\n</div>',307,0,0),
