(101,'Cataract / IFIS','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in -0.5in 0pt 0in\"><b><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">Preoperative Diagnosis</span></b><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">:&nbsp;&nbsp; {PRE-OP DIAGNOSIS} {SITE} </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in -0.5in 0pt 0in\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Alpha-1 adrenergic receptor antagonist use</span></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-indent: 0.75in; margin: 0in -0.5in 0pt -0.75in\"><b><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">Postoperative Diagnosis</span></b><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">: {POST-OP DIAGNOSIS} {SITE}, floppy iris syndrome {SITE}</span></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-indent: 0.75in; margin: 0in -0.5in 0pt -0.75in\"><b><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">Operative Procedure</span></b><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; {PROCEDURE}{SITE} Phacoemulsification cataract extraction using</span></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-indent: 0.75in; margin: 0in -0.5in 0pt -0.75in\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; clear cornea </span><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">Incision with the foldable posterior chamber intraocular lens&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">plantation, {SITE}</span></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-indent: 27pt; margin: 0in -0.5in 0pt -0.75in\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div><b>Description:</b> The patient was admitted to the surgery center. Eye drops were instilled as ordered on arrival.&nbsp;The peri-bulbar block was administered by the C.R.N A. Refer to anesthesia record for medications used and amounts. Following the injection, one drop of Betadine solution which was diluted with balanced salt solution 1:1 was instilled. The Honan balloon was placed on the operative eye at a pressure level of 20mm of mercury for approximately 20 minutes. The eye was tested and found to have good anesthesia and akinesia. The patient was taken to the operating room and prepped and draped in the usual sterile technique. The operating microscope was positioned and the lid speculum was inserted. At the onset of the procedure, the eye was irrigated with balanced</div>\r\n<div>salt solution and the fornices swabbed with a Weck sponge. Paracentesis was performed at approximately 2 o&rsquo;clock. Viscoelastic was instilled in the anterior chamber to deepen it cornea from drying and to keep the visual clarity of the cornea surface at its optimum. A shelved self-sealing incision made with a Diamond keratome blade at the 10 0&rsquo;clock position quadrant. Capsulotomy was performed with a bent-tipped 25-gauge needle for 360 degrees in a circular continuous tear technique. Hydro dissection was performed with balanced salt solution using an angled hydro dissection needle. The phacoemulsification procedure was performed creating approximately 90% thickness grooves going from the incision to 180 degrees opposite the incision and then cracking the groove with a Grayson chopper held with the surgeon&rsquo;s left hand and the phaco tip with the right hand. The lens was rotated in 90 degrees quadrants with each quadrant being grooved and cracked until all four quadrants had been similarly prepared and the phacoemulsification tip used to remove each of the four quadrants. I&amp;A was used to remove soft cortex for 360 degrees by a peeling technique. The posterior capsule was polished centrally and in any area that residual cortical tags remained. The posterior surface of the anterior capsule was polished at 270 degrees opposite the incision. The anterior chamber was deepened with viscoelastic. The injector was loaded with the lens implant. The tip of the injector was inserted into the incision with gentle pressure on the plunger. The lens was then inserted into the capsule bag and rotated into position. The I&amp;A tip was used to remove viscoelastic for 360 degrees in the anterior and posterior chambers. At the end of the procedure, balanced salt solution was used to hydrate the incision along its ends and and centrally and the anterior chamber was deepened with</div>\r\n<div>balanced salt solution and pressurized. No sutures were placed at this point as testing of the wound showed it to be watertight because of the internal flap mechanism. One drop of pilocarpiine 2% was instilled in the operative eye at the end of the case. All instruments and drapes were removed from the eye. Antibiotic ointment was applied on the ocular surface. The patient was sent to the recovery room in good condition, having tolerated the procedure well. Instructions were given to see Dr. Hiatt the day following the procedure for follow-up evaluation, at which time further directions will be given.</div>\r\n<p>{LAST NAME} {MIDDLE INITIAL} {PATIENT FIRST NAME} {DOB}</p>\r\n<p>{SURGEON NAME} {DOS}</p>',307,0,0),
(91,'Repair of Entropian','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in -167.25pt 0pt 0in\">Preoperative Diagnosis:&nbsp;Entropian {SITE} Lower Lid</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in -167.25pt 0pt 0in\">Postoperative Diagnosis:&nbsp;Same</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\">Operative Procedure:&nbsp;Entropian Repair {SITE} Lower Lid</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\">Description:&nbsp;The patient was admitted to the surgery center and given 5mg of Valium orally. The patient was taken to the operating room and prepped and draped in the usual sterile manner. The operating microscope was positioned.&nbsp;Drops of Tetracaine were instilled into the operative eye. Xylocaine 2% PF, approximately 1 ml was injected along the lower eye lid.&nbsp;Double armed 5-0 Chromic Gut suture was placed with the suture going in from the inside of the eyelid below the inferior tarsal plate, exiting just inferior to the lid margin. Two sutures were passed right next to each other and tied.&nbsp;Three of these sutures were placed in the right lower eyelid and two were placed on the left to create an ectropian.&nbsp;Tobradex ointment was placed along the lower lid line.&nbsp;The patient was taken to the recovery room in good condition. Post-operative instructions were given to the patient prior to discharge.</div>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;{LAST NAME}{MIDDLE INITIAL}{PATIENT FIRST NAME}{DOB}</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;{SURGEON NAME}{DOS}</p>',311,0,0),
(92,'Entropian','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in -167.25pt 0pt 0in\"><span style=\"font-size: x-small\">Preoperative Diagnosis:&nbsp;Entropian (site) Lower Lid</span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in -167.25pt 0pt 0in\"><span style=\"font-size: x-small\">Postoperative Diagnosis:&nbsp;Same</span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\"><span style=\"font-size: x-small\">Operative Procedure:&nbsp;Entropian Repair (site) Lower Lid</span>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\"><span style=\"font-size: small\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman\"><strong>Description</strong>:&nbsp;The patient was admitted to the surgery center and given 5mg of Valium orally. The patient was taken to the operating room and prepped and draped in the usual sterile manner. The operating microscope was positioned.&nbsp;Drops of Tetracaine were instilled into the operative eye. Xylocaine 2% PF, approximately 1 ml was injected along the lower eye lid.&nbsp;Double armed 5-0 Chromic Gut suture was placed with the suture going in from the inside of the eyelid below the inferior tarsal plate, exiting just inferior to the lid margin. Two sutures were passed right next to each other and tied.&nbsp;Three of these sutures were placed in the right lower eyelid and two were placed on the left to create an ectropian.&nbsp;Tobradex ointment was placed along the lower lid line.&nbsp;The patient was taken to the recovery room in good condition. Post-operative instructions were given to the patient prior to discharge.</span></span></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\">.{LAST NAME}{MIDDLE INITIAL}{PATIENT FIRST NAME}{DOB}</div>\r\n<p>{SURGEON NAME}{DOS}</p>',311,0,0),
(93,'Limbal Relaxing Incision','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\">PREOPERATIVE DIAGNOSIS:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Corneal Astigmatism,&nbsp;{SITE} eye</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\">POSTOPERATIVE DIAGNOSIS:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Same</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-indent: -219pt; margin: 0in 0in 0pt 219pt\">OPERATIVE PROCEDURE:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Limbal relaxing astigmatic keratotomy,{SITE} eye</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-indent: -3in; margin: 0in 0in 0pt 3in\"><span style=\"font-size: medium\">&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<p><span style=\"display: none\" id=\"1335809043910E\">&nbsp;</span><span style=\"display: none\" id=\"1335809036449E\">&nbsp;</span></p>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in -0.25in 0pt 0in\">&nbsp;\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in -0.25in 0pt 0in\"><b><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">DESCRIPTION:</span></b><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\"> In the holding area, the patient was given Valium 5 mg p.o.&nbsp;A drop of Nevanec, </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in -0.25in 0pt 0in\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">Vigamox and Tetracaine were given upon arrival.&nbsp;The patient was taken to the operating room and </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in -0.25in 0pt 0in\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">prepped and draped in the usual sterile manner.&nbsp;The operating microscope was positioned and the lid speculum introduced. Two drops of Tetracaine 0.5% were instilled in both eyes prior to the start of the procedure. &nbsp;&nbsp;A marker was used and marks were placed at the limbus at the ___ degree axis with the Diamond blade set at 600 microns for a length of ______millimeters and ____limbal-relaxing incision </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in -0.25in 0pt 0in\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">was made.&nbsp;The patient was taken to the recovery area in good condition. </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\"><b>&nbsp;</b></div>\r\n</div>\r\n<p>{LAST NAME}{MIDDLE INITIAL}{PATIENT FIRST NAME}{DOB}</p>\r\n<p>{SURGEON NAME}{DOS}</p>',311,0,0),
(105,'YAG','<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt\">{PRE-OP DIAGNOSIS}{SITE}</span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt\">{PROCEDURE}{SITE}</span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt\">{POST-OP DIAGNOSIS}{SITE}</span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\"><span style=\"font-size: 10pt\">Upon admission the patient the patient received one drop of Alcaine. The eye was dilated with one drop of Phenylephrine 2.5% and Tropicamide 1%. One drop of Iopidine 0.5% was instilled in the operative eye. Immediately prior to the procedure an addition drop of Alcaine was instilled in both eyes to eliminate the blink reflex. The patient was positioned carefully at the Zeiss YAG Laser with the head fixed in the correct position, the chin being in the chin rest and the forehead against the forehead band. A YAG contact lens was applied to the operative eye. The YAG laser machine was set as indicated. The number of YAG laser bursts used are as indicated.&nbsp; Care was taken to ensure that the laser was always focused on the posterior chamber capsule to avoid damage to the ocular tissue or lens implant. The procedure was completed without complication or discomfort. The patient was discharged to home under self-care. The patient was given post-procedure instructions and instructed to return to the clinic in approximately one week for follow-up evaluation.</span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<p>{LAST NAME}{PATIENT FIRST NAME}{MIDDLE INITIAL}</p>\r\n<p>{SURGEON NAME}{DOS}</p>',311,0,0),
(70,'Cat. / Synechia ','<p>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in -0.5in 0pt 0in\"><b><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">Preoperative Diagnosis</span></b><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;{PRE-OP DIAGNOSIS} {SITE}, Synechia {SITE}</span></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-indent: 0.75in; margin: 0in -0.5in 0pt -0.75in\"><b><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">Postoperative Diagnosis</span></b><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">:&nbsp; &nbsp;{POST-OP DIAGNOSIS}&nbsp;{SITE}</span></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-indent: 0.75in; margin: 0in -0.5in 0pt -0.75in\"><b><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">Operative Procedure</span></b><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">:&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;</span><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">&nbsp;{PROCEDURE}&nbsp; {SITE}, Synechiolysis {SITE}\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\"><b><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">Description</span></b><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">:</span> <span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">The patient was admitted to the surgery center.&nbsp;Eye drops were instilled as ordered on </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">arrival.&nbsp;The peri-bulbar block was administered by the C.R.N A.&nbsp;Refer to anesthesia record for</span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">medications used and amounts.&nbsp;Following the injection, one drop of Betadine solution which was </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">diluted with balanced salt solution 1:1 was instilled.&nbsp;The Honan balloon was placed on the operative eye</span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">at a pressure level of 20mm of mercury for approximately 20 minutes.&nbsp;The eye was tested and found to </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">have good anesthesia and akinesia. The patient was taken to the operating room and prepped and </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">draped in the usual sterile technique.&nbsp;The operating microscope was positioned and the lid speculum </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">was inserted.&nbsp;At the </span><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">onset of the procedure, the eye was irrigated with balanced salt solution and the </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">fornices swabbed with a Weck sponge.&nbsp;Paracentesis was performed at approximately 2 o&rsquo;clock. </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">Viscoelastic was instilled in the anterior chamber to deepen it and used to break posterior synechia.</span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">A shelved self-sealing incision made with a Diamond keratome blade at the 10 o&rsquo;clock position quadrant.</span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">Capsulotomy was performed with a bent-tipped 25-gauge needle for 360 degrees in a circular </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">continuous tear technique.&nbsp;Hydro dissection was performed with balanced salt solution using an angled</span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">&nbsp;hydro dissection needle. The phacoemulsification procedure was performed creating approximately </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">90% thickness grooves going from the incision to 180 degrees opposite the incision and then cracking </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">the groove with a Grayson chopper held with the surgeon&rsquo;s left hand and the phaco tip with the right </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">hand.&nbsp;The lens was rotated in 90 degrees quadrants with each quadrant being grooved and cracked </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">until all four quadrants had been similarly prepared and the phacoemulsification tip used to remove </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">each of the four quadrants.&nbsp;I&amp;A was used to remove soft cortex for 360 degrees by a peeling technique.&nbsp;</span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">The posterior capsule was polished centrally and in any area that residual cortical tags remained. The </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">posterior surface of the anterior capsule was polished at 270 degrees opposite the incision.&nbsp;The </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">anterior chamber was deepened with viscoelastic.&nbsp;&nbsp; The injector was loaded with the lens implant.&nbsp;The </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">tip of the injector was inserted into the incision with gentle pressure on the plunger.&nbsp;The lens was then</span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">inserted into the capsule bag and rotated into position. The I&amp;A tip was used to remove the viscoelastic</span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">for 360 degrees in the anterior and posterior chambers.&nbsp;At the end of the procedure, balanced salt </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">solution was used to hydrate the incision along its ends and and centrally and the anterior chamber </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">was deepened with balanced salt solution and pressurized. No sutures were placed at this point as </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">testing of the wound showed it to be watertight because of the internal flap mechanism.&nbsp;&nbsp; One drop </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">of Pilocarpine 2% was instilled in the operative eye at the end of the case. All instruments and drapes </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">were removed from the eye. Antibiotic ointment was applied on the ocular surface. The patient was</span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">sent to the recovery room in good condition, having tolerated the procedure well. Instructions were </span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">given to see Dr. Hiatt the day following the procedure for follow-up evaluation, at which time further</span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\"><span style=\"font-size: 11pt\">directions will be given.</span></div>\r\n</span></div>\r\n<div style=\"text-indent: 0.75in; margin: 0in -0.5in 0pt -0.75in\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"text-indent: 27pt; margin: 0in -0.5in 0pt -0.75in\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin-top: 0in; margin-bottom: 0pt; margin-right: -0.5in\">{LAST NAME}{MIDDLE INITIAL}&nbsp;{PATIENT FIRST NAME}{DOB}</div>\r\n<p>{SURGEON NAME} {DOS}</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>',307,0,0),
(76,'Crystal Lens Implant','<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\"><span style=\"font-size: small\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman\">PREOPERATIVE DIAGNOSIS:&nbsp;&nbsp; {PRE-OP DIAGNOSIS}, {SITE}</span></span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\"><span style=\"font-size: small\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman\">POSTOPERATIVE DIAGNOSIS: {POST-OP DIAGNOSIS},{SITE}</span></span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\"><span style=\"font-size: small\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman\">OPERATIVE PROCEDURE:<strong>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </strong>{PROCEDURE}{SITE}</span></span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\"><span style=\"font-size: small\"><span style=\"font-family: Times New Roman\">\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in -0.25in 0pt 0in\"><b><span style=\"font-size: 12pt\">DESCRIPTION:</span></b><span style=\"font-size: 12pt\"> The patient was admitted to the surgery center.&nbsp;Eye drops were instilled as ordered on arrival. Betadine solution diluted 1:1 with normal balanced salt solution was instilled.&nbsp;The peri-bulbar block administered by anesthesia. Refer to anesthesia record for</span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in -0.25in 0pt 0in\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt\">medications used and amounts administered. The Honan balloon was placed on the eye at a pressure level of 30mm of mercury prior to surgery.&nbsp;The eye was tested and found to have good anesthesia and akinesia.&nbsp;The patient was taken to the operating room and prepped and draped in the usual sterile manner.&nbsp;The operating microscope was positioned and the lid speculum introduced.&nbsp;A stab paracentesis was placed at approximately 12 o&rsquo;clock position in clear cornea using the Diamond blade fully extended.&nbsp;Viscoelastic was instilled in the eye.&nbsp;A groove incision was made with the Diamond blade at 0 .25mm at approximately 10 o&rsquo;clock position just anterior to the limbal vessels.&nbsp;The Diamond blade fully extended was inserted into the clear cornea up to the shoulder of the blade and then the angle of the blade is changed so that it is in the plane of the iris and then the anterior chamber is entered.&nbsp;A 27 gauge bent-tipped needle was used to make a continuous tear capsulorrhexis.&nbsp;A 27-gauge cannula attached to a syringe filled with balanced salt solution was then introduced to perform hydrodissection of the nucleus from the posterior layer of cortex.&nbsp;The phacoemulsification handpiece was inserted and phacoemulsification was performed.&nbsp;The nucleus was emulsified primarily in the posterior chamber.&nbsp;Cortical materials were removed using the irrigating and aspirating unit. Viscoelastic was instilled in the anterior chamber and in the posterior capsular bag.&nbsp;The capsule appeared entirely intact with an intact capsulorrhexis and an intact posterior capsular bag.&nbsp;The delivery tip for the Crystalens lens was introduced into the corneal incision just into the anterior chamber and then intraocular lens implant was slowly injected into the posterior capsular bag.&nbsp;The residual Viscoelastic material was removed with the I&amp;A tip.&nbsp;Balanced salt solution was injected into the eye to fill it to the normal pressure.&nbsp;The eye was tested by pressing on the eye and the incision was noted to be watertight.&nbsp;The chamber remained deep. Antibiotic ointment was applied.&nbsp;The patient was taken to the recovery area in good condition. </span></div>\r\n</span></span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\"><b>{LAST NAME}{MIDDLE INITIAL}{PATIENT FIRST NAME}{DOB}</b></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\">\r\n<p>{SURGEON NAME}{DOS}</p>\r\n</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\"><b>&nbsp;</b></div>',311,0,0),
