r lens implant was slowly injected into the posterior capsular bag. The residual Viscoelastic material was removed with the I&amp;A tip. Balanced salt solution was injected into the eye to fill it to the normal pressure.&nbsp;The eye was tested by pressing on the eye and the incision was noted to be watertight.&nbsp;The chamber remained deep.&nbsp;One drop of Pilocarpine 2% was applied to the eye.&nbsp;Antibiotic ointment was applied.&nbsp;The patient was taken to the recovery area in good condition. </span></div>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 12pt\">{LAST NAME}{MIDDLE INITIAL}{PATIENT FIRST NAME}{DOB}</span></p>\r\n<p><span style=\"font-size: 12pt\">{SURGEON NAME}{DOS}</span></p>',311,0,0),
