 was made at ___ degrees. A second stab paracentisis was made at 6:00 o&rsquo;clock and a 0.25mm groove made for the incision at 10:00 o&rsquo;clock. A keratome blade was used to slightly enlarge this incision. The ICL was slowly injected into the anterior chamber, verifying that the positioning hole was on top, centered, and the orientation hole on the right leading haptic was on the right to ensure the lens was being inserted into the eye in the correct orientation. Once the lens was in, additional Occucoat was instilled into the eye. The ICL manipulator was used to tuck the leading and trailing haptic into the ciliary sulcus, under the iris. Viscoelastic was removed by flushing the anterior chamber with 9cc of BSS. Miochol was instilled to reduce the pupil over the haptics. The lens implant appeared to be stable and centered. The speculum and drape were removed and Vigamox drops were instilled. implant was slowly injected into the posterior capsular bag. . Antibiotic ointment was applied. The patient was taken to the recovery area in good condition</span></div>\r\n</span></span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\">&nbsp;</div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\"><span style=\"font-size: 12pt\">{LAST NAME}{MIDDLE INITIAL}{PATIENT FIRST NAME}{DOB}</span></div>\r\n<div style=\"margin: 0in 0in 0pt\">\r\n<p>{SURGEON NAME}{DOS}</p>\r\n</div>',311,0,0),
